1
00:00:59,977 --> 00:01:03,522
我在138街的办公室里工作。
I was working in my office on 138th Street.

2
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:11,196
主要是治疗一战中受伤的人，比如我。
Mostly fixing up banged-up guys, like myself, from the Great War.

3
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:12,948
看到了吗?美丽。
See? Beautiful.

4
00:01:13,031 --> 00:01:16,660
所有的伤害都是世界乐于忘记的。
All from injuries the world was happy to forget.

5
00:01:17,327 --> 00:01:21,081
修整面部，振奋精神，唱歌。
Fixing faces, lifting spirits, singing songs.

6
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:29,756
花生我的眼睛落在法国了。
Peanuts I left my eye in France.

7
00:01:31,591 --> 00:01:35,887
我经常因为尝试研发新药而被医学委员会留校察看。
And I was constantly on probation with the medical board for trying to make new medicines.

8
00:01:35,971 --> 00:01:43,103
我的意思是，我们需要当时还不存在的药物来度过痛苦和紧张的一天。
I mean, we needed medicines that didn't exist yet just to get through the day, with the pain and the nerves.

9
00:01:43,562 --> 00:01:45,897
我希望这是一种更好的药。这就是我要说的。
I hope this is a better pill. That's all I'm saying.

10
00:01:45,981 --> 00:01:47,024
我希望你是对的。
I hope you're right.

11
00:01:48,692 --> 00:01:50,944
有些人比其他人做得更好。
Some worked better than others.

12
00:01:52,029 --> 00:01:53,572
这是我今天的第二天。
This is my second of the day.

13
00:01:55,991 --> 00:01:57,159
我感觉很好。
And I feel great.

14
00:01:57,868 --> 00:01:59,369
维克多，你想尝尝吗?
Victor, you wanna try one?

15
00:01:59,828 --> 00:02:01,621
是的。我下周会试试新的。
Yeah. I'll try the new one next week.

16
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:04,207
好吧。这会给你活力。
All right. That gives you zing.

17
00:02:04,666 --> 00:02:07,336
把裤子穿上，伯特。我帮你修好了。
Put your pants on, Burt. I repaired 'em for you.

18
00:02:08,003 --> 00:02:09,004
你还好吗?
Are you all right?

19
00:02:09,087 --> 00:02:13,342
因为我在战争中受伤，我的背部有一个我讨厌的支架。
Because of my war injuries, I had a back brace I hated.

20
00:02:13,425 --> 00:02:16,904
如果他们不把这地方关了他们就会把你关起来。
They're gonna put you away if they don't close this place down.

21
00:02:16,928 --> 00:02:17,989
那没用，雪莉。
That's not helpful, Shirley.

22
00:02:18,013 --> 00:02:19,848
实验医学。
Experimental medicine.

23
00:02:20,474 --> 00:02:21,475
你看起来不错。
You look good.

24
00:02:21,558 --> 00:02:22,827
-感染怎么样了?-好吧。
- How's the infection? - All right.

25
00:02:22,851 --> 00:02:24,311
好，好，好，好，好。
Good, good, good, good, good.

26
00:02:24,394 --> 00:02:25,520
我明白了。
And I got the message.

27
00:02:25,604 --> 00:02:26,980
还不需要付钱。
No need to pay yet.

28
00:02:27,064 --> 00:02:28,482
伯特，你有留言。
Burt, you got messages.

29
00:02:28,565 --> 00:02:30,859
你父母打电话来了。他们不能去度假了。
Your parents called. They can't make the holiday.

30
00:02:30,942 --> 00:02:33,320
赫伯·盖兹打电话来问滴耳液的事。
Herb Getz called about the ear drops.

31
00:02:33,403 --> 00:02:36,782
哈罗德·伍德曼打来电话。在这个地址和他见面。
And Harold Woodman called. Meet him at this address.

32
00:02:36,865 --> 00:02:38,950
直接走进去。紧迫。
Walk right in. Urgent.

33
00:02:49,461 --> 00:02:54,174
我和一个律师一起工作，他是我战时最好的朋友，哈罗德·伍德曼。
I worked with an attorney, my best friend from the war, Harold Woodman.

34
00:02:54,883 --> 00:02:55,884
嘿,伯特。
Hey, Burt.

35
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:58,428
这是怎么回事?这是什么地方?
What is going on? What is this place?

36
00:02:58,512 --> 00:03:00,555
-这案子很重要。——是吗?
- It's a very important case. - Yeah?

37
00:03:00,639 --> 00:03:02,099
-报酬非常丰厚。——好。
- Pays very handsomely. - Nice.

38
00:03:02,182 --> 00:03:03,284
我们有很多未付的账单。
We have a lot of back bills.

39
00:03:03,308 --> 00:03:05,519
人们依赖我们，依赖我们的生意。
People depend on us, our business.

40
00:03:05,602 --> 00:03:08,480
最重要的是，它对你我都很有意义。
Most importantly, it's very meaningful to both you and I.

41
00:03:08,563 --> 00:03:09,689
有意义如何?
Meaningful how?

42
00:03:09,773 --> 00:03:12,317
你关心的是年度晚会，不是吗?-是的。
Well, you care about the annual gala, - don't you? - Yeah.

43
00:03:12,401 --> 00:03:17,739
你总说我们退伍军人聚会很重要，被人记住。-是的。
And you always say it's important for us vets to have reunions, - to be remembered. - It is.

44
00:03:17,823 --> 00:03:21,535
你说我们聚在一起唱歌是一剂良药。你不这么说吗?
And you say it's great medicine for us to get together and sing. Don't you say that?

45
00:03:21,618 --> 00:03:22,911
这是怎么回事?
Where's this going?

46
00:03:23,328 --> 00:03:28,333
这是一个特定的程序，我知道你喜欢某些程序。
It's going to a particular procedure, and I know how you prefer some procedures over others.

47
00:03:28,417 --> 00:03:29,543
告诉我是什么。
Just tell me what it is.

48
00:03:29,626 --> 00:03:31,044
什么……什么样的程序?
What... What kind of procedure?

49
00:03:31,753 --> 00:03:33,505
你拿这些花干什么?
What are you doing with these flowers?

50
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:36,049
和碧翠丝的晚餐约会。
Dinner date with Beatrice.

51
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:38,385
-和碧翠丝的晚餐约会?——是的。
- Dinner date with Beatrice? - Yes.

52
00:03:38,468 --> 00:03:40,887
-太令人失望了。-她是我妻子。
- So disappointing. - She's my wife.

53
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:43,140
他能做这个手术吗?
Is he all right to perform the procedure?

54
00:03:45,434 --> 00:03:48,437
是的。他……他是。没关系。
Yes. He... He is. It's okay.

55
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:49,789
-他不会这么做的-他会这么做的
- He's not gonna do it. - He's gonna do it.

56
00:03:49,813 --> 00:03:50,939
-冷静点。-你是谁?
- Calm down. - Who is this?

57
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:54,025
这是莉兹·米金斯，伯特。
This is Liz Meekins, Burt.

58
00:03:54,109 --> 00:04:00,157
Meekins吗?例如，关于……他是我的父亲。我知道你很崇拜他。
Meekins? As in, relation to... He's my father. I know you admire him very much.

59
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,909
-我的天啊。是的。-我们都是。做的。
- Oh, my God. Yes. - We both did. Do.

60
00:04:02,993 --> 00:04:04,202
真的。
I really do.

61
00:04:04,286 --> 00:04:08,457
这就是为什么他要在我们今年的同学会上讲话。
That's why he's gonna speak at our reunion this year.

62
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:10,333
很高兴见到你。
Very nice to meet you.

63
00:04:10,876 --> 00:04:12,210
我们要在这里见你父亲吗?
Are we meeting your father here?

64
00:04:12,294 --> 00:04:13,420
让她说完，伯特。
Let her finish, Burt.

65
00:04:14,212 --> 00:04:17,382
我父亲昨天坐船回来的。
My father came back yesterday on a boat.

66
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:20,802
好的。他去欧洲出差了，对吧?
Okay. He goes to Europe on business, right?

67
00:04:20,886 --> 00:04:21,988
他是被虫子咬了还是怎么了?
Did he catch a bug or something?

68
00:04:22,012 --> 00:04:23,156
我来看看他。他在哪里?
I'll look at him. Where is he?

69
00:04:23,180 --> 00:04:24,306
你应该看看他。
You should see him.

70
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:26,016
是的。来吧。我们走吧。
Yeah. Come on. Let's go.

71
00:04:26,641 --> 00:04:28,810
这地方真漂亮。看看它。
This place is gorgeous. Look at it.

72
00:04:28,894 --> 00:04:33,857
所以,……那个"安静不动"的比尔将军呢?
So, where... where is, uh, the good General "Quiet and Still" Bill?

73
00:04:39,613 --> 00:04:40,739
原谅我。
Excuse me.

74
00:04:41,531 --> 00:04:43,658
我今天过敏得厉害。
My allergies are terrible today.

75
00:04:44,075 --> 00:04:47,913
我一觉醒来，鼻窦里都是，一整天都是。
I wake up, it's in my sinus, and it's the whole day.

76
00:04:48,455 --> 00:04:51,139
我不知道你在干什么，我也不想知道你在干什么。
I don't know what you're doing, and I don't wanna know what you're doing.

77
00:04:52,792 --> 00:04:56,213
两小时后，防腐师就会来了。
You have two hours until the embalmer comes.

78
00:04:57,214 --> 00:05:00,008
发生了什么事?他本来要在晚会上讲话的。
What happened? He was gonna speak at the gala.

79
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:03,595
你会帮我的，是吗?
You will help me, won't you?

80
00:05:03,678 --> 00:05:05,448
我不相信他是自然死亡。
I'm not buying that he died of natural causes.

81
00:05:05,472 --> 00:05:07,098
他是个非常健康的人。
He was a very healthy man.

82
00:05:07,682 --> 00:05:09,042
我家里没人同意我的看法。
No one in my family agrees with me.

83
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:10,495
他们都错了。他们都是骗子。
They're all wrong. They're all liars.

84
00:05:10,519 --> 00:05:12,062
我要尸检。
I want an autopsy.

85
00:05:12,521 --> 00:05:13,801
这是正确的。这是你的权利。
That's correct. It is your right.

86
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:15,357
你父亲没有留下遗嘱就去世了。
Your father died intestate.

87
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:17,234
你是他的近亲。我看了报纸。
You're the next of kin. I read the papers.

88
00:05:18,109 --> 00:05:20,237
我讨厌验尸，哈罗德。你知道的。
I hate autopsies, Harold. You know that.

89
00:05:20,779 --> 00:05:22,197
我们必须这么做，伯特。
We have to do it, Burt.

90
00:05:23,198 --> 00:05:25,700
比尔·"安静与宁静"·米金斯是我们相遇的原因。
Bill "Quiet and Still" Meekins is the reason we met.

91
00:05:25,784 --> 00:05:27,160
他组建了我们的团。
He formed our regiment.

92
00:05:28,245 --> 00:05:30,413
这样的人怎么会死了?
How did a man like this end up dead?

93
00:05:30,497 --> 00:05:31,817
你是说这很可疑?
You're telling me it's suspicious?

94
00:05:32,165 --> 00:05:33,833
是的，我告诉你这很可疑。
Yes, I'm telling you it's suspicious.

95
00:05:35,502 --> 00:05:36,670
你愿意和我一起唱吗?
Will you please sing with me?

96
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:39,047
他说你打仗的时候经常和他一起唱歌。
He said that you used to sing with him when you were at war.

97
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:40,382
他非常喜欢。
He enjoyed it so much.

98
00:05:41,216 --> 00:05:57,357
珍贵的回忆看不见的天使从某处送到我的灵魂快点。
- Precious memories - HAROLD: Memories Unseen angels Sent from somewhere to my soul Hurry up.

99
00:05:58,066 --> 00:06:01,570
你只有两个小时去做你想做的事。
You only have two hours to do whatever it is you're gonna do.

100
00:06:01,653 --> 00:06:05,865
好吧。你得去做尸检，然后马上到明特斯餐厅找我。
All right. You have to do the autopsy, and immediately after, meet me at Minters Restaurant.

101
00:06:05,949 --> 00:06:07,093
我要知道你找到了什么。
I need to know what you find.

102
00:06:07,117 --> 00:06:08,577
她为什么说两个小时?
Why did she say two hours?

103
00:06:08,660 --> 00:06:10,078
因为我们在殡仪馆。
Because we're in the mortician.

104
00:06:10,161 --> 00:06:11,580
他们会让他下葬的。
They're gonna put him in the ground.

105
00:06:12,956 --> 00:06:15,083
明特餐厅，5点后。
Minters Restaurant, after 5:00.

106
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:16,686
你得把他弄出去。
You've gotta get him out of here.

107
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:17,950
我们该走了，伯特。
Yeah, we should get going, Burt.

108
00:06:18,795 --> 00:06:21,214
哈罗德?我不知道你在做什么。
Harold? I don't know what you think you're doin'.

109
00:06:21,298 --> 00:06:23,300
莉兹，失陪一下。你好。
Liz, excuse me. Hello.

110
00:06:24,509 --> 00:06:26,428
你的箱子里有个白人尸体。
You got a dead white man in a box.

111
00:06:27,429 --> 00:06:28,597
连棺材都没有。
Not even a casket.

112
00:06:29,764 --> 00:06:33,184
重要人物，躺在老木头做的松盒子里。
Important man, in a pine box of old wood.

113
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:35,228
甚至连车顶都没有。
Doesn't even have a top on it.

114
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:37,606
他的女儿在哭。
His daughter's cryin'.

115
00:06:37,689 --> 00:06:39,458
你觉得谁会惹上麻烦?
Who do you think is gonna get in trouble here?

116
00:06:39,482 --> 00:06:40,984
-那个黑人，就是他。——弥尔顿。
- The Black man, that's who. - Milton.

117
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:46,656
现在我们得把他，我们的领袖，我们团的创始人，送进卡车。
Right now we need to get him, our leader, who founded our regiment, into the truck.

118
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,450
做尸检。
Do the autopsy.

119
00:06:50,201 --> 00:06:52,370
之后马上到敏特餐厅见我。
Meet me at Minters Restaurant immediately after.

120
00:06:52,454 --> 00:06:53,496
-知道了。-我需要知道。
- Got it. - I need to know.

121
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:54,640
我要知道你找到了什么。
I need to know what you found.

122
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:55,665
好的。
Okay.

123
00:06:55,749 --> 00:06:57,589
- Minters餐厅5点见——弥尔顿。弥尔顿。
- Minters Restaurant at 5:00. - Milton. Milton.

124
00:06:58,168 --> 00:06:59,252
请小心。
Please be careful.

125
00:06:59,336 --> 00:07:01,254
它的轮子坏了。
It's got a bum wheel.

126
00:07:01,338 --> 00:07:02,756
-那可不小心。——弥尔顿。
- That's not careful. - Milton.

127
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:05,401
所以你永远别想开我的车。
This is why you'll never drive my car.

128
00:07:05,425 --> 00:07:07,135
防腐师会来取这个。
The embalmer is coming for this.

129
00:07:07,218 --> 00:07:10,472
你最好在这里。两个小时。
You better be here. Two hours.

130
00:07:12,641 --> 00:07:13,761
你还记得伯特吧?
You remember Burt, don't you?

131
00:07:14,601 --> 00:07:16,728
-当然。-厄玛·圣克莱尔。
- Of course. - Irma St. Clair.

132
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:18,813
-你好，伯特。-你好，厄玛。
- Hello, Burt. - Hello, Irma.

133
00:07:19,481 --> 00:07:20,690
不要紧张。
Don't be nervous.

134
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:22,567
我一个月至少做两次尸检。
I do at least two autopsies a month.

135
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:25,445
我这辈子做过两次尸检。
I've done two autopsies my whole life.

136
00:07:25,528 --> 00:07:31,409
一个是为了证明我没有在某人的小肠上留下夹子，另一个是为了取下我留在某人小肠上的夹子。
One to prove I didn't leave a clamp on someone's small intestine, the other to remove a clamp I did leave on someone's small intestine.

137
00:07:31,785 --> 00:07:33,995
现在我们知道你对小肠子很在行，伯特。
Now we know you're good with small intestines, Burt.

138
00:07:34,079 --> 00:07:35,080
谢谢你！
Thank you.

139
00:07:37,832 --> 00:07:40,251
你和伯特应该找个时间喝杯咖啡，厄玛。
You know, you and Burt should get coffee sometimes, Irma.

140
00:07:40,877 --> 00:07:42,921
也许你和厄玛应该找个时间喝杯咖啡。
Maybe you and Irma should get coffee sometime.

141
00:07:43,004 --> 00:07:44,214
我们是朋友，米尔顿。
We're friends, Milton.

142
00:07:45,006 --> 00:07:48,426
你知道吗，厄玛，他妻子在家人面前都不替他说话。
You know, Irma, his wife wouldn't stand up for him to her family.

143
00:07:48,968 --> 00:07:51,262
他们已经一年多没住在一起了。
They haven't lived together in over a year.

144
00:07:51,346 --> 00:07:53,390
这就是我的情况。不是现在。
That is my situation. Not now.

145
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:54,808
我只想看到你快乐。
I just wanna see you happy.

146
00:07:54,891 --> 00:08:00,063
死人会让你意识到时间是短暂的，而爱是真实的，如果你知道它是什么的话。
Dead man makes you realize time is short and love is real, if you know what it is.

147
00:08:04,401 --> 00:08:06,945
-这是怎么回事?——解剖。文书工作。
- What's going on here? - Autopsy. Paperwork.

148
00:08:09,572 --> 00:08:12,242
警察正等着尸体运回停尸间。
The police are waiting for this body to return to the mortuary.

149
00:08:14,035 --> 00:08:16,496
我们越早开始，他就越早出来。
The sooner we start, the sooner he's out.

150
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:19,165
这两个人必须马上离开。
These two men need to leave immediately.

151
00:08:19,249 --> 00:08:21,501
他们是退伍军人。他们为国家服务。
They're veterans. They served their country.

152
00:08:21,584 --> 00:08:22,585
去麦基餐厅等着。
Go wait at McGee's.

153
00:08:22,669 --> 00:08:23,854
我们会在楼下麦基餐厅。
We'll be downstairs at McGee's.

154
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:25,046
麦基的。
At McGee's.

155
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:27,882
厄玛的葡萄牙语。这是不同的。
Irma's Portuguese. That's different.

156
00:08:34,347 --> 00:08:36,057
我不知道你是葡萄牙人。
I didn't know you were Portuguese.

157
00:08:37,809 --> 00:08:38,810
我不是。
I'm not.

158
00:08:39,686 --> 00:08:41,521
你先来还是我先来?
Do you wanna start this or shall I?

159
00:08:42,689 --> 00:08:44,733
只是有点激动，因为我认识他。
Uh, just emotional because I knew him.

160
00:08:46,943 --> 00:08:48,303
如果你愿意，你可以签了这个。
You can just sign this if you want.

161
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:49,404
不不不不不。
