00:16:20,938 --> 00:16:23,816
伍德曼先生，你为什么不告诉他你为什么在寨子里。
Mr. Woodman, why don't you tell him why you're here in the stockade.

330
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:25,526
我们为什么在寨子里?
Why are we in a stockade?

331
00:16:25,610 --> 00:16:27,028
不服从。
Insubordination.

332
00:16:27,111 --> 00:16:28,487
你不听话吗?
Were you insubordinate?

333
00:16:28,571 --> 00:16:29,864
——是的。——为什么?
- Yes. - Why?

334
00:16:29,947 --> 00:16:32,909
他们给了我们像那个白痴一样的黑人警察。
They gave us Jim Crow officers like that knucklehead.

335
00:16:32,992 --> 00:16:36,996
但我们拒绝继续，除非他们找到合适的人代替他。
But we refuse to continue till they've replaced him with somebody good.

336
00:16:37,079 --> 00:16:38,706
找个体面又尊重人的人。
Someone decent and respectful.

337
00:16:39,582 --> 00:16:41,417
那是我吗，长官?
Is that supposed to be me, sir?

338
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:42,919
那就是你，伯伦森。
That is you, Berendsen.

339
00:16:43,002 --> 00:16:50,593
我的意思是，你在这种巨大压力下遇到的人与你的生活息息相关。
I mean, the people you meet in these circumstances of tremendous stress are bonded to you for life.

340
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:54,865
你是那种会让我失血过多然后我不得不从背后开枪的医生吗?
Are you the kind of doctor that's gonna leave me bleeding out and I'll have to shoot in the back?

341
00:16:54,889 --> 00:17:00,603
因为让我告诉你，他们手下的警官，他们不在乎我们的死活。
Because let me tell you, the officers that they had, they didn't care whether we lived or died.

342
00:17:00,686 --> 00:17:04,982
我不会让任何人失血过多而死，我也不想背后挨一枪。
I am not gonna let anybody bleed out, and I do not wanna get shot in the back.

343
00:17:05,066 --> 00:17:07,068
我是埃尔米拉一个机械师的儿子。
I am the son of a mechanic from Elmira.

344
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:08,152
我结婚了。
I am married.

345
00:17:08,236 --> 00:17:09,654
我一半是天主教徒，一半是犹太人。
I'm half Catholic, half Jewish.

346
00:17:09,737 --> 00:17:12,490
我是医生。我在公园大道有个诊所。
I'm a doctor. I have a practice on Park Avenue.

347
00:17:12,573 --> 00:17:15,576
我觉得我的公婆派我来是为了赶我走。
And I think that my in-laws sent me here to get rid of me.

348
00:17:17,370 --> 00:17:23,459
听起来不错，除了…姻亲的关系，但也许这就是我可以信任你的原因。
Well, that all sounds pretty good, except that... in-laws part, but maybe that's why I can trust you.

349
00:17:28,005 --> 00:17:29,382
所以，我们要做个约定。
So, we'll make a pact.

350
00:17:30,675 --> 00:17:33,636
你要确保我们不会死。
You see to it that we won't die.

351
00:17:34,178 --> 00:17:38,015
我保证你不会被杀。
And I'll make sure you won't get killed.

352
00:17:40,351 --> 00:17:41,602
我们会互相照顾的。
We'll look out for each other.

353
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:44,605
哈罗德·塞迪斯·伍德曼。
Harold Thaddeus Woodman.

354
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:46,274
伯特伦Berendsen。
Bertram Berendsen.

355
00:17:46,357 --> 00:17:48,526
-欢迎来到369。-谢谢。
- Welcome to the 369. - Thank you.

356
00:17:49,151 --> 00:17:50,462
这就是我一直在寻找的。
Finally, that's what I've been looking for.

357
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:51,487
只是尊重一下。
Just some respect.

358
00:17:51,988 --> 00:17:54,657
现在我们去解决这个不幸的制服问题吧。
Now let's go deal with this unfortunate uniform situation.

359
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:57,618
是啊，我们去处理制服的事吧。
Yeah, let's go deal with this uniform shit.

360
00:17:58,494 --> 00:17:59,745
欢迎加入我的军队。
Welcome to my army.

361
00:17:59,829 --> 00:18:01,706
我们为什么要穿法国制服?
Why are we wearing French uniforms?

362
00:18:02,540 --> 00:18:05,710
美国士兵，他们不想被看到和我们在一起。
The American soldiers, they don't wanna be seen with us.

363
00:18:05,793 --> 00:18:11,048
这是可耻的。我以善良和团结的精神奋斗创建了这个团。
It's disgraceful. I fought to create this regiment in the spirit of kindness and unity.

364
00:18:11,132 --> 00:18:14,302
希望在阿贡河的另一边见到你。
Hope to see you on the other side of the Argonne in good shape.

365
00:18:14,385 --> 00:18:15,469
愿上帝与你同在。
God be with you.

366
00:18:21,851 --> 00:18:23,811
我救了哈罗德。
I saved Harold.

367
00:18:23,894 --> 00:18:25,396
他救了我。
He saved me.

368
00:18:26,314 --> 00:18:28,858
有个法国女人救了我们俩。
And there was this French lady saving both of us.

369
00:18:44,165 --> 00:18:46,834
把剩下的给我……不要把它扔掉。
Give me the rest... Do not throw that away.

370
00:18:46,917 --> 00:18:47,978
你为什么要留着它?
Why do you want to keep it?

371
00:18:48,002 --> 00:18:49,003
这是不卫生的。
It's unsanitary.

372
00:18:49,086 --> 00:18:50,166
这不关你的事。
It's none of your business.

373
00:18:50,212 --> 00:18:51,732
Et vous ne portez pas de bonnet en plus!
Et vous ne portez pas de bonnet en plus!

374
00:18:51,756 --> 00:18:53,191
——评论?- Vous ne portez pas de bonnet!
- Comment? - Vous ne portez pas de bonnet!

375
00:18:53,215 --> 00:18:54,300
滚出去!
Get out of here!

376
00:18:55,468 --> 00:18:56,469
滚出去。
Get out of here.

377
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:57,595
哦啦啦!
Oh la la!

378
00:19:15,196 --> 00:19:16,280
Croyez-moi。
Croyez-moi.

379
00:19:26,082 --> 00:19:27,666
停止这种暴行!
Stop this atrocity!

380
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:32,505
不雅…犯罪……你是在亵渎……留着这该死的金属!
It's indecent... criminal... and you are blaspheming... by keeping this bloody metal!

381
00:19:32,588 --> 00:19:34,215
-她在亵渎神明?——是的。
- She's blaspheming? - Oui.

382
00:19:34,423 --> 00:19:35,424
我亵渎?
I'm blaspheming?

383
00:19:35,508 --> 00:19:36,592
是的。
Oui.

384
00:19:37,718 --> 00:19:39,512
那金属进去的时候很恶心。
The metal was obscene when it went in.

385
00:19:39,845 --> 00:19:42,473
我把它取出来的时候再兑换。
I redeem it when I take it out.

386
00:19:42,932 --> 00:19:44,892
你宁愿把一切都隐藏起来。
You prefer to keep it all hidden.

387
00:19:46,018 --> 00:19:49,122
它侮辱了上帝……还有死者和伤者的家属。
It insults God... and the families of the dead and the wounded.

388
00:19:49,146 --> 00:19:50,606
不，她说得对。
No, she's right.

389
00:19:51,524 --> 00:19:52,650
不，她说得对。
No, she's right.

390
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:53,734
谢谢。
Merci.

391
00:19:53,818 --> 00:19:55,694
她可以留着这该死的金属。
She can keep this bloody metal.

392
00:19:55,778 --> 00:19:57,113
——什么?——谢谢。
- Quoi? - Merci.

393
00:19:57,196 --> 00:19:58,656
是的，是的，是的。
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

394
00:19:58,739 --> 00:20:00,199
-她说得对。-看到了吗?
- She's right. - You see?

395
00:20:00,282 --> 00:20:01,343
- Vous voyez!好了。——好。
- Vous voyez! Allez. - Allez.

396
00:20:01,367 --> 00:20:02,868
世界万岁!世界万岁!
Tout le monde! Tout le monde!

397
00:20:02,952 --> 00:20:04,161
杜calme !杜calme !
Du calme! Du calme!

398
00:20:04,245 --> 00:20:05,454
放轻松，哈罗德。
Take it easy, Harold.

399
00:20:05,538 --> 00:20:06,539
这是有理由的!你们看到!
Il a raison! Vous voyez!

400
00:20:06,622 --> 00:20:07,748
你们看到!好了。好了。
Vous voyez! Allez. Allez.

401
00:20:07,832 --> 00:20:10,543
你好大的胆子!
How dare you!

402
00:20:10,626 --> 00:20:11,919
我的天啊!
Oh, my God!

403
00:20:12,378 --> 00:20:14,797
Ca suffit。
Ça suffit.

404
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,549
我不知道发生了什么事。
I don't know what is happening.

405
00:20:16,632 --> 00:20:19,051
Liberté pour nous tous。Arrêtez de mentir!
Liberté pour nous tous. Arrêtez de mentir!

406
00:20:19,135 --> 00:20:23,055
Liberté pour nous tous。Arrêtez de mentir!
Liberté pour nous tous. Arrêtez de mentir!

407
00:20:23,472 --> 00:20:24,974
“自由……
Liberté...

408
00:20:27,643 --> 00:20:30,187
伍德曼先生，我想我应该感谢你。
Mr. Woodman, I believe I owe you my gratitude.

409
00:20:30,980 --> 00:20:31,981
哦，你会说英语?
Oh, you speak English?

410
00:20:32,314 --> 00:20:34,191
——是的。-我以为你是法国人。
- Yes. - I thought you were French.

411
00:20:34,275 --> 00:20:35,609
我是瓦莱丽·班登伯格。
I'm Valerie Bandenberg.

412
00:20:37,069 --> 00:20:39,405
-你不是法国人?——没有。
- You're not French? - No.

413
00:20:40,656 --> 00:20:41,991
我可以请你喝一杯吗?
May I buy you a drink?

414
00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:44,410
是的。我们……我们可以在这里做吗?
Yes. We... We can do that here?

415
00:20:44,493 --> 00:20:46,787
-我可以。-我们可以…我们可以在这里喝酒吗?
- I can. - We can... We can drink here?

416
00:20:46,871 --> 00:20:47,872
哈罗德!
Harold!

417
00:20:47,955 --> 00:20:50,124
-你到底在干什么?-年轻人!
- What the hell are you doing? - Young man!

418
00:20:50,207 --> 00:20:51,208
你要去哪里?
Where you goin'?

419
00:20:51,292 --> 00:20:52,710
他和我在一起很安全。
Oh, he's in safe hands with me.

420
00:20:52,793 --> 00:20:57,798
如果那些密西西比的家伙现在能看到你…协议怎么了?
If those Mississippi crackers could see you now... What happened to the pact?

421
00:20:58,466 --> 00:21:00,134
我在这里失去了一只眼睛。
I lost an eye here.

422
00:21:12,521 --> 00:21:15,065
抽烟斗的女人抽烟斗的女人
A woman who smokes a pipe.

423
00:21:18,152 --> 00:21:19,236
你害怕吗?
Are you intimidated?

424
00:21:20,029 --> 00:21:21,447
现在有一点。
A little bit right now.

425
00:21:28,454 --> 00:21:37,338
当你看到一个人，你真的看到了他们，你看到的是曾经的他们。
When you see someone, and you really see them, you see the kid that used to be them.

426
00:21:38,797 --> 00:21:42,259
你看到了他们脆弱的一面。
You see the part of them that's vulnerable.

427
00:21:43,677 --> 00:21:47,640
哈罗德和我从一开始就有这种感觉。
Harold and I had that kind of seeing each other right from the start.

428
00:21:49,642 --> 00:21:51,727
既然战争已经结束了…
Well, now that the war is over...

429
00:21:55,314 --> 00:21:56,982
我只想做一个真正的人。你知道吗?
I just want to be a person. You know?

430
00:21:57,066 --> 00:22:01,153
我只想自由自在地四处走走……毫米。
I just want to walk around - free... - Mm.

431
00:22:01,237 --> 00:22:05,908
作为一个人。只是…过我自己的生活。
As a person. Just... Just living my life.

432
00:22:06,825 --> 00:22:08,160
这里是欧洲。
Here in Europe.

433
00:22:08,661 --> 00:22:11,205
这就是问题所在。活下去，自由自在。
That's the ticket. Just live and be free.

434
00:22:11,288 --> 00:22:13,958
我强烈推荐它。我已经走遍了欧洲。
I highly recommend it. I've walked around Europe.

435
00:22:15,042 --> 00:22:16,835
它给我带来了奇迹。
It's done wonders for me.

436
00:22:17,169 --> 00:22:22,049
不用多说，她就能看穿你的灵魂。
Without even too many words, I mean, she's looking right into your soul.

437
00:22:22,299 --> 00:22:24,552
是啊，你穿得很好。
Yeah, you wear it well.

438
00:22:25,010 --> 00:22:29,640
我们的生命在上帝面前岌岌可危。在这里。
Both our lives were in the balance before God. Right there.

439
00:22:35,187 --> 00:22:36,313
我能问你个问题吗?
Can I ask you something?

440
00:22:36,772 --> 00:22:37,773
毫米。
Mm.

441
00:22:38,649 --> 00:22:41,735
你怎么处理从我们身上取出的血淋淋的弹片?
What do you do with the bloody shrapnel that you take from our bodies?

442
00:22:42,194 --> 00:22:44,029
我不能白给你。
I can't give you that for nothing.

443
00:22:44,113 --> 00:22:46,240
你得跟我换一样东西。
You have to trade me something.

444
00:22:46,323 --> 00:22:47,866
这不是免费的。
You don't get that for free.

445
00:22:48,701 --> 00:22:49,702
贸易吗?
Trade you?

446
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:52,496
好的。多少钱?
Okay. What does it cost?

447
00:22:53,497 --> 00:22:54,999
美丽的东西。
Something beautiful.

448
00:22:56,375 --> 00:22:57,793
活着的意义。
Something to live for.

449
00:22:59,169 --> 00:23:00,838
我现在正看着呢。
I'm looking at that right now.

450
00:23:08,345 --> 00:23:11,181
我已经把我身上的金属弹片给你了。
I already gave you pieces of metal shrapnel from my body.

451
00:23:12,099 --> 00:23:15,394
其实，我从你朋友的身体里提取了更多的金属。
You know, actually, I took a lot more metal from your friend's body.

452
00:23:16,186 --> 00:23:17,313
他叫什么名字?
What's his name?

453
00:23:17,396 --> 00:23:19,732
他叫伯特·伯伦森。
His name is Burt Berendsen.

454
00:23:19,815 --> 00:23:20,816
哦,男孩。
Oh, boy.

455
00:23:20,899 --> 00:23:27,031
他一瘸一拐地走着，想起了一段友谊的约定。
And he is hobbling along here, remembering something about a friendship pact.

456
00:23:27,114 --> 00:23:29,450
你还记得吗?还记得我吗?我在这里。
Do you remember that? Remember me? Here I am.

457
00:23:29,533 --> 00:23:30,635
-很高兴见到你，伯特- - - - - -你好。
- Good to see you, Burt. - Hello.

458
00:23:30,659 --> 00:23:32,077
对不起，伯特·伯伦森。
My apologies, Burt Berendsen.

459
00:23:32,161 --> 00:23:35,664
我倒两杯的时候再也不会少了第三杯了。
Never again shall I pour two without a third.

460
00:23:35,748 --> 00:23:42,463
伯特，你得帮帮我…-很好。-用美好的东西交换，作为回报，她会向我们展示她如何处理她从我们身体上取下的金属。
Hey, Burt, you gotta help me... - Very good. - trade something beautiful, and in return, she's gonna show us what she does with all the metal she took from our bodies.

461
00:23:43,589 --> 00:23:44,673
她叫瓦莱丽。
Her name is Valerie.

462
00:23:44,757 --> 00:23:46,800
你怎么处理那些弹片，瓦莱丽?
What do you do with all that shrapnel, Valerie?

463
00:23:47,509 --> 00:23:49,845
如果你想知道，你得跟我换一样东西。
If you want to know, you have to trade me something.

464
00:23:49,928 --> 00:23:51,728
-她也是这么说的。-我什么都没有。
- She told me the same thing. - I got nothing.

465
00:23:52,056 --> 00:23:53,057
无意义的歌。
Nonsense song.

466
00:23:53,557 --> 00:23:55,768
这是个好主意。怎么样?
That's a good idea. How about that?

467
00:23:56,935 --> 00:23:58,228
什么是废话歌?
What's a nonsense song?

468
00:24:00,105 --> 00:24:01,106
好吧。
All right.

469
00:24:02,566 --> 00:24:05,444
红色的太阳。
The red sun.

470
00:24:05,527 --> 00:24:09,031
嗯…一些柚子。
Um... Some grapefruit.

471
00:24:09,198 --> 00:24:10,824
他的手帕。
The handkerchief.

472
00:24:11,367 --> 00:24:24,088
红日……一些柚子…手帕……当你打电话的时候。
The red sun... some grapefruit... the handkerchief... when you call.

473
00:24:24,838 --> 00:24:31,470
看到一张脸…谁的?
To see a face... whose?

474
00:24:32,054 --> 00:24:36,975
我的名字……我自己的名字。
My name... my own name.

475
00:24:37,976 --> 00:24:42,815
它是生动的，那一刻……去爱，才会存在。
It's vivid, the moment... to love, to be.

476
00:24:42,898 --> 00:24:43,899
你说对了。
You got it.

477
00:24:43,982 --> 00:24:50,447
海滩很温暖……天空很冷……死亡是真实的…当我们奄奄一息的时候。
The beach is warm... The sky is cold... Death is real... when we're dying.

478
00:24:50,864 --> 00:24:58,455
但是天空……有了朋友是温暖的。
But the sky... is warm with friends.

479
00:25:06,088 --> 00:25:08,966
我从人的身体里取出过这些东西。
I've taken all these pieces out of people's bodies.

480
00:25:09,049 --> 00:25:11,635
看。这个东西更原始。
Look. This is more primitive, this stuff.

481
00:25:12,177 --> 00:25:13,595
看，我要开一个茶话会。
Look, I'm having a tea party.

482
00:25:14,221 --> 00:25:17,391
这是用火药做的。和弹片。
This is made out of gun powder. And shrapnel.

483
00:25:17,933 --> 00:25:19,893
文明的高度。
The height of civilization.

484
00:25:25,733 --> 00:25:27,818
欢迎来到我的世界。
Welcome to my world.

485
00:25:27,901 --> 00:25:29,903
哦，我在化妆。
Oh, I'm doing my makeup.

486
00:25:29,987 --> 00:25:31,613
我只有半张脸吗?
Oh, do I only have half a face?

487
00:25:31,697 --> 00:25:32,865
这是怎么发生的?
How did that happen?

488
00:25:32,948 --> 00:25:34,658
只要我有口红就行。
As long as I have my lipstick.

489
00:25:36,410 --> 00:25:37,536
漂亮。
Pretty.

490
00:25:37,619 --> 00:25:40,122
你得知道你喜欢什么。
You got to know what you love.

491
00:25:40,205 --> 00:25:48,338
你得从生活中得到真正的乐趣，否则，如果你任其发展，会有太多该死的麻烦从头到尾地破坏这种生活的乐趣。
And you got to get a real kick out of it, or there's too much damn trouble in it to spoil this affair of living from beginning to end, if you let it.

492
00:25:49,089 --> 00:25:53,886
为什么不为美好的事物而活，即使你有点穷?
Why not live it for the beautiful things, even if you were a bit broke?

