You gotta go up, down, up, down, up.

571
00:29:42,823 --> 00:29:44,700
它们会闪烁一会儿。看到了吗?
They'll flicker for a little bit. See?

572
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:46,368
卢米埃。
Lumière.

573
00:29:46,451 --> 00:29:47,703
我是说，这地方很大。
I mean, it's a big place.

574
00:29:47,786 --> 00:29:49,806
保罗和亨利帮我安排的，但太乱了。
Paul and Henry organized it for me, but it's a wreck.

575
00:29:49,830 --> 00:29:50,831
她是对的。
She was right.

576
00:29:50,914 --> 00:29:57,129
-这是精彩的部分。-还有这个水龙头…-太棒了。-我是说，别被吓到。当你用水的时候……它会这样做的。
- This was the good part. - And this tap... - It was fantastic. - I mean, don't let it scare you. When you use the water... it will do that.

577
00:29:57,212 --> 00:29:59,339
整个世界突然变成了我们的牡蛎，它是如此的辉煌。
The world was suddenly our oyster and it was glorious.

578
00:30:00,007 --> 00:30:01,008
这是正常的。
That's normal.

579
00:30:09,933 --> 00:30:14,354
是的。阿姆斯特丹是在心脏，一直在那里。
Yeah. Amsterdam is in the heart, and was there all along.

580
00:30:14,438 --> 00:30:16,440
去吧!
Go on!

581
00:30:16,523 --> 00:30:18,734
保罗，让他们看看沙舞!
Paul, show them the sand dance!

582
00:30:20,527 --> 00:30:21,611
沙舞。
The sand dance.

583
00:30:21,695 --> 00:30:24,531
疯狂的大英帝国沙舞。
The crazy British Empire sand dance.

584
00:30:40,047 --> 00:30:42,883
她聪明又疯狂。
She was brilliant and nuts.

585
00:30:42,966 --> 00:30:44,843
但她和我们是一类疯子。
But she was our kind of nuts.

586
00:30:46,261 --> 00:30:48,930
所以条约现在有了三个。
And so the pact now had three.

587
00:30:51,349 --> 00:30:56,021
我在阿姆斯特丹呆了一段时间，因为那里的景色很美。
I stayed in Amsterdam for a while because it was glorious there.

588
00:30:56,855 --> 00:30:58,815
他又稳又壮。
He was steady and strong.

589
00:30:58,899 --> 00:31:00,734
她很大胆，很聪明。
She was bold and luminous.

590
00:31:01,485 --> 00:31:03,820
这就是法国人所说的“千钧一发”。
It was what the French call a coup de foudre.

591
00:31:03,904 --> 00:31:05,238
一见钟情。
Love at first sight.

592
00:31:06,073 --> 00:31:07,157
她创造了自己的艺术。
She made her art.

593
00:31:08,992 --> 00:31:12,245
我是他们最好的朋友，用我的新眼睛。
I was their best friend, with my new eye.

594
00:31:13,914 --> 00:31:16,722
我们帮助经过城镇的老兵。——好的。这工作。
We helped vets - passing through town. - Okay. That works.

595
00:31:20,128 --> 00:31:22,255
我们经常去跳舞。
We went dancing all the time.

596
00:31:23,340 --> 00:31:25,008
它是宏伟的。
It was magnificent.

597
00:31:26,176 --> 00:31:31,556
在探戈舞厅，你真的会觉得自己在飞翔。
These tango parlors, you really feel like you're flying.

598
00:31:42,192 --> 00:31:44,545
你不能走。我…那边现在太糟糕了。
You can't go. I... It's terrible over there right now.

599
00:31:44,569 --> 00:31:46,863
-你在说什么?-我要见我妻子。
- What are you talking about? - I have to see my wife.

600
00:31:48,198 --> 00:31:50,492
伯特，我有很不好的预感。
Burt, I have a very bad feeling about this.

601
00:31:50,575 --> 00:31:52,744
我…我认为如果你离开是一个不好的预兆。
I... I think it's a bad omen if you leave.

602
00:31:53,870 --> 00:31:54,871
请不要走。
Please don't go.

603
00:31:56,164 --> 00:31:58,625
我成了公园大道的一名医生。
I became a doctor on Park Avenue.

604
00:31:58,708 --> 00:31:59,876
-公园大道。-我结婚了。
- Park Avenue. - I'm married.

605
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:05,632
我们可以……我们能算出来的，对吧?我们可以……我对公园大道略知一二。
We can... We can figure it out, right? We can... I know a thing or two about Park Avenue.

606
00:32:07,092 --> 00:32:08,218
请不要走。
Please don't go.

607
00:32:09,970 --> 00:32:11,012
瓦莱丽。
Valerie.

608
00:32:13,181 --> 00:32:16,685
让我们现实一点。这不会永远持续下去。
Let's be realistic. This can't last forever.

609
00:32:17,352 --> 00:32:18,728
我们要怎么生活?
How are we supposed to live?

610
00:32:19,271 --> 00:32:23,650
我想念碧翠丝，尽管她和她的家人把我送去了战场。
I missed Beatrice, even though she and her family sent me off to war.

611
00:32:23,733 --> 00:32:25,026
为你的国家服务。
Serve your country.

612
00:32:25,110 --> 00:32:28,822
我第一次见到她是在医学院的慈善活动上
When I first met her, I was at a charity event at medical school.

613
00:32:28,905 --> 00:32:31,551
我看到了这个女人，我见过的最漂亮的女人。
And I see this woman, the most beautiful woman I've ever seen.

614
00:32:31,575 --> 00:32:32,802
我的天啊。你真该看看她。
Oh, my God. You should've seen her.

615
00:32:32,826 --> 00:32:33,910
我们跳了一整晚。
And we danced all night.

616
00:32:33,994 --> 00:32:35,370
我们都头晕了。我们都笑了。
We were giddy. We were laughing.

617
00:32:35,453 --> 00:32:36,454
我们相爱了。
We were in love.

618
00:32:36,538 --> 00:32:40,292
我不知道她是那个给我奖学金的人的女儿。
I had no idea that she was the daughter of the guy who gave me the scholarship.

619
00:32:40,375 --> 00:32:50,177
在他眼里，这个有一半犹太人血统的人，就像是在说"你可以拿奖学金，但我女儿，- "不准拿"-听起来很糟糕。
