645
00:34:09,631 --> 00:34:12,259
吃止痛药的时候有点失控了。
It got a little out of control with the pain medicine.

646
00:34:13,551 --> 00:34:17,430
我被强制休息，这是纽约州的恩赐。
And I was given an enforced rest, courtesy of the State of New York.

647
00:34:17,514 --> 00:34:18,723
来吧，伙计。
Come on, buddy.

648
00:34:18,807 --> 00:34:21,226
写信给我朋友，让他们救我出来。
Wrote my friends to help get me out.

649
00:34:21,309 --> 00:34:23,895
不知道这会对他们造成什么影响。
Had no idea what it would do to them.

650
00:34:23,979 --> 00:34:28,608
如果你的家人有能力帮伯特出狱，我觉得你应该这么做。
If your family has the kind of influence that can help Burt get out of jail, I think you should do it.

651
00:34:29,276 --> 00:34:31,444
约定就是约定，瓦莱丽。
I mean, the pact is the pact, Valerie.

652
00:34:31,820 --> 00:34:35,031
我告诉过你我逃离了什么，不是吗?
I told you I ran away from something, didn't I?

653
00:34:35,115 --> 00:34:36,449
这就是你需要知道的。
That's all you need to know.

654
00:34:37,659 --> 00:34:39,953
但是，是的，我的家人可能会帮他。
But, yes, my family could possibly help him.

655
00:34:40,036 --> 00:34:42,789
但如果我联系他们，他们就会知道我在哪里。
But if I contact them, they'll know where I am.

656
00:34:42,872 --> 00:34:47,752
如果他们知道我在哪里，他们可能会想办法把我拖回去。
And if they know where I am, they will find a way to possibly drag me back.

657
00:34:48,878 --> 00:34:50,297
他们很有说服力。
And they're very persuasive.

658
00:34:50,380 --> 00:34:52,507
他所做的一切都是为了帮助这个团。
All he was doing was trying to help the regiment.

659
00:34:53,508 --> 00:34:55,635
我听说那些人在老家日子不好过。
I hear those guys have it rough back at home.

660
00:34:57,679 --> 00:35:00,473
我想我们都知道这是怎么回事。
I think we both knew where this was headed anyway.

661
00:35:00,557 --> 00:35:02,475
-是的。-你这是什么意思?
- Yeah. - What do you mean by that?

662
00:35:02,559 --> 00:35:04,978
我是说，我们…我们只存在于阿姆斯特丹。
Well, I mean, we... we only exist in Amsterdam.

663
00:35:06,146 --> 00:35:11,067
你也说了很多关于你回美国后打算做的事。
You know, and you've spoken a lot about the things that you plan on doing back in America.

664
00:35:11,151 --> 00:35:12,360
也许是时候了。
Maybe it's time.

665
00:35:13,903 --> 00:35:15,780
我说我想成为一名律师。
I said I wanted to become a lawyer.

666
00:35:16,614 --> 00:35:17,907
为人民而战。
To fight for people.

667
00:35:17,991 --> 00:35:19,576
人们喜欢家乡的那些士兵。
People like those soldiers back at home.

668
00:35:19,659 --> 00:35:24,414
我想为那些无法反抗的人而战，为那些无法利用法律为自己而战的人而战。
I wanted to fight for people like that who couldn't fight back, who couldn't fight for themselves, to use the law.

669
00:35:25,540 --> 00:35:28,209
你还说你想和我一起住在阿姆斯特丹。
You also said that you wanna live in Amsterdam with me.

670
00:35:29,669 --> 00:35:30,670
是的。
Yes.

671
00:35:31,212 --> 00:35:33,798
我两样都想做。我想回家战斗。
I wanna do both. I wanna go back home and fight.

672
00:35:35,216 --> 00:35:36,551
我想和你待在一起。
And I wanna stay here with you.

673
00:35:36,634 --> 00:35:38,845
我想活下去。我想要真正的生活。
And I wanna live. I wanna truly live.

674
00:35:39,804 --> 00:35:41,514
你怎么能同时拥有这两样东西呢?
How do you have both those things?

675
00:35:44,976 --> 00:35:45,977
有个办法。
There's a way.

676
00:35:47,103 --> 00:35:48,730
但现在我们得帮伯特。
But right now we have to help Burt.

677
00:35:56,905 --> 00:35:58,823
我们会怎么样?我爱你。
What will happen to us? I love you.

678
00:36:05,747 --> 00:36:06,956
我们得帮伯特。
We gotta help Burt.

679
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:10,001
好的。
Okay.

680
00:36:13,171 --> 00:36:14,172
穿好衣服。
Get dressed.

681
00:36:27,477 --> 00:36:33,858
不久之后的一天，她消失了，除了一张便条，没跟哈罗德说一句话。
She vanished, one day soon after, without a word to Harold, except a note.

682
00:36:36,277 --> 00:36:38,154
我突然从监狱里被释放了。
I was suddenly released from jail.

683
00:36:38,863 --> 00:36:40,323
再也没有她的消息。
Never heard from her.

684
00:36:41,074 --> 00:36:43,785
哈罗德回到了纽约。拿到了法律学位。
Harold came back to New York. Got his law degree.

685
00:36:43,868 --> 00:36:44,869
你有权要求赔偿。
You have a claim.

686
00:36:44,953 --> 00:36:46,955
我们一起工作了10多年。
We worked together over 10 years.

687
00:36:47,038 --> 00:36:49,833
好医生和我会好好照顾你的。
The good doctor and I will take good care of you.

688
00:36:49,916 --> 00:36:55,004
我们帮别人摆脱了各种麻烦，直到米金斯的案子。
All kinds of trouble we got people out of, until the Meekins case.

689
00:36:58,174 --> 00:37:01,094
这就是我们现在所处的困境。
This was trouble that now we were in, ourselves.

690
00:37:02,095 --> 00:37:04,431
我们很可能无法存活。
And we may very well not survive.

691
00:37:05,723 --> 00:37:07,642
我的天啊。那个可怜的女孩。
Oh, my God. That poor girl.

692
00:37:07,725 --> 00:37:09,018
我受不了了。
I can't bear this.

693
00:37:09,102 --> 00:37:12,021
某物出事了，哈罗德。
Something... Something is very wrong, Harold.

694
00:37:14,190 --> 00:37:16,901
你总是对我说的那句话是什么?
What's that thing that you always say to me?

695
00:37:18,611 --> 00:37:19,654
我们会奋战到底的。
We'll fight through it.

696
00:37:21,030 --> 00:37:22,699
不管发生什么，我们都会有办法的。
We'll find a way, no matter what.

697
00:37:25,410 --> 00:37:27,537
谢谢你！我需要这个。
Thank you. I need that.

698
00:37:30,373 --> 00:37:31,583
在那里……你要去哪里?
Where... Where you going?

699
00:37:32,750 --> 00:37:34,544
我们离开这条街会更安全。
It's safer if we can get off the street.

700
00:37:34,627 --> 00:37:36,880
哦……我知道我们在哪里。
Oh... I know where we are.

701
00:37:37,380 --> 00:37:39,841
我知道我们在哪里。不是那个女人，伯特。
I know where we are. Not that woman, Burt.

702
00:37:41,718 --> 00:37:44,929
灯都关了。这是一个惊喜晚餐吗?
The lights are off. Is it a surprise dinner?

703
00:37:45,013 --> 00:37:48,516
她认识莉兹·米金斯那个世界的人。
She knows people from Liz Meekins's world.

704
00:37:49,142 --> 00:37:50,351
这个地方看起来还是老样子。
The place looks the same.

705
00:37:50,435 --> 00:37:52,187
闻起来像樟脑丸，像你的婚姻。
Smells of mothballs, like your marriage.

706
00:37:52,854 --> 00:37:53,855
谢谢你,朋友。
Thanks, pal.

707
00:37:54,355 --> 00:37:56,149
如果没有诚实，朋友还有什么用?
What are friends for if not honesty?

708
00:37:56,232 --> 00:37:58,109
火,会被火灼伤。情况如何?
That burns. How we looking?

709
00:38:00,820 --> 00:38:01,821
好吗?
Good?

710
00:38:03,698 --> 00:38:04,699
帮助我。
Help me.

711
00:38:06,534 --> 00:38:07,702
-是直的吗?-是的。
- Is that straight? - Yeah.

712
00:38:08,661 --> 00:38:09,829
哦，我明白了。
Oh, I see.

713
00:38:09,913 --> 00:38:11,748
你在她面前装得真漂亮啊?
You're really putting it on nice for her, huh?

714
00:38:11,831 --> 00:38:13,458
伯特伦吗?
Bertram?

715
00:38:13,541 --> 00:38:14,542
坐下来。放松。
Sit down. Relax.

716
00:38:14,626 --> 00:38:15,835
伯特，别等太久。
Hey, Burt, don't be too long.

717
00:38:15,919 --> 00:38:16,920
帮我个忙。
Do me a favor.

718
00:38:17,003 --> 00:38:19,088
-试着乐观一点。——伯特伦?伯特伦吗?
- Try to be optimistic. - Bertram? Bertram?

719
00:38:21,966 --> 00:38:23,426
哦，看看你。
Oh, look at you.

720
00:38:26,221 --> 00:38:29,724
没有晚餐。我很抱歉。我很抱歉。这是一个错误。
There is no dinner. I'm sorry. I'm sorry. It was a mistake.

721
00:38:31,017 --> 00:38:32,185
你为什么邀请我?
Why did you invite me?

722
00:38:32,685 --> 00:38:34,729
因为它是…我有一时的软弱。
Because it was... I had a moment of weakness.

723
00:38:35,396 --> 00:38:39,359
我们变成这样了?一时的软弱?
That's what we've become? A moment of weakness?

724
00:38:39,442 --> 00:38:43,905
不能让我父亲知道我在做这件事因为他会剥夺我所有的特权。
And my father can't even know that I'm doing this because he'll take away all kinds of privileges.

725
00:38:46,908 --> 00:38:48,493
怎么了?
What's wrong here?

726
00:38:49,661 --> 00:38:58,169
你还记得我们在晚上，只唱艾米莉·狄金森的诗，一起唱歌，彼此对视吗?
Do you remember when we would have nights, just Emily Dickinson poetry, and singing together and just staring at each other?

727
00:38:58,253 --> 00:39:00,505
-怎么了?-我记得，是的。
- What happened? - I remember, yeah.

728
00:39:01,005 --> 00:39:02,173
这就是为什么我爱你。
That's why I love you.

729
00:39:05,009 --> 00:39:06,052
你摔倒了吗?
Did you fall?

730
00:39:06,135 --> 00:39:08,805
你的背受伤了吗?让我看一下。
Did you hurt your back? Let me take a look at it.

731
00:39:09,639 --> 00:39:12,475
我的背疼了一整天。
My back has been killing me all day.

732
00:39:12,559 --> 00:39:14,018
现在不是时候。
This is not the right time.

733
00:39:14,102 --> 00:39:15,395
只是看了一眼。来吧。
Just a glimpse. Come on.

734
00:39:26,030 --> 00:39:28,408
你曾经如此美丽。
You were once so beautiful.

735
00:39:28,992 --> 00:39:30,660
看在上帝的份上。
Oh, for God's sakes.

736
00:39:31,411 --> 00:39:35,039
而现在你变得又丑又丑。
And now you're just hideous and grotesque.

737
00:39:35,999 --> 00:39:38,251
你又丑又畸形。
You're so ugly and deformed.

738
00:39:38,334 --> 00:39:40,128
看着你真是太难受了。
It's so hard to look at you.

739
00:39:40,837 --> 00:39:43,047
你穿得像个女人。
And you wear a corset like a woman.

740
00:39:43,131 --> 00:39:48,386
-你很无助。-碧翠丝，我受不了了。
- You're helpless. - Beatrice, I can't do this anymore.

741
00:39:48,469 --> 00:39:52,557
你对我的伤疤这么不正常。
This deviance that you've come to have about my scars.

742
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:56,978
你是选择我，还是需要我?
Do you choose me or do you need me?

743
00:39:58,313 --> 00:40:00,023
这是什么问题啊?
What kind of a question is that?

744
00:40:01,316 --> 00:40:13,119
今天我和一个人聊天，他们说爱是选择一个人，而不是因为其他原因需要他。
I was talking to someone today and they said that love is choosing someone, not needing them for some other reason.

745
00:40:14,245 --> 00:40:17,665
是我们相遇时你需要我，还是你选择了我这个人?
Did you need me when we met, or did you choose me as a person?

746
00:40:17,749 --> 00:40:19,626
是因为我身边的人吗?
Was it the people around me?

747
00:40:19,709 --> 00:40:24,297
你还是从纽约北部来的奖学金生时我家族在医学界的声望?
The prestige of my family in medicine when you were a scholarship student from Upstate New York?

748
00:40:25,256 --> 00:40:26,758
还是你选择了我?
Or did you choose me?

749
00:40:28,593 --> 00:40:29,719
只是我吗?
Just me?

750
00:40:32,347 --> 00:40:35,558
我刚才也问过伯特同样的问题。
I asked Burt the exact same question just a little while ago.

751
00:40:35,642 --> 00:40:37,060
哈罗德樵夫。
Harold Woodman.

752
00:40:37,143 --> 00:40:38,561
你为什么拿着女人的钱包?
Why do you have a woman's purse?

753
00:40:40,355 --> 00:40:45,068
比尔·米金斯的女儿莉兹，今晚被推到了卡车下面。
Bill Meekins's daughter, Liz, was pushed under a truck tonight.

754
00:40:45,568 --> 00:40:47,487
你是认真的吗?
What, are you serious?

755
00:40:47,570 --> 00:40:49,614
她雇我是因为我们和她父亲关系很好。
She hired me because we were close to her father.

756
00:40:49,697 --> 00:40:50,948
所以她才信任我们。
That's why she trusted us.

757
00:40:51,449 --> 00:40:54,202
不知为何，他们认为是我们干的。
Somehow, they think that we did it.

758
00:40:54,285 --> 00:40:56,871
我们需要一个人。我们需要一些东西。
And we need somebody. We need something.

759
00:40:56,954 --> 00:40:59,290
我们需要有人帮助我们。
We need someone to help us.

760
00:40:59,999 --> 00:41:01,376
“罗斯”这个名字怎么样?
What about the name "Rose"?

761
00:41:01,459 --> 00:41:06,089
这是莉斯·米金斯死前说的最后一句话，罗斯先生能帮她。
That's the last thing Liz Meekins said before she died, that a Mr. Rose could help her.

762
00:41:07,215 --> 00:41:09,401
莉兹绝不会认识一个叫罗斯的人。那是犹太人的名字。
Liz would never have known a Rose. That's a Jewish name.

763
00:41:09,425 --> 00:41:11,678
哦。谢谢你，碧翠丝。
Oh. Thank you, Beatrice.

764
00:41:11,761 --> 00:41:13,971
你只有一半。哈罗德，你听错了。
You're only half. Harold, you misheard.

765
00:41:14,055 --> 00:41:15,139
为什么?
Why?

766
00:41:15,223 --> 00:41:17,350
因为必须是"Voze"加" v "
Because it has to be "Voze" with a "V."

767
00:41:17,433 --> 00:41:19,435
那是社会记录上有名的家族。
That's a prominent family in the Social Register.

768
00:41:21,104 --> 00:41:23,272
沃兹一家在最上面。
The Vozes are at the top of it.

769
00:41:24,482 --> 00:41:25,942
伯特，这就是我说的。
Burt, this is what I'm talking about.

770
00:41:26,025 --> 00:41:28,611
我们身处的是你的世界，不是我的。
This is your world that we're in trouble in, not mine.

771
00:41:33,991 --> 00:41:35,785
那是什么?
What's that?

772
00:41:36,828 --> 00:41:38,663
你怎么敢进来?
How dare you come in here?

773
00:41:38,746 --> 00:41:39,831
门没锁。
The door was unlocked.

774
00:41:39,914 --> 00:41:41,514
这还是你登记的地址，对吧?
This is still your listed address, right?

775
00:41:41,541 --> 00:41:42,667
显然如此。
Apparently so.

776
00:41:42,750 --> 00:41:45,795
盖特韦勒警探，什么风把你吹来了?莱姆，你还需要药吗?
Detective Getweiler, what brings you here at this hour? You need more pills, Lem?

777
00:41:45,878 --> 00:41:50,299
我知道你和我戴着一样的支架，不像希尔兹先生。
I know you have the same brace as I do, not like Mr. Hiltz.

778
00:41:50,383 --> 00:41:53,386
你的平拱让德国人在莱茵兰看不到你。
Your flat arches stopped the Germans from seeing you in the Rhineland.

779
00:41:54,178 --> 00:41:55,680
你知道我为什么来这里，伯特。
You know why I'm here, Burt.

780
00:41:55,763 --> 00:41:59,143
你和伍德曼在把米金斯家的女人推到卡车下面后逃离了现场。
You and Woodman fled the scene after you pushed the Meekins woman under a truck.

781
00:41:59,684 --> 00:42:02,145
你为什么会认为是我们干的?
Why would you possibly think that was us?

782
00:42:02,228 --> 00:42:07,608
没有多少人符合医生和他的黑人律师在地上寻找他的眼睛的描述。
Well, there's not too many people that fit the description of a doctor looking for his eye on the ground with his Black attorney.

783
00:42:08,109 --> 00:42:12,822
死去的女人雇了哈罗德调查她父亲的死。
The woman who died hired Harold to look into her father's death.

784
00:42:12,905 --> 00:42:15,616
我今天下午给他做了尸检。
I did an autopsy on him this afternoon.

785
00:42:15,700 --> 00:42:18,661
他是我们所在兵团的将军，莱姆。
He was the general of the regiment we served in, Lem.

786
00:42:19,996 --> 00:42:21,622
目击者说你推了她。
Witnesses say you pushed her.

787
00:42:22,123 --> 00:42:24,041
不，我们必须离开那里。当时一片混乱。
No, we had to get out of there. It was chaos.

788
00:42:24,125 --> 00:42:26,085
一场打斗爆发了。凶手指着我们。
A fight broke out. The killer pointed at us.

789
00:42:26,169 --> 00:42:27,754
他很擅长当罪犯。
He's very good at being a criminal.

790
00:42:27,837 --> 00:42:28,963
我只知道一件事。
Well, I know one thing.

791
00:42:29,046 --> 00:42:30,715
我得给队长一个答案。
I need to give my captain answers.

792
00:42:30,798 --> 00:42:33,176
现在，你们两个是嫌疑人。
And at the moment, you two are the suspects.

793
00:42:34,969 --> 00:42:38,014
你能证明你和莉兹·米金斯有雇佣合同吗?
Can you prove you have an employment contract with Liz Meekins?

794
00:42:38,097 --> 00:42:40,016
她雇你做她的律师吗?
That she hired you to be her attorney?

795
00:42:40,099 --> 00:42:41,410
绝对的。我可以拿给你。
Absolutely. I can get that to you.

796
00:42:41,434 --> 00:42:45,938
另外，我可以给你初步尸检报告和比尔·米金斯的遗产文件。
Plus, I can get you the preliminary autopsy report and the Bill Meekins estate papers.

797
00:42:46,022 --> 00:42:47,106
好。
Good.

798
00:42:47,190 --> 00:42:50,902
不，我们得…我们得带你去…-别碰我。——Hiltz。Hiltz Hiltz。
No, we gotta... we gotta take you in... - Get your hands off of me. - Hiltz. Hiltz, Hiltz.

799
00:42:50,985 --> 00:42:52,305
我是律师协会的一员。
I'm a part of the Bar Association.

800
00:42:52,361 --> 00:42:53,362
别碰我。
Don't touch me.

801
00:42:53,446 --> 00:42:57,200
我甚至不喜欢这个人是律师。
I don't even like that this man is a lawyer.

802
00:42:58,743 --> 00:42:59,994
哥伦比亚大学法学院。
Columbia Law School.

803
00:43:01,370 --> 00:43:04,141
也许你的平臀弓让你很难理解。
Maybe those flat-ass arches of yours make that hard for you to comprehend.

804
00:43:04,165 --> 00:43:05,750
别跟我说我的扁足。
Don't talk to me about my flat arches.

805
00:43:05,833 --> 00:43:08,836
我要敲碎你的头…希尔兹，不，你不会的。别吵了!
I'll crack your head right... Hiltz, no, you won't. Knock it off!

806
00:43:09,837 --> 00:43:11,380
如果我们找个人为我们做担保呢?
What if we got someone to vouch for us?

807
00:43:11,464 --> 00:43:13,049
社会登记处的人吗?
Someone from the Social Register?

808
00:43:14,383 --> 00:43:16,135
这会引起你们队长的注意吗?
Would that get your captain's attention?

809
00:43:16,761 --> 00:43:21,307
像沃兹先生这样认识比尔·米金斯的人。
Someone like Mr. Voze, who knew Bill Meekins.

810
00:43:21,849 --> 00:43:24,852
伯特伦……比阿特丽斯。
Bertram... Beatrice.

811
00:43:25,686 --> 00:43:28,481
我的家人是州医疗委员会的长期成员。
My family are long-standing members of the state medical board.

812
00:43:28,564 --> 00:43:34,589
我可以证明这两个男人都是可怕的骗子，对彼此都是，更不用说对警察了。
And I can attest to the fact that both of these men are horrible liars, to each other, let alone to the police.

813
00:43:35,154 --> 00:43:41,744
如果你在给他们机会给你他们所提供的一切之前就收留了他们，我担心这可能会让你失去工作。
If you take them in before giving them the chance to give you everything that they've offered, I'm afraid it might cost you your job.

814
00:43:42,245 --> 00:43:44,080
我父亲在市政厅有很多朋友。
My father has a lot of friends at City Hall.

815
00:43:51,420 --> 00:43:53,172
把你答应过的东西都给我们。
Get us everything you promised.

816
00:43:53,673 --> 00:43:58,302
明白吗，你和我，我们有共同点。
Understand, you and me, we got something in common.

817
00:43:58,719 --> 00:44:00,972
我们服过役，不像这家伙。
We served, not like this guy.

818
00:44:01,055 --> 00:44:03,933
丢失的钱包怎么办?它去哪了?
What about the missing purse? Where did that go?

819
00:44:04,433 --> 00:44:06,936
这可能……这可能是证据。
This could... This could be evidence.

820
00:44:07,019 --> 00:44:08,080
你拿那个干什么?把它放下。
What are you doing with that? Put that down.

821
00:44:08,104 --> 00:44:09,289
-放回去。-这里面是什么?
- Put that back. - What's in here?

822
00:44:09,313 --> 00:44:10,374
-这是什么?-把它放下。
- What's this? - Put it down.

823
00:44:10,398 --> 00:44:11,458
-我只是说…-放回去。
- I'm just saying... - Put that back.

824
00:44:11,482 --> 00:44:12,692
哦,哦。
Oh-oh.

825
00:44:14,318 --> 00:44:16,070
我很抱歉。我很小心。
I'm sorry. I was being careful.

826
00:44:16,153 --> 00:44:17,822
你怎么了?
What is the matter with you?

827
00:44:18,239 --> 00:44:19,574
他在学习，伯特。
He's learning, Burt.

828
00:44:19,657 --> 00:44:21,534
他,呃…他可以成为一个好侦探。
He, uh... He can be a good detective.

829
00:44:22,702 --> 00:44:25,204
你跟沃兹谈过之后，马上告诉我。
And when you spoke to Voze, you let me know right away.

830
00:44:25,288 --> 00:44:27,206
我不会等那么久的。听到了吗，伯特?
I'm not gonna wait that long. You hear me, Burt?

831
00:44:27,290 --> 00:44:28,749
——是的。-我给你几天时间。
- Yes. - I'll give you a few days.

832
00:44:28,833 --> 00:44:31,311
但如果有必要的话-我会亲自带你来。-我明白。
But if I have to, - I'll bring you in myself. - I understand.

833
00:44:31,335 --> 00:44:33,212
-我还需要一些药。-我知道了。
- And I need some pills too. - I got it.

834
00:44:33,296 --> 00:44:35,172
我很快就会在你办公室见你。
I'll be seeing you in your office pretty soon.

835
00:44:35,256 --> 00:44:37,216
——是的。-但情况很糟糕。
- Yes. - But it's a bad situation.

836
00:44:38,009 --> 00:44:39,135
这很糟糕。
It's very bad.

837
00:44:43,639 --> 00:44:45,349
那真是令人兴奋。
Well, that was exciting.

838
00:44:45,933 --> 00:44:48,458
去拿你的东西，但别在回家的路上被杀了。
Go and get your things, but don't get killed on the way home.

839
00:45:00,907 --> 00:45:02,909
五人委员会，活下去。
Committee of the Five, stay alive.

840
00:45:03,326 --> 00:45:04,869
闭上你的嘴。
Keep your mouth shut.

841
00:45:04,952 --> 00:45:07,288
为什么不直接开车朝我们开枪?
Why not just drive up and shoot us?

842
00:45:08,748 --> 00:45:10,458
五人委员会，永远活着!
Committee of the Five, always alive!

843
00:45:11,125 --> 00:45:13,461
这家伙还想对我们做什么?
What else did this guy have in mind for us?

844
00:45:13,544 --> 00:45:14,670
我们无处不在。
We're everywhere.

845
00:45:22,929 --> 00:45:26,307
所以现在我们必须撒谎才能进入这家伙的房子。
So now we have to lie to get into this guy's house.

846
00:45:27,975 --> 00:45:30,811
怎样做并不重要。我们要去见沃兹先生。
Doesn't matter how. We are gonna see Mr. Voze.

847
00:45:33,230 --> 00:45:34,398
什么是慈善?
What is this charity?

848
00:45:34,482 --> 00:45:35,900
这是圣公会的。
Okay, that's the Episcopal one.

849
00:45:35,983 --> 00:45:37,109
门开了，你说?
The door opens and you say?

850
00:45:37,193 --> 00:45:38,194
我说:“你好……”
I say, "Hello..."

851
00:45:38,986 --> 00:45:40,696
我是伯特·伯伦森医生。
My name is Dr. Burt Berendsen.

852
00:45:40,780 --> 00:45:43,950
这位是哈罗德·伍德曼，时尚先生，荣誉勋章获得者。
This is Harold Woodman, Esquire, Medal of Honor recipient.

853
00:45:44,700 --> 00:45:47,550
这是英勇十字勋章，不是荣誉勋章，你知道的。
It's the Croix de Guerre, not the Medal of Honor, and you know that.

854
00:45:47,620 --> 00:45:49,997
十字勋章，是的。对不起。
Croix de Guerre, yes. Sorry.

855
00:45:58,381 --> 00:46:01,258
我们知道圣公会教徒有多爱沃兹先生。
We know how the Episcopalians love Mr. Voze.

856
00:46:01,342 --> 00:46:03,219
他错过了你会很遗憾的。他不在。
He'll be sorry to have missed you. He's not in.

857
00:46:03,302 --> 00:46:05,054
你觉得他什么时候会回来?
Well, when do you think he'll be back?

858
00:46:05,137 --> 00:46:06,514
我不知道。
I don't know.

859
00:46:06,597 --> 00:46:08,450
但也许你可以把那封信交给我?
But perhaps you could leave that letter with me?

860
00:46:08,474 --> 00:46:11,060
我们得把这个直接交给沃兹先生。
We need to hand this directly to Mr. Voze.

861
00:46:11,852 --> 00:46:13,646
是主教的命令。
On orders from the Bishop.

862
00:46:13,729 --> 00:46:15,940
正确的。那你可以留张卡片。
Right. Well, then, you can leave a card.

863
00:46:16,023 --> 00:46:17,733
很抱歉让你们失望了，先生们。
I'm sorry to disappoint you, gentlemen.

864
00:46:19,151 --> 00:46:20,403
不过，你介意吗?
However, do you mind?

865
00:46:21,487 --> 00:46:28,703
我看着这个柜子，然后我…我忍不住认出了这些工艺品。
I'm looking at this cabinet, and I... I couldn't help but recognize these crafts.

866
00:46:28,786 --> 00:46:30,746
这些是医院制造的吗?
Are these made in a hospital, over here?

867
00:46:30,830 --> 00:46:31,956
看到了吗?是的。
See? Yes.

868
00:46:32,039 --> 00:46:33,624
看起来像是老兵的作品。是的。
Looks like the works of veterans. Yes.

869
00:46:34,083 --> 00:46:35,543
-都是老兵干的。——正确的。
- All by veterans. - Right.

870
00:46:35,626 --> 00:46:37,211
沃兹的主要慈善事业。
Mr. Voze's primary charity.

871
00:46:37,294 --> 00:46:39,046
他们一直寄来感谢信。
They send them all the time as thanks.

872
00:46:39,130 --> 00:46:41,048
你真是太好了。
That, uh, is very kind.

873
00:46:41,132 --> 00:46:45,199
事实上，我们……呃，退伍军人…莉比，能把药给我吗?
And we, in fact... uh, are veterans... Libby, can I have the remedy, please?

874
00:46:45,261 --> 00:46:49,306
我双手发麻，神经发冷，剧痛。
I've got that numbness in my hands, and the chills in the nerves and shooting pains.

875
00:46:49,390 --> 00:46:50,391
好吗?
Please?

876
00:46:50,474 --> 00:46:53,185
瓦莱丽，请回你的房间或者上楼去。
Valerie, please go into your room or go back upstairs.

877
00:46:53,269 --> 00:46:55,271
你没看见我们有客人吗?
Can't you see we have company present?

878
00:46:59,650 --> 00:47:00,901
你在这里做什么?
What are you doing here?

879
00:47:03,904 --> 00:47:05,156
你在这里做什么?
What are you doing here?

880
00:47:05,656 --> 00:47:08,242
不。别跟她说话。她身体不舒服。
No. Don't talk to her. She's not well.

881
00:47:08,325 --> 00:47:10,202
瓦莱丽，别跟这些人说话。
Valerie, don't talk to these men.

882
00:47:10,286 --> 00:47:13,539
我不是血友病患者，莉比。我可以和人们交谈。
I'm not a hemophiliac, Libby. I can talk to people.

883
00:47:13,622 --> 00:47:18,127
是的，你不是血友病患者，但你有癫痫，你有神经紊乱。不!
Yes, you're not a hemophiliac, but you are epileptic, and you have a nervous disorder. No!

884
00:47:18,210 --> 00:47:20,963
-我们谈了娃娃的事。-我要咬掉你的耳朵。
- We talked about the doll. - I'll bite your ears off.

885
00:47:21,047 --> 00:47:23,841
不!我告诉过你别对娃娃这么做。
No! I told you not to do that with the doll.

886
00:47:23,924 --> 00:47:26,093
-莫兰太太!卡尔顿……-卡尔顿!
- Mrs. Moran! Carlton... - Carlton!

887
00:47:26,177 --> 00:47:28,012
你知道这让我很不安，瓦莱丽。
You know that disturbs me, Valerie.

888
00:47:28,095 --> 00:47:29,764
你好大的胆子!卡尔顿!
How dare you! Carlton!

889
00:47:29,847 --> 00:47:31,015
卡尔顿。
Carlton.

890
00:47:31,098 --> 00:47:32,224
瓦莱丽,诚实。
Valerie, honestly.

891
00:47:32,308 --> 00:47:35,061
我们说过要把我和她单独留在一起。
We spoke about leaving me alone with her.

892
00:47:35,478 --> 00:47:37,271
进来吧。我们可以在这里谈。
Come in here. We can talk in here.

893
00:48:11,055 --> 00:48:13,015
这种巧合怎么可能?
How is this coincidence even possible?

894
00:48:13,099 --> 00:48:14,892
因为这不是巧合。
Because it's not a coincidence.

895
00:48:16,519 --> 00:48:18,854
是我让莉斯·米金斯雇你们俩的。
I told Liz Meekins to hire you two.

896
00:48:18,938 --> 00:48:21,440
你叫莉斯·米金斯雇我们是什么意思?
What do you mean, you told Liz Meekins to hire us?

897
00:48:21,524 --> 00:48:22,525
她是我的朋友。
She's a friend of mine.

898
00:48:22,608 --> 00:48:23,794
她需要一个她可以信任的人。
She needed someone she could trust.

899
00:48:23,818 --> 00:48:25,486
我们社交圈之外的人。
Someone outside our social circle.

900
00:48:26,195 --> 00:48:27,655
这太奇怪了。
This is so strange.

901
00:48:28,114 --> 00:48:29,754
我从没告诉过你我的真名。
I never really told you my real last name.

902
00:48:29,782 --> 00:48:31,450
班登堡是个流动的名字。
Bandenberg was a traveling name.

903
00:48:32,034 --> 00:48:33,702
但这是我们在阿姆斯特丹的协议。
But that was our deal in Amsterdam.

904
00:48:33,786 --> 00:48:35,162
没有关于过去的事。
Nothing about the past.

905
00:48:37,623 --> 00:48:38,624
对吧?
Right?

906
00:48:39,208 --> 00:48:41,127
你住在新泽西?一直以来?
You live in New Jersey? This whole time?

907
00:48:43,170 --> 00:48:44,797
-是的。-这房子真大。
- Yeah. - This is a big house.

908
00:48:44,880 --> 00:48:46,799
-这就是你的生活方式?-是的。
- This is how you live? - Yeah.

909
00:48:51,137 --> 00:48:52,596
不信。
No letter.

910
00:48:54,056 --> 00:48:56,892
-不是打电话。-我很尴尬。
- Not a phone call. - I was embarrassed.

911
00:48:57,393 --> 00:48:58,602
这不是我曾经的样子。
This is not who I once was.

912
00:48:58,686 --> 00:49:00,479
不是你在阿姆斯特丹遇到的人。
It's not who you met in Amsterdam.

913
00:49:05,359 --> 00:49:06,610
你的平衡有什么问题吗?
What's wrong with your balance?

914
00:49:06,694 --> 00:49:09,238
我有神经障碍。
I have a nerve disorder.

915
00:49:10,239 --> 00:49:11,407
你以前从来没有过。
You never had that before.

916
00:49:11,490 --> 00:49:13,325
不，她以前从来没有过。
No, she never had that before.

917
00:49:16,287 --> 00:49:18,539
我们在这里是有原因的。
We are here for a reason.

918
00:49:18,622 --> 00:49:20,749
哈罗德，别忘了，这事很紧急。
Harold, let's not forget, it's pretty urgent.

919
00:49:21,250 --> 00:49:24,211
瓦莱丽，你认识汤姆·沃兹吗?
Valerie, do you know Tom Voze?

920
00:49:24,628 --> 00:49:26,046
我当然认识汤姆。
Of course I know Tom.

921
00:49:26,130 --> 00:49:27,756
我们有大麻烦了，瓦莱丽。
We're in a lot of trouble, Valerie.

922
00:49:27,840 --> 00:49:29,300
我们需要他为我们担保。
We need him to vouch for us.

923
00:49:29,383 --> 00:49:32,112
他是个好人，但我不知道他会不会为你担保。
He's a good guy, but I don't know if he's gonna vouch for you.

924
00:49:32,136 --> 00:49:34,138
他避免引起争议。他不喜欢那样。
He avoids controversy. He doesn't like that.

925
00:49:34,221 --> 00:49:35,848
他很容易被吓倒。
He's easily intimidated.

926
00:49:35,931 --> 00:49:38,184
-他是你丈夫吗?-卡尔顿在路上了!
- Is he your husband? - Carlton's on his way!

927
00:49:38,267 --> 00:49:39,310
不，他不是我丈夫。
No, he's not my husband.

928
00:49:39,393 --> 00:49:41,872
他娶了一个在外面大喊着要把你赶出去的女人。
He's married to the woman out there screaming to have you kicked out right now.

929
00:49:41,896 --> 00:49:42,897
他是我哥哥。
He's my brother.

930
00:49:43,564 --> 00:49:47,443
我们在阿姆斯特丹经历了那么多，结果伯特和我根本不知道你是谁。
After everything we had in Amsterdam, turns out Burt and I have no idea who you are.

931
00:49:48,527 --> 00:49:52,031
你很清楚我是谁。我很清楚你是谁。
You know exactly who I am. I know exactly who you are.

932
00:49:52,865 --> 00:49:55,451
我们三个。伯特。
All three of us. Burt too.

933
00:49:55,993 --> 00:49:57,703
我们都很了解对方。
We know each other the way it counts.

934
00:49:58,329 --> 00:50:01,624
如果你们俩还有协议，那我也是其中一员。
And if you two still have an arrangement, then I'm still part of it.

935
00:50:01,707 --> 00:50:03,042
也许12年后就不会了。
Maybe not after 12 years.

936
00:50:03,125 --> 00:50:05,127
是的，12年后。是的。
Yes, after 12 years. Yes.

937
00:50:05,211 --> 00:50:06,587
因为我最终来到了这里。
Because I ended up here.

938
00:50:06,670 --> 00:50:08,964
我回来是因为你和你。
And I came back because of you and you.

939
00:50:13,177 --> 00:50:14,428
这是真的。
That's true.

940
00:50:17,223 --> 00:50:19,868
我说过你离开阿姆斯特丹后，会有坏事发生。
I told you when you left Amsterdam, something bad would happen.

941
00:50:19,892 --> 00:50:21,578
我说过这是梦中最糟糕的部分。
I said it would be the bad part of the dream.

942
00:50:21,602 --> 00:50:22,645
我没说过吗?
Did I not say that?

943
00:50:23,229 --> 00:50:24,230
这是真的。
It's true.

944
00:50:24,313 --> 00:50:25,314
现在我们到了。
And here we are.

945
00:50:25,397 --> 00:50:27,399
瓦莱丽，卡尔顿在路上了。
Valerie, Carlton's on his way.

946
00:50:27,483 --> 00:50:29,026
打开门。
Open the door.

947
00:50:29,109 --> 00:50:30,361
我们可以摆脱它。
We can get out of it.

948
00:50:33,656 --> 00:50:36,367
这里不一样，所以我不知道。
Well, it's different here, so I don't know about that.

949
00:50:36,450 --> 00:50:37,952
卡尔顿来了，瓦莱丽。
Carlton is coming, Valerie.

950
00:50:38,035 --> 00:50:39,578
我感觉这是卡尔顿。
I have a feeling this is Carlton.

951
00:50:39,662 --> 00:50:41,205
哦,不。
Oh, no.

952
00:50:41,580 --> 00:50:43,040
不。哦，不，不，不。
No. Oh, no, no, no.

953
00:50:43,666 --> 00:50:48,837
啊…-卡尔顿。卡尔顿。请。——等待。等待……哦!
Ah... - Carlton. Carlton. Please. - Wait. Wait... Oh!

954
00:50:52,383 --> 00:50:54,009
瓦莱丽，你看到发生了什么吗?
Valerie, do you see what happens?

955
00:50:54,093 --> 00:50:56,053
你怎么可能认识这些人?
How do you possibly know any of these men?

956
00:51:01,600 --> 00:51:03,978
他在那儿。白兰地，莫兰太太。
There he is. The brandy, Mrs. Moran.

957
00:51:09,608 --> 00:51:11,068
不用了，谢谢。我不喝酒。
No, thank you. I don't drink.

958
00:51:11,568 --> 00:51:15,990
我觉得我不会相信一个不爱喝酒的人，尤其是在这种时候。
Well, I don't think I trust a man who doesn't like a drink, especially at a time like this.

959
00:51:17,408 --> 00:51:19,201
我的眼睛在哪里，哈罗德?
Where is my eye, Harold?

960
00:51:20,286 --> 00:51:21,870
-就在这里。——谢谢。
- Right here. - Thanks.

961
00:51:22,496 --> 00:51:26,667
我从没想过两个功勋军人会在我家里被打晕。
I never expected two decorated soldiers to get knocked out in my own home.

962
00:51:27,543 --> 00:51:28,794
不，只有一个，先生。
No, just one, sir.

963
00:51:29,712 --> 00:51:32,381
哦，对了，伍德曼先生。你对卡尔顿来说太快了。
Oh, that's right, Mr. Woodman. You were too fast for Carlton.

964
00:51:33,757 --> 00:51:34,967
我是。
I was.

965
00:51:35,050 --> 00:51:37,803
他们和瓦莱丽谈过了，她身体不太好。
They started talking to Valerie, and she's not well.

966
00:51:37,886 --> 00:51:41,223
求你了，亲爱的女孩，别哭了。
And please, darling girl, stop crying.

967
00:51:41,974 --> 00:51:44,059
她哭是很自然的事，莉比。
It's only natural for her to cry, Libby.

968
00:51:44,143 --> 00:51:46,061
她刚发现她的朋友死了。
She just found out her friend is dead.

969
00:51:47,146 --> 00:51:49,189
我们不能永远瞒着她。
We couldn't keep it from her for forever.

970
00:51:49,940 --> 00:51:52,526
我还没病到不能和人说话的地步。
I'm not so ill that I can't talk to people.

971
00:51:52,609 --> 00:51:57,007
你明明知道我认为她应该住院，却把我留在这里和这个病人在一起。-利比。
You leave me here with this invalid when you know very well that I think - she should be hospitalized. - Libby.

972
00:51:57,031 --> 00:52:01,011
-这是为她好-如果你再对我说这种话…-我处理不了…对你来说，那里会更好。
- It's for her own good. - If you ever say that - to me again... - I can't handle... It will be a better place for you.

973
00:52:01,035 --> 00:52:02,095
我就送你去医院
I'll put you in a hospital.

974
00:52:02,119 --> 00:52:03,179
我会送你去女巫审判。
I'll send you to a witch trial.

975
00:52:03,203 --> 00:52:05,998
女士们,请。女士们。停止。
Ladies, please. Ladies. Stop.

976
00:52:07,750 --> 00:52:11,587
我很抱歉。很抱歉我提高了嗓门。
I'm sorry. I'm sorry I had to raise my voice.

977
00:52:12,421 --> 00:52:14,190
她跟这些人说话，好像她认识他们一样。
She was talking to these men like she knows them.

978
00:52:14,214 --> 00:52:15,966
这把我吓坏了。
That terrified me.

979
00:52:18,969 --> 00:52:20,554
你们认识吗?
Do you know one another?

980
00:52:20,637 --> 00:52:21,680
——是的。——没有。
- Yes. - No.

981
00:52:23,057 --> 00:52:24,683
——是的。-确实是这样。
- Yes. - We do, indeed.

982
00:52:24,767 --> 00:52:26,101
欧洲。
Europe.

983
00:52:26,185 --> 00:52:28,187
-阿姆斯特丹来的。-医院
- From Amsterdam. - The hospital.

984
00:52:28,270 --> 00:52:30,647
他们说是圣公会慈善机构的。
They said they were from the Episcopal charities.

985
00:52:30,731 --> 00:52:32,816
这有什么道理吗?
Is there any truth to that at all?

986
00:52:33,317 --> 00:52:34,526
-当然。-部分如此。
- Uh, absolutely. - In part.

987
00:52:34,610 --> 00:52:35,611
部分?
In part?

988
00:52:36,236 --> 00:52:37,905
嘿，晚会马上就要到了。
Hey, the gala is coming up.

989
00:52:37,988 --> 00:52:39,239
这基本上是一个老手的活动。
Mostly a veteran event.

990
00:52:39,323 --> 00:52:41,367
但那里可能有圣公会教徒。
But there might be Episcopalians there.

991
00:52:41,450 --> 00:52:44,203
比尔·米金斯是我们的特邀演讲者。
And Bill Meekins was our featured speaker.

992
00:52:44,787 --> 00:52:50,959
但我们却陷入了这样一个可怕的境地我们被指控杀害了莉兹·米金斯，无论如何这都不是事实。
But we find ourselves in this terrible situation where we're accused of killing Liz Meekins, which is not true in any way.

993
00:52:51,043 --> 00:52:52,586
莉兹提到了"沃兹"这个名字
Liz mentioned the name "Voze,"

994
00:52:52,669 --> 00:52:56,256
所以我们觉得你可能知道是谁在跟踪她能帮我们洗清罪名。
and so we thought you might know who was after her and can help clear our names.

995
00:52:56,340 --> 00:52:58,509
我们的退伍军人。我们尊敬的。
We're veterans. We're respectable.

996
00:52:58,592 --> 00:53:03,097
我们不会掺和进来的，除非帮忙。
We wouldn't be involved in any of this, except to help.

997
00:53:04,098 --> 00:53:07,559
比尔·米金斯是一个爱吃全麦饼干的人。
Bill Meekins was a graham cracker of a man.

998
00:53:07,976 --> 00:53:10,604
他的骨子里一点也不吝啬。
Not a mean bone in his body.

999
00:53:10,687 --> 00:53:13,023
那么为什么……我为什么要帮她?
Then why... Why did I have to help her?

1000
00:53:13,107 --> 00:53:16,777
为什么我要鼓励她去找我们认识的所有人，然后雇佣这两个人?
Why did I have to encourage her to go around everyone we know and hire these two?

1001
00:53:16,860 --> 00:53:18,278
我确实帮了她，亲爱的。
I did help her, darling.

1002
00:53:18,987 --> 00:53:21,532
我让她在事情变糟之前来找我。
I told her to come to me before it got bad.

1003
00:53:22,157 --> 00:53:23,367
现在看看发生了什么。
Now look what happened.

1004
00:53:24,368 --> 00:53:26,995
是的。看看你做了什么，瓦莱丽。
Yes. Look what you did, Valerie.

1005
00:53:27,079 --> 00:53:29,849
我很抱歉，很不幸，但你不应该卷进来。
I'm sorry, it's unfortunate, but you shouldn't have gotten involved.

1006
00:53:29,873 --> 00:53:31,041
这不是她的错。
It's not her fault.

1007
00:53:31,708 --> 00:53:33,585
-这不是她的错。——汤姆。
- It's not her fault. - Tom.

1008
00:53:33,669 --> 00:53:37,589
-这怎么不是她的错?-这不是…-有些事是她的错。——汤姆。汤姆。
- How is this not her fault? - It's not... - Some things are her fault. - Tom. Tom.

1009
00:53:38,257 --> 00:53:39,383
哦,汤姆。
Oh, Tom.

1010
00:53:39,466 --> 00:53:41,009
她生病了。
She's sick.

1011
00:53:45,722 --> 00:53:47,558
我们能找到杀害比尔·米金斯的凶手。
We can find who killed Bill Meekins.

1012
00:53:47,641 --> 00:53:50,185
很可能就是杀了他女儿的人。
It's probably the same people who killed his daughter.

1013
00:53:50,727 --> 00:53:51,854
我们正在调查。
We're looking into it.

1014
00:53:52,354 --> 00:53:55,941
这个信息就能洗清我们的罪名。
And, uh, that information will clear our names.

1015
00:53:56,024 --> 00:54:02,072
验尸报告显示他可能是在欧洲时服用过量药物中毒。
Now, the autopsy indicated that he was possibly poisoned by too many medicines while he was in Europe.

1016
00:54:02,156 --> 00:54:05,075
你知道他和谁一起来的吗，谁派他来的?
Do you know who he was traveling with, who sent him?

1017
00:54:05,159 --> 00:54:08,662
我可以帮你查清楚，但我不能亲自插手。
I can help you find out, but I can't get personally involved.

1018
00:54:08,745 --> 00:54:09,830
你是个胆小鬼，汤姆。
You're a coward, Tom.

1019
00:54:09,913 --> 00:54:11,707
你竟敢叫他胆小鬼。
Don't you dare call him a coward.

1020
00:54:11,790 --> 00:54:14,126
你知道预科学校的孩子们是这么叫他的。
You know that's what he was called by those prep-school kids.

1021
00:54:14,209 --> 00:54:16,295
太残忍了，瓦莱丽，你知道的。
It's cruel, Valerie, and you know that.

1022
00:54:16,712 --> 00:54:19,965
他们想让我参与所有的委员会，俱乐部。
They want me to get involved in all these committees, clubs.

1023
00:54:20,757 --> 00:54:22,134
你知道我是怎么做的吗?
Do you know what I do instead?

1024
00:54:24,344 --> 00:54:26,013
我是一个鸟类观察者。
I'm a bird watcher.

1025
00:54:26,513 --> 00:54:27,931
这就是我的工作。
That's what I do.

1026
00:54:28,015 --> 00:54:29,933
一定很好吧，带你出去。
Mm, it must be good, get you outside.

1027
00:54:30,017 --> 00:54:32,519
你是一个观鸟者。他是荒谬的。
You're a bird watcher. He's ridiculous.

1028
00:54:32,603 --> 00:54:37,774
他并不比你和你的电影，刀片，茶杯，你做的那些可怕的东西更可笑。
He's no more ridiculous than you are with your movies, razor blades, teacups, the horrid things you make.

1029
00:54:37,858 --> 00:54:39,526
说真的，瓦莱丽，他们疯了。
Honestly, Valerie, they're demented.

1030
00:54:39,610 --> 00:54:40,652
原谅我。
Excuse me.

1031
00:54:41,236 --> 00:54:46,408
你说过你能帮我们找到和他一起去欧洲的人。谁会知道呢?
You said that you could help us find who traveled with him to Europe. Who would know?

1032
00:54:49,745 --> 00:54:51,914
吉尔·迪伦贝克会知道的。你认识他吗?
Gil Dillenbeck would know. Do you know him?

1033
00:54:53,040 --> 00:54:54,374
全国人民都知道他。
The whole country knows him.

1034
00:54:54,458 --> 00:54:57,252
他是美国历史上授勋最多的海军陆战队员。
He's the most decorated Marine in US history.

1035
00:54:57,336 --> 00:54:58,670
-是的。-是的，他是。
- Yeah. - Yes, he is.

1036
00:54:59,296 --> 00:55:01,548
迪伦贝克是米金斯的朋友。
Dillenbeck was friends with Meekins.

1037
00:55:01,632 --> 00:55:02,799
他们都是将军。
They were both generals.

1038
00:55:02,883 --> 00:55:04,551
我从没参过军。
I never got involved in the military.

1039
00:55:04,635 --> 00:55:06,887
我只是经营家族的纺织公司。
I just ran the family's textile company.

1040
00:55:07,554 --> 00:55:10,516
迪伦贝克能告诉你谁和米金斯一起去的。
Dillenbeck can tell you who was traveling with Meekins.

1041
00:55:11,183 --> 00:55:12,327
我不会相信其他人。
I wouldn't trust anyone else.

1042
00:55:12,351 --> 00:55:15,145
而我自己没有接触到这种信息的渠道。
And I don't have access to that kind of information myself.

1043
00:55:16,063 --> 00:55:18,774
-好的，好的。我们见过他两次。-是的。
- Okay, okay. We met him twice. - Yeah.

1044
00:55:18,857 --> 00:55:24,530
在比利时和他拍过一次照，还有一次…——华盛顿——红利军行军——在32年夏天。——正确的。
Took a picture with him once in Belgium and another... - D.C. - at the Bonus Army march - in summer '32. - Right.

1045
00:55:24,613 --> 00:55:26,007
我们还留着那些照片，沃兹先生。
We still have those pictures, Mr. Voze.

1046
00:55:26,031 --> 00:55:27,032
是的。正确的。
Yeah. Right.

1047
00:55:27,115 --> 00:55:29,117
他对和谁说话很讲究。
He's very particular about who he'll speak to.

1048
00:55:30,410 --> 00:55:34,998
如果你们见过他，你们是他尊敬的士兵，你们的机会比我大得多。
If you've met him, and you're soldiers he respects, your chances are far better than mine.

1049
00:55:35,082 --> 00:55:37,084
是的，他不信任有钱的人。
Yeah, he distrusts people of means.

1050
00:55:37,918 --> 00:55:39,586
如果你见到他，请一定告诉我们。
If you meet him, please do let us know.

1051
00:55:39,670 --> 00:55:41,255
我很想和他握手。
I would love to shake his hand.

1052
00:55:42,422 --> 00:55:46,009
莉比在新闻短片里看到了迪伦贝克，她迷上了他。
Libby saw Dillenbeck in the newsreel, and she has a crush on him.

1053
00:55:46,093 --> 00:55:47,719
别傻了，瓦莱丽。
Don't be ridiculous, Valerie.

1054
00:55:47,803 --> 00:55:49,429
你已经谈到了那个新闻短片。
You have talked about that newsreel.

1055
00:55:49,513 --> 00:55:50,597
他是个令人印象深刻的人。
He's a very impressive man.

1056
00:55:50,681 --> 00:55:51,682
是的，他是。
Yes, he is.

1057
00:55:51,765 --> 00:55:53,141
我正好喜欢那部新闻片。
And I happen to like that newsreel.

1058
00:55:53,225 --> 00:55:54,285
别玩了。别玩了，汤姆。
Don't play it. Don't play it, Tom.

1059
00:55:54,309 --> 00:55:55,662
我们应该在他们走之前放一放。
Oh, we should play it before they go.

1060
00:55:55,686 --> 00:56:00,466
瓦莱丽，吉尔·迪伦贝克也许是你朋友们摆脱麻烦的唯一希望。
Valerie, Gil Dillenbeck is perhaps the one hope your friends have of getting out of all this trouble.

1061
00:56:04,987 --> 00:56:07,114
你想看新闻片吗?
Would you like to see the newsreel?

1062
00:56:09,199 --> 00:56:10,367
哦,很好。
Oh, good.

1063
00:56:12,828 --> 00:56:18,333
去年夏天为福利而游行的退伍军人仍在吉尔·迪伦贝克将军的领导下。
The veterans who marched last summer for benefits remain under the leadership of General Gil Dillenbeck.

1064
00:56:18,417 --> 00:56:23,589
尽管这位勇敢的将军仍然是他们的代言人，但退伍军人的福利仍然没有支付。
The veterans' benefits are still unpaid, though the brave general remains their spokesperson.

1065
00:56:24,256 --> 00:56:27,467
听着，听着，这让我很生气。
Look, look, it makes me so damn mad.

1066
00:56:27,551 --> 00:56:30,053
很多人都说你们是流浪汉。
A whole lot of people speak of you as tramps.

1067
00:56:30,137 --> 00:56:32,598
“流浪汉!你们这些人都是流浪汉。”
"Tramps! You men are tramps."

1068
00:56:32,681 --> 00:56:35,517
这些人是谁，竟敢这么叫你?
Who are these people who dare call you that?

1069
00:56:35,601 --> 00:56:36,768
你是士兵。
You're soldiers.

1070
00:56:36,852 --> 00:56:39,771
你们牺牲了自己的生命和四肢。
You sacrificed your lives, your limbs.

1071
00:56:39,855 --> 00:56:42,608
你为你的国家受苦了。
You've suffered that for your country.

1072
00:56:45,944 --> 00:56:48,905
政府把他们赶出了首都。
The government burned them out of the nation's capital.

1073
00:56:48,989 --> 00:56:51,325
退伍军人从未得到过任何福利。
Veterans never got one benefit.

1074
00:56:51,408 --> 00:56:57,998
除了你们这些家伙，还有谁为这个国家，为这部法律，为这部宪法，流血牺牲了?
Who in the hell has done all the bleeding for this country, and for this law, and this Constitution anyhow, but you fellows?

1075
00:56:58,081 --> 00:56:59,750
汤姆，它毁了新闻片。
Tom, it ruined the newsreel.

1076
00:56:59,833 --> 00:57:01,918
我很抱歉，亲爱的。我会把它换掉。
I'm so sorry, darling. I will replace that.

1077
00:57:02,002 --> 00:57:03,378
Libby珍贵的新闻短片。
Libby's precious newsreel.

1078
00:57:03,462 --> 00:57:06,089
我们在那里。我们和将军合影留念。
We were there. We took pictures with the general.

1079
00:57:06,173 --> 00:57:08,634
这么英俊的男人。真是个强壮的男人。
Such a handsome man. Such a strong man.

1080
00:57:08,717 --> 00:57:11,178
这才是一个人真正的品质。
Now that is true character in a man.

1081
00:57:11,261 --> 00:57:13,221
汤姆的性格也很好。
Tom is also of excellent character.

1082
00:57:13,305 --> 00:57:15,932
是的，比起政治，他更喜欢观鸟。
And, yes, he prefers birding to politics.

1083
00:57:16,016 --> 00:57:17,684
但它是有意义的。
But it's meaningful.

1084
00:57:17,768 --> 00:57:19,561
你说你会回来的。
You said you'd come back.

1085
00:57:20,479 --> 00:57:22,814
为什么?这样你就可以离开我了?
Why? So you could leave me?

1086
00:57:23,815 --> 00:57:28,236
我不知道我是不是一场短暂的冒险或者你有没有想过我，瓦莱丽。
I didn't know if I was a fleeting adventure or if you even thought about me at all, Valerie.

1087
00:57:28,737 --> 00:57:31,907
我从没想过别人。不是真的。
I never thought of anyone else. Not really.

1088
00:57:33,116 --> 00:57:34,284
你呢?
What about you?

1089
00:57:35,786 --> 00:57:37,579
不。不是真的。
No. Not really.

1090
00:57:38,914 --> 00:57:39,915
真的吗?
Really?

1091
00:57:41,083 --> 00:57:42,084
是的。
Yes.

1092
00:57:43,794 --> 00:57:45,021
你说"尴尬"是什么意思?
And what did you mean, "embarrassed"?

1093
00:57:45,045 --> 00:57:46,085
你这话是什么意思?
What did you mean by that?

1094
00:57:46,129 --> 00:57:49,174
这么多年都不好意思联系我?
Embarrassed to contact me all these years?

1095
00:57:49,841 --> 00:57:53,512
只是看到我这个样子。我…这不是我在阿姆斯特丹时的样子。
Just seeing me like this. I... It's not who I was in Amsterdam.

1096
00:57:53,595 --> 00:57:55,180
为了什么?为了什么?
And for what? For what?

1097
00:57:55,263 --> 00:57:57,099
在这个国家我们不能在一起。
We can't be together in this country.

1098
00:58:03,939 --> 00:58:05,190
你看到那个花园了吗?
You see that garden?

1099
00:58:06,942 --> 00:58:09,361
我每天至少在外面待一个小时。
I spend at least an hour out there every day.

1100
00:58:09,444 --> 00:58:10,946
-哦，太好了。毫米。
- Oh, that's great. - Mm.

1101
00:58:11,863 --> 00:58:18,870
看到玫瑰胸脯的巨嘴鸟，黑眼睛的junco，让我想起上帝的绿色大地。
See a rose-breasted grosbeak, a dark-eyed junco, reminds me of God's green earth.

1102
00:58:18,954 --> 00:58:20,038
嗯。
Hmm.

1103
00:58:20,747 --> 00:58:37,514
是啊，我不认识那些鸟。但是…有一个来自英国的人违反了观鸟的所有神圣规则，他进入了一种濒临灭绝的鸟类的24个巢穴，取下了24个鸟蛋。
Yeah, I don't know those birds. But... There's this man from England who has violated every sacred rule of birding by going into 24 nests of a near-extinct species of bird to take 24 eggs.

1104
00:58:38,265 --> 00:58:43,979
这一切都是为了一个人的自私荣耀为了让他的名字因为一些毫无意义的发现而出现在鸟类书籍上。
All for one man's selfish glorification to get his name in a bird book for some meaningless discovery.

1105
00:58:46,565 --> 00:58:52,237
我认为，这种人，很可能会对比尔·米金斯和他的女儿做出可怕的事。
And that is the type of person, I think, who very likely did something awful to Bill Meekins and his daughter.

1106
00:58:52,320 --> 00:58:53,381
我正试着跟你走呢，先生。
I'm trying to follow you here, sir.

1107
00:58:53,405 --> 00:59:01,246
你是说那个人，那个鸟，英格兰，那个巢，还有那本书，是他杀了比尔·米金斯?
You're saying that man, the bird thing, England, the nest, and the book, that he killed Bill Meekins?

1108
00:59:02,247 --> 00:59:04,958
我只是想说明一点。是吗?
I'm trying to make a point. Yeah?

1109
00:59:05,041 --> 00:59:06,793
那种男人。
That type of man.

1110
00:59:07,878 --> 00:59:11,089
好的。我还是不确定。你是什么意思?
Okay. I'm still not certain. What do you mean?

1111
00:59:12,048 --> 00:59:16,845
伯伦森医生，你的药和老兵让你看起来是个好人。
Dr. Berendsen, you seem like a good person with your medicines and your veterans.

1112
00:59:17,721 --> 00:59:20,599
你不应该被阻碍。你应该得到帮助。
You shouldn't be hindered. You should be helped.

1113
00:59:21,516 --> 00:59:27,272
-但我只是一个人。-长官，我们什么都没做，我们要让警察知道这一点。
- But I'm only one person. - Sir, we didn't do anything, and we need the police to know that.

1114
00:59:30,066 --> 00:59:31,151
也许Dillenbeck。
Maybe Dillenbeck.

1115
00:59:35,572 --> 00:59:37,324
明天好吗?
Tomorrow?

1116
00:59:37,407 --> 00:59:39,427
你明天能再来吗?房子将是空的。
Can you come back tomorrow? The house will be empty.

1117
00:59:39,451 --> 00:59:42,412
他们会去另一个家参加莉比的文化讲座，谢谢。
They'll be at the other house for one of Libby's culture talks, please.

1118
00:59:43,705 --> 00:59:45,916
嘘。
Shush.

1119
00:59:45,999 --> 00:59:48,210
“嘘”是什么意思?你们在做什么?
What do you mean, "shush"? What are you guys doing?

1120
00:59:48,752 --> 00:59:51,713
我一直在讨论英国鸟类协会的罪行。
I've been discussing crimes of the bird society of England.

1121
00:59:52,214 --> 00:59:53,673
你哥哥有点古怪。
Your brother's a little kooky.

1122
00:59:53,757 --> 00:59:57,260
伯特，我不知道发生了什么，但这绝不是米金斯和他女儿的事。
Burt, I don't know what's happening, but it's far beyond Meekins and his daughter.

1123
00:59:57,344 --> 00:59:59,763
我现在也不相信我的药物了。
And I don't trust my medications now either.

1124
01:00:00,472 --> 01:00:03,975
我们只要找到迪伦贝克就行了。就是这样。
We just have to get Dillenbeck. That's it.

1125
01:00:04,601 --> 01:00:06,061
太好了，带我一起去。
Great, take me with you.

1126
01:00:06,144 --> 01:00:08,563
-瓦莱丽。-我可以来。我可以帮忙。
- Valerie. - I can come. I can help.

1127
01:00:09,397 --> 01:00:11,650
-她可以。这是真的。——伯特。
- She can. It's true. - Burt.

1128
01:00:11,733 --> 01:00:13,401
我们三个，形影不离。
The three of us, we were inseparable.

1129
01:00:13,485 --> 01:00:16,780
我们做事，我们做事，最重要的是，我们活着。
We did things, we got things done, and most of all, we lived.

1130
01:00:17,364 --> 01:00:21,076
——哈罗德?-我必须离开这里-求你了-她说得对。
- Harold? - I have to get out of here, - please! - She's right.

1131
01:00:21,159 --> 01:00:23,703
——伯特。她可以帮助我们。-我可以帮忙。
- Burt. She could help us. - I can help.

1132
01:00:23,787 --> 01:00:24,788
瓦莱丽?
Valerie?

1133
01:00:24,871 --> 01:00:25,997
你在做什么?
What are you doing?

1134
01:00:26,081 --> 01:00:27,642
是时候把你的朋友叫到门口了。
It's time to get your friends to the door.

1135
01:00:27,666 --> 01:00:29,334
马林医生要来了。
Dr. Malin's coming.

1136
01:00:33,338 --> 01:00:35,382
谢谢你能来。抱歉给您添麻烦了。
Thank you for coming. Sorry for the trouble.

1137
01:00:35,841 --> 01:00:38,510
谢谢你！这是非常有用的。
Thank you. This turned out very helpful.

1138
01:00:38,593 --> 01:00:39,886
很期待。
Looking forward to this.

1139
01:00:40,554 --> 01:00:42,722
请代我向卡尔顿告别。
Please say goodbye to Carlton for me.

1140
01:00:45,475 --> 01:00:47,352
谢谢你！回头再聊。
Thank you. Talk to you soon.

1141
01:00:53,441 --> 01:00:54,442
瓦莱丽?
Valerie?

1142
01:00:55,235 --> 01:00:58,071
玛琳医生会带着你要的药过来，记得吗?
Dr. Malin will be here with the remedies you asked for, remember?

1143
01:01:02,117 --> 01:01:03,201
你是马林医生吗?
Are you Dr. Malin?

1144
01:01:03,577 --> 01:01:04,744
是的。是的，我是。
Yes. Yes, I am.

1145
01:01:04,828 --> 01:01:10,500
哦，我是医生。如果你不介意我问一下，以你的专业意见，她的情况如何?
Oh, I'm a doctor. If you don't mind my asking, in your professional opinion, what is her condition?

1146
01:01:11,376 --> 01:01:13,545
遗传性神经紊乱。
Hereditary nervous disorder.

1147
01:01:13,920 --> 01:01:17,674
影响她的血压，平衡，神经和动作。
Affects her blood pressure, her balance, her nerves and movement.

1148
01:01:18,174 --> 01:01:20,218
不，她以前没得过，医生。
No, she never had that before, Doctor.

1149
01:01:21,052 --> 01:01:22,554
它随着年龄的增长而增长。
It advances with age.

1150
01:01:23,972 --> 01:01:25,432
-谢谢。-谢谢你，医生。
- Thank you. - Thank you, Doctor.

1151
01:01:31,730 --> 01:01:32,814
我的上帝。
My God.

1152
01:01:32,898 --> 01:01:34,357
真不敢相信我们见到了瓦莱丽。
I can't believe we saw Valerie.

1153
01:01:34,441 --> 01:01:36,651
-明天第一件事…-她看起来很好。
- First thing tomorrow... - She looks great.

1154
01:01:37,277 --> 01:01:39,589
第一件事……真倒霉，她得了那种病。
First thing... Such bad luck, she got that ailment.

1155
01:01:39,613 --> 01:01:42,532
我们去迪伦贝克，希望能进去。
We go to Dillenbeck's, and we hope we get in.

1156
01:01:42,616 --> 01:01:45,118
迪伦贝克说不行，伯特。
Dillenbeck said no, Burt.

1157
01:01:45,201 --> 01:01:46,453
Dillenbeck说不?
Dillenbeck said no?

1158
01:01:46,536 --> 01:01:48,472
什么叫他拒绝了?你和他谈过了吗?
What do you mean, he said no? Did you talk to him?

1159
01:01:48,496 --> 01:01:49,789
我和他妻子谈过了。
I talked to his wife.

1160
01:01:49,873 --> 01:01:51,833
她说没有。他们的游客太多了。
She said no. They get too many visitors.

1161
01:01:51,917 --> 01:01:54,085
我们……我们必须继续努力。
We... We have to keep trying.

1162
01:01:54,169 --> 01:01:58,840
你有没有把……我们见面时的照片?
Uh, did you send, uh, the... the... the photographs of when we met him?

1163
01:01:58,924 --> 01:02:02,469
不行，因为你得自己带照片来。
No, because you have to bring the pictures yourself.

1164
01:02:02,552 --> 01:02:03,803
好吧，哈罗德在哪儿?
All right, where is Harold?

1165
01:02:03,887 --> 01:02:05,531
他本该带我去迪伦贝克家的。
He was supposed to take me to Dillenbeck's.

1166
01:02:05,555 --> 01:02:07,265
他几小时前就该来了。
He was meant to be here hours ago.

1167
01:02:07,349 --> 01:02:08,350
我不知道。
I don't know.

1168
01:02:08,433 --> 01:02:11,937
但警察来了，他们想和你谈谈。
But the police are here, and they wanna talk to you.

1169
01:02:13,647 --> 01:02:17,067
好的。好吧，一切都要一起来。
Okay. All right, everything all at once.

1170
01:02:17,150 --> 01:02:19,319
厄玛·圣克莱尔也在等着。
Irma St. Clair is waiting, also.

1171
01:02:19,402 --> 01:02:21,863
哦,上帝!好吧。
Oh, God! All right.

1172
01:02:22,656 --> 01:02:26,493
嗯…现在不行。不是现在。
Uh... Peanuts Not now. Not now.

1173
01:02:28,662 --> 01:02:31,873
-哦，得了吧。-你确定这里安全吗，瓦莱丽?-是的，很安全。它很好。
- Oh, come on. - Are you sure - this is safe, Valerie? - Yes, it's safe. It's fine.

1174
01:02:31,957 --> 01:02:34,584
他们在另一栋房子里。他们会在那里呆一整天。
They're at the other house. They'll be there all day.

1175
01:02:38,129 --> 01:02:39,673
还记得这个吗?
Remember this?

1176
01:02:39,756 --> 01:02:42,217
你看起来很完美。
You look perfect.

1177
01:02:42,926 --> 01:02:43,927
这是你的。
That's you.

1178
01:02:48,640 --> 01:02:49,641
这是你的。
That's you.

1179
01:02:58,108 --> 01:02:59,734
为什么?
Pourquoi?

1180
01:02:59,818 --> 01:03:02,028
——阿姆斯特丹。-说“阿姆斯特丹”。
- Amsterdam. - Say, "Amsterdam."

1181
01:03:02,570 --> 01:03:03,822
阿姆斯特丹。
Amsterdam.

1182
01:03:05,240 --> 01:03:06,950
阿姆斯特丹。
Amsterdam.

1183
01:03:07,575 --> 01:03:08,868
这药肯定更好。
This pill has gotta be better.

1184
01:03:08,952 --> 01:03:10,036
当然。
Of course.

1185
01:03:10,120 --> 01:03:12,747
莫蒂，这是缓解疼痛和紧张的药。
Morty, it's for the pain and the nerves.

1186
01:03:13,665 --> 01:03:16,209
盖特韦勒警探，你想要药。
Detective Getweiler, you want the medicine.

1187
01:03:16,292 --> 01:03:17,293
让我来帮你。
Let me do that for ya.

1188
01:03:17,377 --> 01:03:18,437
-来吧。-我的屁股疼死了。
- Come on. - This hip is killing me.

1189
01:03:18,461 --> 01:03:19,754
不，不，不。来吧。来吧。
No, no, no. Come on. Come on.

1190
01:03:19,838 --> 01:03:21,715
把它给我。把它给我。
Give it to me. Give that to me.

1191
01:03:21,798 --> 01:03:24,050
我的屁股疼死了。
My hip is killing me.

1192
01:03:25,552 --> 01:03:27,053
好了。
There you go.

1193
01:03:27,137 --> 01:03:29,055
-太痛苦了。-求你了，求你了。
- So painful. - Please, please, please.

1194
01:03:29,139 --> 01:03:31,182
我下次再做吧。朋友是干什么用的?
Let me do that next time. What are friends for?

1195
01:03:31,266 --> 01:03:33,018
我想不会再有下次了。
I think there will be no next time.

1196
01:03:33,101 --> 01:03:34,269
听我说。
Listen to me.

1197
01:03:34,352 --> 01:03:36,396
我们可能要关闭你的办公室了。
We might have to close down your office.

1198
01:03:37,105 --> 01:03:39,357
莱姆，把办公室关了?
Lem, close down the office?

1199
01:03:39,441 --> 01:03:41,317
是的，关闭你的办公室，是的。
Yeah, close down your office, yeah.

1200
01:03:41,401 --> 01:03:42,610
我们需要确凿的证据。
We need hard evidence.

1201
01:03:42,694 --> 01:03:45,321
希尔兹警探，你不明白。
Detective Hiltz, look, you don't understand.

1202
01:03:45,405 --> 01:03:47,198
我和莱姆，这个和这个。
Me and Lem, this and this.

1203
01:03:47,282 --> 01:03:48,283
告诉他，莱姆。
Tell him, Lem.

1204
01:03:48,366 --> 01:03:52,370
没错，我们的血液里，大脑里都有金属。想象一下。
Exactly, we got metal in our blood, in our brain. Imagine that.

1205
01:03:52,454 --> 01:03:54,164
你的足弓很平。
You have flat arches.

1206
01:03:54,247 --> 01:03:56,958
你不能发球。我们理解。
You couldn't serve. We understand.

1207
01:03:57,042 --> 01:03:58,269
你们还是我们的头号嫌疑人。
You're still our chief suspects.

1208
01:03:58,293 --> 01:03:59,294
为什么?
Why?

1209
01:03:59,377 --> 01:04:02,547
为什么?你知道，你知道这不是我们干的。
Why? You know, you know we didn't do this.

1210
01:04:02,630 --> 01:04:03,923
不，所有人都说是你干的。
No, everyone says you did it.

1211
01:04:04,007 --> 01:04:07,010
每个人都说吗?每一个…有一个人。
Everyone says? Every... There was one man.

1212
01:04:07,093 --> 01:04:08,344
-是的。-他做到了。
- Yeah. - He did it.

1213
01:04:08,428 --> 01:04:12,640
现在我的队长需要知道你为什么要，秘密地对父亲进行尸检。
Now my captain needs to know why you did that, uh, hush-hush autopsy on the father.

1214
01:04:12,724 --> 01:04:14,684
这件事没有什么秘密可言。
There was nothing hush-hush about it.

1215
01:04:14,768 --> 01:04:18,313
莉兹·米金斯授权的。完全合法的。
Liz Meekins authorized it. Completely legal.

1216
01:04:18,396 --> 01:04:19,689
哈罗德可以证实。
Harold can verify that.

1217
01:04:19,773 --> 01:04:21,024
让我们看看尸检结果。
Let's see the autopsy results.

1218
01:04:21,107 --> 01:04:23,544
是的，让我把厄玛·圣克莱尔的尸检报告拿过来。
Yes, let me get the autopsy from Irma St. Clair right in here.

1219
01:04:23,568 --> 01:04:27,280
对不起，医生。在海外，我知道他们有增强力量的药物。
Excuse me, Doctor. Overseas, I understand that they have medicines for strength.

1220
01:04:27,363 --> 01:04:29,199
你这里有什么东西可以增强体力吗?
Do you got anything here for strength?

1221
01:04:29,282 --> 01:04:30,909
——什么?——权力?权力。
- What? - Power? Power.

1222
01:04:30,992 --> 01:04:34,221
能给我验尸报告吗是的,但是……-来自Irma St. claire…-希尔兹，等等。
Can I get the autopsy report... Yeah, but... - from Irma St. Clair... - Hiltz, wait.

1223
01:04:34,245 --> 01:04:35,598
城里最好的验尸护士之一?
One of the best autopsy nurses in the city?

1224
01:04:35,622 --> 01:04:36,915
谢谢你！是的，谢谢。
Thank you. Yes, thank you.

1225
01:04:37,540 --> 01:04:39,042
乐观。
Optimism.

1226
01:04:40,001 --> 01:04:44,923
我知道自从上次见面后我们都过得很不寻常。
I understand we both had a very unusual time since last we saw each other.

1227
01:04:45,715 --> 01:04:46,716
发生了什么事?
What happened?

1228
01:04:46,800 --> 01:04:48,802
你的外套为什么披在肩上?
Why is your coat over your shoulder?

1229
01:04:49,427 --> 01:04:50,845
这就是我想告诉你的。
That's what I wanted to tell you.

1230
01:04:50,929 --> 01:04:55,850
我在提交尸检结果的时候，这个满脸通红的人，一脸怒气……-天啊。
I was filing the autopsy results when this red-faced man - with an angry face... - Oh, God.

1231
01:04:55,934 --> 01:04:57,977
-还有另一个人…-怎么了?
- And this other man... - What happened?

1232
01:04:58,061 --> 01:05:03,608
他们把我推倒，打断了我的手腕，然后拿到了尸检结果。
They threw me down, they broke my wrist, and they took the autopsy results.

1233
01:05:03,691 --> 01:05:04,984
他们拿走了一切。
They took everything.

1234
01:05:05,068 --> 01:05:06,778
-但那不是…-做得不好。
- But it wasn't... - That's not well done.

1235
01:05:06,861 --> 01:05:08,029
-我知道。-那是有角度的。
- I know. - That is angulated.

1236
01:05:08,113 --> 01:05:10,657
这需要重新设置，否则情况会非常糟糕。
That needs to be reset, or else that is gonna be very bad.

1237
01:05:10,740 --> 01:05:12,951
嗯…-可以吗?——好的。
Uh... - Can I? - Okay.

1238
01:05:13,034 --> 01:05:15,154
我来帮你拿外套。-让我坐下。谢谢你！
- Let me take your coat. - Let me sit down. Thank you.

1239
01:05:15,245 --> 01:05:16,871
你还好吗?
Are you all right?

1240
01:05:20,208 --> 01:05:22,752
不，这不是…不是一份好工作。
No, this is not... not a good job.

1241
01:05:22,836 --> 01:05:24,546
就是这样。等一等。两个。
That's it. Hold on. Two more.

1242
01:05:24,629 --> 01:05:30,802
有一次，你告诉我你是否喜欢西班牙的旋律…——什么?——还是古典音乐?
One time, you were telling me whether you like the Spanish melody... - What? - or was it classical?

1243
01:05:30,885 --> 01:05:35,765
经典……就是这样。就是这样。
Classical... That's it. That's it.

1244
01:05:35,849 --> 01:05:37,851
全部完成。没关系。
All done. It's okay.

1245
01:05:38,476 --> 01:05:41,521
没关系。好了。
It's okay. All right now.

1246
01:05:41,604 --> 01:05:42,772
——好吗?——是的。
- Okay? - Yes.

1247
01:05:42,856 --> 01:05:44,732
就是这样。我得找个吊绳。
That's it. I gotta get a sling.

1248
01:05:44,816 --> 01:05:47,026
-保持支撑。——是的。
- Just keep that supported. - Yes.

1249
01:05:47,777 --> 01:05:49,988
我很抱歉把你卷进来了。
I'm so sorry that you got mixed up in all this.

1250
01:05:50,572 --> 01:05:51,698
我是验尸护士。
I'm an autopsy nurse.

1251
01:05:51,781 --> 01:05:53,575
我卷入了各种各样的事情。
I get mixed up in all sorts of things.

1252
01:05:53,658 --> 01:05:56,077
而且，让我离你更近了…
Besides, brought me closer to you and to...

1253
01:05:59,038 --> 01:06:00,456
他们在等我们。
They're waiting for us.

1254
01:06:02,458 --> 01:06:03,585
让他们等待。
Let them wait.

1255
01:06:12,969 --> 01:06:14,387
他为什么在放音乐?
Why is he playing music?

1256
01:06:14,470 --> 01:06:15,471
他喜欢音乐。
He likes music.

1257
01:06:15,555 --> 01:06:17,891
我不知道他现在为什么要弹。
I don't know why he's playing it now.

1258
01:06:19,142 --> 01:06:20,393
你喜欢这种音乐吗?
Do you like this music?

1259
01:06:21,311 --> 01:06:24,355
我吗?我不知道。
Me? I don't know.

1260
01:07:10,735 --> 01:07:11,736
比阿特丽斯。
Beatrice.

1261
01:07:13,905 --> 01:07:14,989
你在这里做什么?
What are you doing here?

1262
01:07:15,073 --> 01:07:16,449
这个女人是谁?
Who is this woman?

1263
01:07:18,910 --> 01:07:21,037
这是厄玛。我们一起工作。
This is Irma. We work together.

1264
01:07:21,120 --> 01:07:22,372
嗯哼。
Mm-hmm.

1265
01:07:23,873 --> 01:07:26,918
她是…她是验尸护士。
She's, uh... She's an autopsy nurse.

1266
01:07:27,001 --> 01:07:28,086
别跟我胡扯。
Don't give me that.

1267
01:07:28,836 --> 01:07:30,004
回家。
Come home.

1268
01:07:30,588 --> 01:07:32,590
我会违抗我的家人，这样我们就能在一起了。
I'll defy my family so we can be together.

1269
01:07:32,674 --> 01:07:33,883
这是真的吗?
Is this real?

1270
01:07:34,926 --> 01:07:36,636
你为什么偏偏现在在这里?
Why are you here now, of all times?

1271
01:07:36,719 --> 01:07:38,304
你从没来过这里。
Like, you never come here.

1272
01:07:38,388 --> 01:07:42,254
因为雪莉是站在我这边的，她会给我打电话告诉我什么时候该保护我丈夫。
'Cause Shirley's on my side, and she calls me and tells me when to protect my husband.

1273
01:07:43,059 --> 01:07:44,619
我父亲控制着你的行医执照
My father controls your medical license.

1274
01:07:44,644 --> 01:07:45,979
你知道的。
You know that.

1275
01:07:47,522 --> 01:07:58,491
你能让你父母在退伍军人晚会的委员会上签名吗，这样我们就能获得尊重和尊严，你也可以告诉你父母汤姆·沃兹可能会参与进来?
Can you get your parents to put their names on the committee for the gala for the veterans, so we can get respect and dignity, and you can tell your parents that Tom Voze might, uh, get involved?

1276
01:07:59,158 --> 01:08:00,743
嗯，是的。
Well, uh, yes.

1277
01:08:00,827 --> 01:08:02,471
但你要怎么抓到他?你抓不到他的。
But how will you get him? You won't get him.

1278
01:08:02,495 --> 01:08:03,538
我见过他了。
I already met him.

1279
01:08:04,789 --> 01:08:06,082
我介绍过你。
I introduced you.

1280
01:08:06,165 --> 01:08:12,422
你没介绍我们认识。你跟我们说了他的事，然后我和哈罗德见了他。
Well, you didn't introduce us. You told us about him, and then me and Harold, we met him.

1281
01:08:13,506 --> 01:08:15,300
真的很抱歉，伯特。
Really sorry, Burt.

1282
01:08:15,925 --> 01:08:20,263
我觉得你应该想想你是谁，你想成为什么。
I think you should think about who you are and what you want to be.

1283
01:08:32,233 --> 01:08:34,110
雪莉。不是有益的。
Shirley. Not helpful.

1284
01:08:34,944 --> 01:08:35,945
我们需要一个吊绳!
We need a sling!

1285
01:08:36,029 --> 01:08:37,363
尸检结果呢?
Where are the autopsy results?

1286
01:08:37,447 --> 01:08:43,536
莱姆，她很可能是被推利兹·米金斯的那个人推的。-我拿到弹弓了。
She was rolled, Lem, quite possibly by the same man - who pushed Liz Meekins. - I got the sling.

1287
01:08:43,619 --> 01:08:46,372
我可以给你描述一下。他大概……你是说它们被偷了?
I can give you a description. He was about... You mean, they're stolen?

1288
01:08:46,456 --> 01:08:47,623
是的，它们被偷了。
Yes, they were stolen.

1289
01:08:48,333 --> 01:08:49,751
那么，结果如何呢?
So, what about the results?

1290
01:08:49,834 --> 01:08:51,711
我可以告诉你结果。我记得他们。
I can tell you the results. I remember them.

1291
01:08:51,794 --> 01:08:57,216
我在他的胃里发现了水银，鲁米诺和安眠药，含量很高。
I found mercury, luminol, and somnifene in his stomach, and they were in high amounts.

1292
01:08:57,300 --> 01:09:00,053
我相信是在他生命的最后一周给他的。
I believe they were given to him the last week of his life.

1293
01:09:00,136 --> 01:09:03,222
上周，也就是说可能在船上。
Last week, which means probably on the boat.

1294
01:09:03,306 --> 01:09:05,426
所以我们没有东西可以给队长，对吧?
So, we don't have anything to give our captain, right?

1295
01:09:05,975 --> 01:09:08,353
她刚把证据给你了。
She just gave you the evidence.

1296
01:09:09,020 --> 01:09:11,481
我可以给你一份宣誓书。我一直都在做。
I can give you an affidavit. I do them all the time.

1297
01:09:11,564 --> 01:09:12,648
我被这座城市束缚住了。
I'm bonded by the city.

1298
01:09:12,732 --> 01:09:13,900
怎么样?对吧?
How about that? Right?

1299
01:09:13,983 --> 01:09:15,210
-我是说，我们正在做…-还有认证。
- I mean, we are doing... - And certified.

1300
01:09:15,234 --> 01:09:16,736
是的。我们在为你做你的工作。
Yes. We're doing your job for you.

1301
01:09:16,819 --> 01:09:18,446
那死去的女儿呢?
What about the dead daughter?

1302
01:09:18,529 --> 01:09:19,530
把这家伙扔进监狱。
Throw this guy in jail.

1303
01:09:19,614 --> 01:09:20,865
让我来处理。
Let me handle this.

1304
01:09:20,948 --> 01:09:23,076
——登月舱。登月舱,登月舱。-这是什么…请不要碰那个。
- Lem. Lem, Lem. - What's this... Please do not touch that.

1305
01:09:23,159 --> 01:09:24,911
-堕落的茶具?-那是艺术。
- Degenerate tea set? - That is art.

1306
01:09:24,994 --> 01:09:26,513
你得把这个处理掉。它是淫秽的。
You gotta get rid of this. It's obscene.

1307
01:09:26,537 --> 01:09:27,890
-那是艺术。-不，那不是艺术
- That's art. - No, that's not art.

1308
01:09:27,914 --> 01:09:30,750
艺术是美丽的，可爱的，发人深省的。
Art is beautiful, lovely, evokes thoughts.

1309
01:09:30,833 --> 01:09:31,876
就是这样。
That's what that is.

1310
01:09:32,377 --> 01:09:33,795
-是这样吗?——是的。
- That's what that is? - Yes.

1311
01:09:33,878 --> 01:09:37,924
为什么你要拿一套茶具，一个可爱的茶具，把它变成暴力工具?
Why would you take a tea set, a lovely tea set, and turn it into an instrument of violence?

1312
01:09:38,007 --> 01:09:39,777
-问得好。-这没道理。
- That's a good question. - It makes no sense.

1313
01:09:39,801 --> 01:09:42,428
莱姆，也许是世纪问题。
Perhaps, Lem, the question of the century.

1314
01:09:43,596 --> 01:09:45,973
不要想太多。
Don't think about it too much.

1315
01:09:46,057 --> 01:09:47,308
——登月舱。——伯特。
- Lem. - Burt.

1316
01:09:47,392 --> 01:09:49,477
莱姆，友情在哪里?
Lem, where is the camaraderie?

1317
01:09:49,560 --> 01:09:51,646
我们在阿贡河。让我们活下去。
We were in the Argonne. Let's live.

1318
01:09:51,729 --> 01:09:53,606
Voulons温文尔雅。
Voulons vivre.

1319
01:09:53,689 --> 01:09:55,733
新药丸。记住这一点。
New pill. Remember this.

1320
01:09:55,817 --> 01:09:56,943
Souviens-toi。
Souviens-toi.

1321
01:09:57,026 --> 01:09:58,778
-你欠我的。——好的。
- You owe me. - Okay.

1322
01:09:58,861 --> 01:10:00,279
但你也欠我的。
But you owe me too.

1323
01:10:01,614 --> 01:10:03,574
把哈罗德和利兹·米金斯的合同给我。
Get me Harold's contract with Liz Meekins.

1324
01:10:04,283 --> 01:10:05,410
我会的。
I will.

1325
01:10:05,493 --> 01:10:08,162
真理是可能的。
Truth is possible.

1326
01:10:08,246 --> 01:10:12,834
我想，爱，也许，甚至是可能的。
And I think that love, maybe, is even possible.

1327
01:10:12,917 --> 01:10:15,461
这个药丸起作用了。
And this pill is working.

1328
01:10:19,382 --> 01:10:20,716
真理，爱，还是什么?
Truth, love, what?

1329
01:10:23,136 --> 01:10:25,680
哈罗德有辆车。我只有一只眼睛。
Harold has the car. I only got one eye.

1330
01:10:25,763 --> 01:10:27,849
-他们不让我开车。-我们会找到他们的
- They don't let me drive. - We'll find them.

1331
01:10:27,932 --> 01:10:28,933
没关系。
It's okay.

1332
01:10:29,016 --> 01:10:40,445
西班牙夫人，我崇拜你从我第一次见到你的那一晚起我的心就一直渴望着你我还能做什么呢?
Lady of Spain, I adore you Right from the night I first saw you My heart has been yearning for you What else could any heart do?

1333
01:10:40,528 --> 01:10:44,031
西班牙夫人，我爱你天哪。
Lady of Spain, I love you Oh, my God.

1334
01:10:44,115 --> 01:10:46,075
这听起来很棒。拉里。
This sounds terrific. Larry.

1335
01:10:46,159 --> 01:10:47,702
它没有被取消，对吧?
It's not canceled, right?

1336
01:10:47,785 --> 01:10:48,786
不是取消了吧?
It's not canceled, is it?

1337
01:10:48,870 --> 01:10:50,550
-绝对没有取消。-哦，谢谢。
- Definitely not canceled. - Oh, thank you.

1338
01:10:50,621 --> 01:10:52,999
同学聚会太棒了，你要唱歌。
The reunion is a gem, and you're gonna sing.

1339
01:10:53,082 --> 01:10:55,126
我们要表演了!
We are going to perform!

1340
01:10:56,711 --> 01:10:59,046
你要小心。
You be careful.

1341
01:11:00,214 --> 01:11:01,215
弥尔顿!
Milton!

1342
01:11:02,425 --> 01:11:05,553
哈罗德几小时前就该来我办公室了。
Harold was supposed to be at my office hours ago.

1343
01:11:05,636 --> 01:11:07,472
你没事吧?你看起来不太好。
You okay? You don't look good.

1344
01:11:08,014 --> 01:11:09,974
事情变得越来越复杂了，不是吗?
Things have gotten more complicated, haven't they?

1345
01:11:10,683 --> 01:11:13,019
你知道吗，我祖父朝一个人的脸开了一枪。
You know, my grandfather shot a guy in the face.

1346
01:11:13,561 --> 01:11:15,271
他的脸中枪了。
And he got shot in the face.

1347
01:11:15,354 --> 01:11:16,564
不同场合。
Separate occasions.

1348
01:11:16,647 --> 01:11:18,232
不同场合。不是同一个人。
Separate occasions. Not the same guy.

1349
01:11:18,858 --> 01:11:20,151
一切都解决了。
And it all worked out.

1350
01:11:20,693 --> 01:11:22,361
——好。-走吧。
- Good. - Let's go.

1351
01:11:22,445 --> 01:11:25,198
Burt博士。伯特。我神经紧绷。
Dr. Burt. Burt. I got a pinched nerve.

1352
01:11:25,656 --> 01:11:28,326
不,我……我…我还不知道该怎么办。
No, I'm... I... I don't know what to do with that yet.

1353
01:11:28,409 --> 01:11:30,786
我们可以在那里。好的,很好。
We can be right there. Okay, good.

1354
01:11:32,455 --> 01:11:35,333
你去哪儿了?我担心死了。
Where have you been? I've been worried sick.

1355
01:11:35,416 --> 01:11:37,668
我们开车去兜风，发现了很多东西。
We went on a drive and found out a lot of things.

1356
01:11:38,211 --> 01:11:43,591
你本来要去见吉尔·迪伦贝克的，却不能开车出去。
Well, you're not supposed to go for a drive, when you're supposed to meet Gil Dillenbeck.

1357
01:11:43,674 --> 01:11:47,178
警察在等你答应他们的文件。
And the police are waiting on papers that you promised them.

1358
01:11:47,261 --> 01:11:48,471
有人扇你耳光了吗，伯特?
Did someone slap you, Burt?

1359
01:11:48,554 --> 01:11:50,223
因为你脸上有一块红印。
'Cause you have a red mark on your face.

1360
01:11:50,306 --> 01:11:54,519
我摔倒了，我被扇了耳光，我…卡尔顿打了我一拳。
I fell, I got slapped, I got... Carlton punched me.

1361
01:11:54,602 --> 01:11:55,853
是啊，我当时在场。
Yeah, I was there for that one.

1362
01:11:55,937 --> 01:11:57,730
我们也被打了。
We got roughed up too.

1363
01:11:57,813 --> 01:11:59,315
我们的处境很尴尬。
We were in quite a situation.

1364
01:11:59,398 --> 01:12:02,026
求你了，现在不行。在车里。
Please, not now. In the car.

1365
01:12:02,109 --> 01:12:05,279
米尔顿，把这些拿给盖特韦勒警探。好吧?
Milton, get these to Detective Getweiler. All right?

1366
01:12:05,363 --> 01:12:07,865
这是莉斯·米金斯的雇佣合同。
This is Liz Meekins's employment contract.

1367
01:12:07,949 --> 01:12:12,537
我有说过我预言过一个被关在盒子里的白人会带来极大的麻烦吗?
Did I mention that I predicted extreme trouble from a white man in a box?

1368
01:12:13,079 --> 01:12:19,252
然后被一个卡车下的白人女人加了进去。
Then added to by a white woman under a truck.

1369
01:12:19,335 --> 01:12:20,670
重点是什么，弥尔顿?
The point, Milton?

1370
01:12:20,753 --> 01:12:25,800
你知道吗，我宁愿因为杀了五个白人男人而受审，而不是一个白人女人。
You know, I'd rather be on trial for killin' five white men than one white woman.

1371
01:12:26,175 --> 01:12:30,680
因为这会导致一个或多个黑人死在盒子里。
'Cause this can lead to one Black man or more dead in a box.

1372
01:12:31,389 --> 01:12:32,932
拜托，我们走吧。
Please, let's get going.

1373
01:12:33,015 --> 01:12:35,810
我们几小时前就该去迪伦贝克家了。
We should've left for Dillenbeck's hours ago.

1374
01:12:36,269 --> 01:12:40,273
这是我们摆脱警察困境的唯一希望。
That's the only hope that we have to get out of this situation with the police.

1375
01:12:41,065 --> 01:12:42,191
我们为什么停在这里?
Why are we stopping here?

1376
01:12:42,275 --> 01:12:43,401
这里不是巴克斯县。
This is not Bucks County.

1377
01:12:43,484 --> 01:12:44,753
这还没出城呢。
This is not even out of the city.

1378
01:12:44,777 --> 01:12:46,904
我们要在华尔道夫酒店稍作停留。
We're making a quick stop at the Waldorf.

1379
01:12:46,988 --> 01:12:48,155
迪伦贝克在华尔道夫吗?
Is Dillenbeck at the Waldorf?

1380
01:12:48,239 --> 01:12:49,466
我们不是来见迪伦贝克的。
We're not here to see Dillenbeck.

1381
01:12:49,490 --> 01:12:50,530
你在说什么?
What are you talking about?

1382
01:12:50,575 --> 01:12:52,135
我们在这里做什么?哈罗德,瓦莱丽!
What are we doing here? Harold, Valerie!

1383
01:12:53,077 --> 01:12:54,078
难以置信!
Unbelievable!

1384
01:12:54,161 --> 01:12:55,305
先生，欢迎光临华尔道夫酒店。
Welcome to the Waldorf Astoria, sir.

1385
01:12:55,329 --> 01:12:57,641
还要多久……我们不会住在华尔道夫的。
How long will... We're not staying at the Waldorf.

1386
01:12:57,665 --> 01:12:59,584
我们今天只有一件事要做，哈罗德。
We had one thing to do today, Harold.

1387
01:12:59,667 --> 01:13:01,752
一件事。试着和吉尔·迪伦贝克谈谈。
One thing. Try to talk to Gil Dillenbeck.

1388
01:13:01,836 --> 01:13:06,483
也许还会有个活动…-这就是我的情况…-尊严和…我们今天看到的，伯特。
And maybe have an event with a modicum... - This is my situation... - of dignity and... from my past that we saw today, Burt.

1389
01:13:06,507 --> 01:13:08,527
被扭曲的是我内心的平静，伯特。
And it's my peace of mind that's been twisted, Burt.

1390
01:13:08,551 --> 01:13:11,196
在我们弄清真相之前，迪伦贝克帮不了我们。
Dillenbeck can't help us until we know what's really going on.

1391
01:13:11,220 --> 01:13:12,722
这是怎么回事?
Well, what is going on?

1392
01:13:12,805 --> 01:13:14,682
我不知道，但我们会查出来的。
I don't know, but we're gonna find out.

1393
01:13:14,765 --> 01:13:15,766
把钥匙给我。
Give me the keys.

1394
01:13:15,850 --> 01:13:16,910
-绝对不行。-给我钥匙。
- Absolutely not. - Give me the keys.

1395
01:13:16,934 --> 01:13:19,437
你不能开车。你不会开车，你这个独眼疯子。
You're not driving. You can't drive, you one-eyed nut.

1396
01:13:20,688 --> 01:13:22,356
哈罗德，这可不明智。
Harold, this is not smart.

1397
01:13:23,482 --> 01:13:26,986
至少告诉我这是谁。
At least, just tell me who we're seeing here.

1398
01:13:27,612 --> 01:13:28,988
保罗·坎特伯雷。
Paul Canterbury.

1399
01:13:30,156 --> 01:13:31,282
保罗·坎特伯雷?
Paul Canterbury?

1400
01:13:31,741 --> 01:13:33,534
-是的。是的。-那个玻璃眼的家伙?
- Yeah. Yeah. - The glass-eye guy?

1401
01:13:33,618 --> 01:13:35,494
从阿姆斯特丹。恩人吗?
From Amsterdam. The benefactor?

1402
01:13:36,037 --> 01:13:37,496
她还在和他们说话，伯特。
She still talks to them, Burt.

1403
01:13:40,541 --> 01:13:43,377
-你好，保罗。-瓦莱丽，你好吗?
- Hello, Paul. - Oh, Valerie, how are you?

1404
01:13:43,461 --> 01:13:44,503
给你。
There you are.

1405
01:13:45,546 --> 01:13:46,547
哈罗德。
Harold.

1406
01:13:46,631 --> 01:13:47,840
保罗·坎特伯雷。
Paul Canterbury.

1407
01:13:48,341 --> 01:13:50,009
伯伦森，你好吗?
Berendsen, how are you?

1408
01:13:51,052 --> 01:13:54,221
给你。深褐色的绿色。
Here you go. Dark hazel green.

1409
01:13:54,847 --> 01:13:56,599
——嗯。-一盒六个。
- Eh. - Box of six.

1410
01:13:57,558 --> 01:13:58,684
你真是太好了。谢谢你！
Very kind of you. Thank you.

1411
01:14:00,269 --> 01:14:01,270
啊!
Ah!

1412
01:14:01,771 --> 01:14:02,938
这是喝茶时间。
It's teatime.

1413
01:14:04,106 --> 01:14:06,192
只有我喜欢红葡萄酒吗?
Is it just me who fancies claret?

1414
01:14:06,275 --> 01:14:09,111
我喜欢一手拿着它，一手拿着茶。
I like to have it going in one hand and tea in the other.

1415
01:14:09,195 --> 01:14:11,197
我们现在有点困境，保罗。
We're in a bit of a predicament, Paul.

1416
01:14:11,280 --> 01:14:12,907
谢谢你抽出时间来见我们。
Thank you for taking the time to see us.

1417
01:14:12,990 --> 01:14:18,245
瓦莱丽，作为绅士，我们愿意做任何必须做的事。
Valerie, we're prepared to do anything we must as gentlemen.

1418
01:14:18,329 --> 01:14:19,413
你粗鲁的人!
You bounder!

1419
01:14:19,497 --> 01:14:21,540
你作弊!你真让我恶心!
You cheat! You disgust me!

1420
01:14:21,624 --> 01:14:23,459
历史会救赎我的。
History will redeem me.

1421
01:14:23,542 --> 01:14:24,543
才不会呢。
Like hell it will.

1422
01:14:25,544 --> 01:14:27,004
对不起,每一个人。
Sorry, everyone.

1423
01:14:27,880 --> 01:14:31,342
没关系。酒水我请。字面上。
It's all right. Drinks on me. Literally.

1424
01:14:33,469 --> 01:14:35,012
你好。这边请。
Hello. This way, please.

1425
01:14:37,723 --> 01:14:43,979
你记得亨利·诺克罗斯吗?他是那个美国人……他们不需要谈论的联邦雇员，否则我相信他们不会在这里。
You remember Henry Norcross? He's the American... Federal employee they don't need to talk about, or I trust they wouldn't be here.

1426
01:14:45,356 --> 01:14:53,030
这一切与英国的“玻璃生意”和华盛顿的融资有什么关系?
What does all of this have to do with a "glass business" in England and, uh, financing in Washington?

1427
01:14:53,114 --> 01:14:54,323
它们是重叠的。
Well, they overlap.

1428
01:14:54,407 --> 01:14:55,676
有很多事情是重叠的，伯伦森。
Lots of things overlap, Berendsen.

1429
01:14:55,700 --> 01:15:00,204
如果你仔细观察，整个世界以最危险的方式重叠在一起。
The whole world overlaps in its most treacherous way if you pay attention.

1430
01:15:00,287 --> 01:15:03,374
你们好，伯特，哈罗德，瓦莱丽。
And hello, Burt, Harold, Valerie.

1431
01:15:03,457 --> 01:15:05,185
-你好，亨利。-你气色不错，亨利
- Hello, Henry. - You're looking good, Henry.

1432
01:15:05,209 --> 01:15:10,548
我也很高兴在我们再次聚集在历史正确的一边时见到你们。嗯?
It's good to see you too as we gather here once more on the right side of history. Huh?

1433
01:15:10,631 --> 01:15:15,803
保罗，我知道刚才在茶馆有人把饮料泼到你脸上了。——是的。
