1434
01:15:15,886 --> 01:15:18,013
只是英格兰的一些旧事，亨利。
Just some old business from England, Henry.

1435
01:15:18,097 --> 01:15:20,474
不，不，不。在你脸上喝一杯就是在我脸上喝一杯。
No, no, no. A drink in your face is a drink in my face.

1436
01:15:20,558 --> 01:15:21,660
我想听一听。
I'd like to hear about it, please.

1437
01:15:21,684 --> 01:15:23,227
然后我们再谈别的事。
Then we'll get on to new business.

1438
01:15:23,310 --> 01:15:26,897
他是英国鸟类学会的人。
It was someone from the Ornithological Society of Great Britain.

1439
01:15:26,981 --> 01:15:28,941
那些混蛋中的一个，是吧?
Ah, one of those rotten bastards, huh?

1440
01:15:29,024 --> 01:15:31,360
是的。
Yeah.

1441
01:15:33,028 --> 01:15:34,029
什么?
What?

1442
01:15:34,739 --> 01:15:39,535
有人给我讲了一个发生在英国鸟类协会的坏事。
I was told a story about a misdeed in the bird society of England.

1443
01:15:40,327 --> 01:15:43,414
我开始怀疑那个故事是不是关于你的。
And I'm starting to wonder if that story is about you.

1444
01:15:43,497 --> 01:15:46,125
我们的发现绝非微不足道。
Our discovery was hardly trivial.

1445
01:15:46,208 --> 01:15:51,422
是的，我们证明了布谷鸟缺乏建造自己巢穴的能力，礼貌和性格。
Yes, we proved that the cuckoo lacks the capacity, the civility, the character to build its own nest.

1446
01:15:51,505 --> 01:15:52,506
哇。
Wow.

1447
01:15:53,257 --> 01:15:58,804
这对任何人或任何事来说有什么意义或有趣的呢?
How is that possibly significant or interesting to anybody or anything?

1448
01:15:58,888 --> 01:16:01,474
因为这表明杜鹃是一种寄生鸟。
Because it shows that the cuckoo is a parasitic bird.

1449
01:16:01,557 --> 01:16:04,101
它欺骗了那些筑巢的好鸟。
It tricks better birds who build nests.

1450
01:16:04,185 --> 01:16:08,481
布谷鸟破坏宿主的蛋，然后破坏巢穴本身。
Cuckoo destroys the host's eggs, and then destroys the nest itself.

1451
01:16:08,564 --> 01:16:11,358
伯伦森，布谷鸟根本不在乎。好吗?
Berendsen, the cuckoo doesn't give a damn. Okay?

1452
01:16:11,442 --> 01:16:17,740
我想说，这是对自然界包括人类在内的寄生破坏行为的深刻阐述。-听着，听着。
I'd say it's a profound statement on the parasitic destructive behavior of nature, - including humans. - Hear, hear.

1453
01:16:17,823 --> 01:16:20,534
在我们今天看到的事情之后，这一点尤其正确。
That is especially true after what we saw today.

1454
01:16:21,243 --> 01:16:23,662
伯特，这是关于我们遭遇的故事。听好了。
Burt, it's the story about what happened to us. Listen up.

1455
01:16:23,746 --> 01:16:25,289
我们一直想告诉你，伯特。
We have been trying to tell you, Burt.

1456
01:16:25,372 --> 01:16:27,625
我觉得保罗和亨利也该听听。
And I think Paul and Henry should hear this too.

1457
01:16:27,708 --> 01:16:31,504
但我们今天去了一个很奇怪的诊所发现了这个。
But we ended up at a very strange clinic today and we found this.

1458
01:16:33,631 --> 01:16:35,382
这些符号到处都是。
Those symbols were everywhere.

1459
01:16:36,342 --> 01:16:37,843
你以前见过吗?
Have you seen it before?

1460
01:16:37,927 --> 01:16:39,345
五人委员会。
The Committee of the Five.

1461
01:16:41,388 --> 01:16:46,310
按照我们的约定，我去见了瓦莱丽，但我们注意到有人在监视我们。
I went to see Valerie as we'd arranged, but then we noticed somebody was watching us.

1462
01:16:46,393 --> 01:16:48,153
有人隔着窗帘看着我们。
Someone was watching us through the curtains.

1463
01:16:48,938 --> 01:16:51,148
就是他推了莉斯·米金斯。
That's the man who pushed Liz Meekins.

1464
01:16:51,690 --> 01:16:56,028
他一定是等得不耐烦了因为他要走了，然后我们决定跟踪他。
And he must've got bored waiting because he started to leave, and then we decided to follow him.

1465
01:16:56,111 --> 01:16:57,822
他带我们去了罗克兰县。
And he led us to Rockland County.

1466
01:16:58,739 --> 01:17:00,783
去了一栋没有标志的砖房。
To an unmarked brick building.

1467
01:17:09,750 --> 01:17:11,603
他们以为我们是做手术的病人。
They assumed that we were patients for a procedure.

1468
01:17:11,627 --> 01:17:13,128
消毒。
To be sterilized.

1469
01:17:13,212 --> 01:17:15,256
强制绝育诊所。
Ah, a forced sterilization clinic.

1470
01:17:15,339 --> 01:17:16,757
然后我看到了那个人。
Then I saw the man.

1471
01:17:16,841 --> 01:17:19,718
这个红脸男人。推利兹·米金斯的人。
This red-faced man. The man who pushed Liz Meekins.

1472
01:17:19,802 --> 01:17:24,014
他看着我，然后说…这是你结束自卑的时刻。
He looked right at me, and he said... This is your moment to end your inferiority.

1473
01:17:24,098 --> 01:17:25,683
你要做这个手术。
You're gonna have that procedure.

1474
01:17:30,980 --> 01:17:32,147
不要动!
Don't move!

1475
01:17:34,275 --> 01:17:35,568
大便。
Shit.

1476
01:17:38,028 --> 01:17:39,405
谁去叫船长!
Somebody call the captain!

1477
01:17:41,657 --> 01:17:43,117
-来吧。-阻止那些人!
- Come on. - Stop those people!

1478
01:17:43,200 --> 01:17:45,035
——帮助!我们需要帮助!-叫舰长!
- Help! We need help! - Call the captain!

1479
01:17:46,996 --> 01:17:51,792
瓦莱丽的枪走火的时候，打中了一块玻璃，我们离开了那里，回城里去了。-天啊。
Well, when Valerie's gun finally went off, it hit a glass, and we got out of there - and headed back to the city. - My God.

1480
01:17:52,543 --> 01:17:54,753
我很高兴你没事。
Well, I'm glad you're all right.

1481
01:17:54,837 --> 01:18:00,426
但如果你没有拿到红脸杀手的身份证明，那就毫无用处了。
But if you didn't get the red-faced killer's identification, then it's of no help, whatsoever.

1482
01:18:00,509 --> 01:18:01,844
你在说什么，伯特?
What are you talking about, Burt?

1483
01:18:01,927 --> 01:18:03,446
它与一切都有关系。
It has everything to do with everything.

1484
01:18:03,470 --> 01:18:05,973
今天，所发生的一切，不得不……——如何?-从我开始。
Today, that what happened, has to... - How? - It starts with me.

1485
01:18:06,056 --> 01:18:07,141
好吧，从我开始。
Well, it starts with me.

1486
01:18:08,017 --> 01:18:14,481
我告诉德克萨斯州朗维尤的一些朋友，不要去这个非常恐怖的诊所，就像我们今天看到的那样。
I told some friends in Longview, Texas, not to visit this very horrifying clinic, a lot like the one we saw today.

1487
01:18:15,274 --> 01:18:17,484
一群暴徒。一群白人追我。
A mob. A mob of white men chased me.

1488
01:18:17,568 --> 01:18:19,153
他们骚扰我。他们想杀我。
They harassed me. They tried to kill me.

1489
01:18:19,236 --> 01:18:22,239
他们没有成功。他们非常不成功。
They were unsuccessful. They were very unsuccessful.

1490
01:18:22,323 --> 01:18:24,658
我离开了德州朗维尤，再也没回头。
I left Longview, Texas, and I never looked back.

1491
01:18:26,285 --> 01:18:30,080
不只是你和德州的事，也不只是今天洛克兰的事。
It's not just about you and Texas, nor today in Rockland.

1492
01:18:31,373 --> 01:18:34,960
有一个组织希望在全世界范围内这样做。
There is an organization that wishes to do this all over the world.

1493
01:18:36,420 --> 01:18:37,630
这是什么意思?
What does it mean?

1494
01:18:38,797 --> 01:18:46,597
这意味着这个国家有一个阴谋集团和德国的另一个阴谋集团有联系他们支持这些诊所，想要统治世界。
It means there's a cabal in this country tied to another in Germany who supports these clinics, who want to rule the world.

1495
01:18:47,640 --> 01:18:49,183
统治世界?
Rule the world?

1496
01:18:50,935 --> 01:18:52,227
完全正确的。
Exactly correct.

1497
01:18:53,812 --> 01:18:55,272
阴谋集团里有谁?
Who's in the cabal?

1498
01:18:55,689 --> 01:19:01,028
也许问谁是错误的问题。而是要问为什么。
Maybe who is the wrong question to ask. Instead ask why.

1499
01:19:02,863 --> 01:19:03,864
去找迪伦贝克。
Go see Dillenbeck.

1500
01:19:04,615 --> 01:19:08,452
问他为什么他的同事米金斯将军被杀了。
Ask him why his fellow, General Meekins, was murdered.

1501
01:19:08,535 --> 01:19:16,001
迪伦贝克，他一直在领导这个阴谋集团想弄清楚他们是谁，有什么计划。
Dillenbeck, he's been leading on this cabal to find out who they are, what they plan.

1502
01:19:17,211 --> 01:19:19,046
五人委员会。
Committee of the Five.

1503
01:19:20,547 --> 01:19:22,549
该组织名为Der Fünf。
The organization named Der Fünf.

1504
01:19:23,384 --> 01:19:24,385
五人委员会。
Committee of the Five.

1505
01:19:24,468 --> 01:19:25,788
想弄清楚他们是谁。
Trying to figure out who they are.

1506
01:19:25,844 --> 01:19:27,262
五人委员会。
Committee of the Five.

1507
01:19:27,346 --> 01:19:28,681
-是的。-是的。
- Yeah. - Yeah.

1508
01:19:28,764 --> 01:19:32,184
我觉得如果迪伦贝克能在你的同学会上发言就太好了。
I think it would be wonderful if Dillenbeck was the speaker at your reunion.

1509
01:19:33,811 --> 01:19:36,939
看来你的活动越来越重要了，伯伦森。
Seems your event's becoming rather important, Berendsen.

1510
01:19:37,982 --> 01:19:43,946
如果你能让迪伦贝克开口，也许能吸引到阴谋集团中更有影响力的成员。
If you can get Dillenbeck to speak, perhaps it might attract more influential members of the cabal.

1511
01:19:44,029 --> 01:19:47,783
是啊，是街上的杀手还是高层为这一切埋单。
Yeah, the killer from the street or the higher-ups paying for it all.

1512
01:19:47,866 --> 01:19:48,993
等等，等等，等等，等等。
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

1513
01:19:49,660 --> 01:19:59,044
不。我不希望我们的活动，哈罗德和我的活动，被任何人这样利用。
No. I don't want our event, Harold's and my event, to be used like this by anybody.

1514
01:19:59,128 --> 01:20:00,879
使用?不。
Used? No.

1515
01:20:02,172 --> 01:20:04,967
就当这是在保护你所爱的人。
Think of it as protecting what you love.

1516
01:20:05,050 --> 01:20:06,176
好吗?
Okay?

1517
01:20:07,094 --> 01:20:09,930
我们在阿姆斯特丹告诉过你我们会来拜访你，现在我们来了。
We told you in Amsterdam we'd come a-calling, and here we are.

1518
01:20:10,806 --> 01:20:11,974
给你。
And here you are.

1519
01:20:15,060 --> 01:20:16,395
我们谈完了吗?
Well, we done here?

1520
01:20:17,771 --> 01:20:19,606
还是你想多聊聊鸟类?
Or you wanna talk more about birds?

1521
01:20:19,690 --> 01:20:24,862
你知道吗，很多人认为这是关于…宁静:与自然的宁静或交流
You know, a lot of people assume that it's about the, uh... the tranquility or the communion with nature.

1522
01:20:24,945 --> 01:20:32,786
但我发现观鸟是如此迷人，因为它迫使你决定你在看什么。
But I find bird-watching so fascinating because it forces you to decide what you are looking at.

1523
01:20:34,288 --> 01:20:36,874
我在磨练我的鉴别力。
I am honing my art of discernment.

1524
01:20:36,957 --> 01:20:41,253
我希望你们相信我，我相信现在是干预的时候了。
And I want you to trust me that I believe now is the time to intervene.

1525
01:20:41,336 --> 01:20:51,430
我们请吉尔·迪伦贝克做这次活动的演讲者，他就会像磁铁一样吸引所有的钉子把这个充满背叛的房子推倒在地。
We get Gil Dillenbeck to be the speaker at this event, he will be the magnet that draws all the nails out of the wood and brings this house of treachery down to the ground.

1526
01:20:51,513 --> 01:20:52,931
你说呢，伯特?拜托。
So what do you say, Burt? Please.

1527
01:20:55,142 --> 01:20:56,560
请你试试，伯特。
Please try, Burt.

1528
01:21:02,149 --> 01:21:03,609
我不想说"我早告诉过你"
I don't like to say, "I told you so,"

1529
01:21:03,692 --> 01:21:07,237
但这一切比我们所有人想象的都要大得多。
but this is all turning out to be a lot larger than any of us imagined.

1530
01:21:07,321 --> 01:21:08,405
是的。
Yeah.

1531
01:21:08,489 --> 01:21:12,034
如果晚会是保罗用的…-你没事吧?-你没事吧?
If the gala is used by Paul... - Are you okay? - You good?

1532
01:21:12,117 --> 01:21:14,620
嗯哼。好吧。它来了又去。我很好。
Mm-hmm. Fine. It comes and goes. I'm fine.

1533
01:21:14,703 --> 01:21:15,704
是吗?
Yeah?

1534
01:21:16,246 --> 01:21:22,336
你感觉很好，然后突然眩晕，你感到头晕……它来了又去。
You feel fine, then all of a sudden, vertigo, you get dizzy... It comes and goes.

1535
01:21:22,419 --> 01:21:24,838
首先，他们告诉我，我患有癫痫。
First, they told me that I had epilepsy.

1536
01:21:24,922 --> 01:21:29,218
我从来没有发作过，但他们说我有癫痫，而且癫痫迟早会发作。
I'd never had a seizure, but they said I had epilepsy, and the seizures would come sooner or later.

1537
01:21:29,301 --> 01:21:31,970
但如果我服用药物，这是可以避免的。
But that could be avoided if I took medication.

1538
01:21:32,054 --> 01:21:33,138
我就这样做了。
And so I did.

1539
01:21:33,931 --> 01:21:37,559
然后我开始出现其他症状，更多的症状，他们说，“这是遗传的。”
And then I started having other symptoms, more symptoms, and they said, "That's hereditary."

1540
01:21:37,643 --> 01:21:38,870
“那是你母亲的遗传。”
"That's from your mother's side."

1541
01:21:38,894 --> 01:21:41,355
所以他们给了我新的药物，我一直在服用。
So they gave me new medications, and I kept taking that.

1542
01:21:41,438 --> 01:21:50,072
现在一年又一年过去了，我几乎不出家门，我感觉自己像个病人，活不下去了，我……我开始怀疑这一切了。
And now years and years have gone by and I'm barely leaving the house, and I feel like I'm a patient, and I can't live, and I... I'm starting to question all of it.

1543
01:22:16,723 --> 01:22:17,724
-你没事吧?——嗯。
- You okay? - Mm-hmm.

1544
01:22:17,808 --> 01:22:19,077
不，别碰我。别抱着我。
No, don't touch me. Don't hold me.

1545
01:22:19,101 --> 01:22:26,900
我很好。我能做到，我只需要…我只是需要在这里休息一下，只是……-天啊。你好吗?——婊子。
I'm fine. I can do this, and I just need... I just need a minute here to rest, just... - Oh, God. You good? - Bitch.

1546
01:22:26,984 --> 01:22:27,985
-瓦莱丽。-哦，是的。
- Valerie. - Oh, yes.

1547
01:22:28,068 --> 01:22:29,403
我很好。
I'm fine.

1548
01:22:30,112 --> 01:22:31,572
看，我在爬楼梯。
Look, I'm doing stairs.

1549
01:22:31,655 --> 01:22:33,824
我上楼梯也不会头晕。
I can go up stairs with no vertigo.

1550
01:22:33,907 --> 01:22:37,411
没有眩晕。我很好。我能跑。
No vertigo. I'm fine. I can run.

1551
01:22:37,494 --> 01:22:38,694
-哦，天哪…瓦莱丽!-瓦莱丽!
- Oh, my... Valerie! - Valerie!

1552
01:22:39,663 --> 01:22:40,807
带着那个喝醉的女人走!
Collect that drunk woman and go!

1553
01:22:40,831 --> 01:22:41,832
我们认识将军。
We know the general.

1554
01:22:41,915 --> 01:22:43,101
-我们有照片。-我没事，该死
- We have pictures. - I'm all right, damn it.

1555
01:22:43,125 --> 01:22:45,460
好了，我不要那些照片。
There, I don't want the pictures.

1556
01:22:45,544 --> 01:22:47,254
-快走!-我是医生。
- Go, now! - I'm a doctor.

1557
01:22:47,337 --> 01:22:48,547
-现在就走。-我是老兵。
- Go now. - And I am a veteran.

1558
01:22:48,630 --> 01:22:49,899
-你需要一个医生…-谢谢。
- You're gonna need a doctor... - Thank you.

1559
01:22:49,923 --> 01:22:51,609
-等我解决了你。——呼吸。简单呼吸就好。
- When I'm through with you. - Breathe. Just breathe.

1560
01:22:51,633 --> 01:22:53,027
快走，不然我就报警了。
Now, go or I'm gonna call the police.

1561
01:22:53,051 --> 01:22:54,362
-就几分钟…-不，我来吧。我做的事。
- Just a few minutes... - No, I've got it. I do.

1562
01:22:54,386 --> 01:22:55,613
-你丈夫的时间。——没有。
- Of your husband's time. - No.

1563
01:22:55,637 --> 01:22:59,325
我一定要战胜这些症状-走了…我并没有因此而沮丧。
I have to fight through these symptoms - at some point. - There goes... I'm not getting depressed about it.

1564
01:22:59,349 --> 01:23:01,143
我们洗清罪名的唯一机会。
Our one chance to clear our names.

1565
01:23:01,226 --> 01:23:03,645
你得换药，换医生。
You have to change your medicine and your doctor.

1566
01:23:04,146 --> 01:23:07,316
狗娘养的。我很好。
Son of a bitch. I was fine.

1567
01:23:09,151 --> 01:23:10,777
也许我该走了。
Maybe it's time for me to leave anyway.

1568
01:23:10,861 --> 01:23:12,154
离开是什么意思?
What do you mean, leave?

1569
01:23:12,237 --> 01:23:16,033
就算我们三个把米金斯解决了，坐牢的还是我。
Well, even if we solve Meekins out of the three of us, I'm the one that's going to jail.

1570
01:23:16,116 --> 01:23:18,076
-系统被操纵了。——哈罗德。
- The system's rigged. - Harold.

1571
01:23:18,160 --> 01:23:21,705
我从一开始就告诉过你，这份工作不是个好主意。
I told you from the get-go, this job was a bad idea.

1572
01:23:21,788 --> 01:23:26,460
弥尔顿告诉过你这份工作不是个好主意…
Milton told you this job was a bad idea...

1573
01:23:29,129 --> 01:23:30,881
但她得帮我们找到工作。
but she had to get us hired.

1574
01:23:30,964 --> 01:23:32,674
哦,“她”吗?“她得去……”
Oh, "she"? "She had to get..."

1575
01:23:33,759 --> 01:23:36,404
"她"还把你从监狱里救了出来，你好像忘了很多。
"She" also got you out of jail, which you seem to forget a lot.

1576
01:23:36,428 --> 01:23:38,347
你不能现在就不理我。
You can't turn your backs on me now.

1577
01:23:38,805 --> 01:23:40,641
你违反了约定，记得吗?
You broke the pact, remember?

1578
01:23:41,058 --> 01:23:42,935
我毁约了?什么时候?
I broke the pact? When?

1579
01:23:43,435 --> 01:23:45,103
我们告诉过你别走，伯特。
We told you not to leave, Burt.

1580
01:23:46,647 --> 01:23:50,400
至少你找到了爱，即使你得不到。
At least you found love, even if you can't get it.

1581
01:23:50,484 --> 01:23:53,237
我从来没那么幸运知道那到底是什么。
I've never been lucky enough to even know what the hell it is.

1582
01:23:53,737 --> 01:23:56,823
这种可怕的痛苦我不希望发生在任何人身上。
And that's a terrible affliction I don't wish on anyone.

1583
01:23:58,033 --> 01:23:59,701
我真希望我从没找到过它。
I wish I never did find it.

1584
01:24:00,661 --> 01:24:02,371
因为太疼了。
Because it hurts too much.

1585
01:24:04,957 --> 01:24:06,124
等等!
Wait!

1586
01:24:06,208 --> 01:24:08,752
将军想见你。
The general wants to meet you.

1587
01:24:11,255 --> 01:24:12,589
别搞砸了。
Don't screw this up.

1588
01:24:12,673 --> 01:24:13,966
-振作起来。-来吧!
- Straighten up. - Come on!

1589
01:24:14,049 --> 01:24:15,300
扶我走。
Help me walk.

1590
01:24:15,384 --> 01:24:17,788
之前的误会我很抱歉。
I'm sorry about the misunderstanding before.

1591
01:24:17,844 --> 01:24:19,221
不要紧。不要紧。
Never mind. Never mind.

1592
01:24:19,304 --> 01:24:22,224
我们这里有很多不速之客。
We get so many uninvited guests here.

1593
01:24:22,307 --> 01:24:24,768
-当然。-我们不想见到的人。
- Of course. - People we don't want to see.

1594
01:24:24,851 --> 01:24:26,603
-对不起。-谢谢。
- I'm sorry. - Thank you.

1595
01:24:26,687 --> 01:24:28,063
我没醉。
I'm not drunk.

1596
01:24:28,146 --> 01:24:31,566
小姐，你怎么了?你还好吗?
Uh, young lady, what is wrong with you? Are you all right?

1597
01:24:31,650 --> 01:24:35,829
有点眩晕，还有一些其他的…我现在正在停药。
It's a touch of vertigo and a couple of other... I'm coming off some medication at the moment.

1598
01:24:35,904 --> 01:24:39,741
我有过眩晕症，但世界一直在转。
I had vertigo once and the world just keeps moving.

1599
01:24:39,825 --> 01:24:42,494
我想请你喝一杯，但我们家没有酒。
I'd offer you a drink, but we don't keep alcohol in the house.

1600
01:24:42,577 --> 01:24:43,578
哦，那很好。
Oh, that's fine.

1601
01:24:46,164 --> 01:24:49,543
你可以把你的帽子和外套放在那边。
You can put your hat and coats over there.

1602
01:24:50,460 --> 01:24:51,878
你往这边走。
You're going up this way.

1603
01:24:51,962 --> 01:24:53,839
我们要赶在另一个客人前面吗?
Are we jumping ahead of another visitor?

1604
01:24:53,922 --> 01:25:00,304
马奎尔先生每个月都来讨论一些我丈夫永远得不到明确答复的问题。
Oh, Mr. Maguire comes every month to discuss something my husband can never get a clear answer about.

1605
01:25:00,387 --> 01:25:01,805
对吧，马奎尔先生?
Right, Mr. Maguire?

1606
01:25:01,888 --> 01:25:02,889
啊。
Ah.

1607
01:25:05,475 --> 01:25:07,060
我知道什么?
What do I know?

1608
01:25:07,144 --> 01:25:12,316
我只是想做鱼汤因为将军曾经在法国做过。
I'm just trying to make bouillabaisse because the general had it once in France.

1609
01:25:14,401 --> 01:25:17,154
将军?你的客人来了。
General? Your visitors are here.

1610
01:25:17,654 --> 01:25:19,448
你管你丈夫叫“将军”?
You call your husband "General"?

1611
01:25:19,531 --> 01:25:21,408
只在工作日。
Only on the weekdays.

1612
01:25:22,034 --> 01:25:23,577
你周末叫他什么?
What do you call him on weekends?

1613
01:25:24,453 --> 01:25:27,289
这是一个非常私人的问题。
That's a very personal question.

1614
01:25:27,956 --> 01:25:29,017
没人教过你礼貌吗?
Were you taught no manners?

1615
01:25:29,041 --> 01:25:30,101
别怪我害我们被赶出来了。
Don't blame me for getting us kicked out.

1616
01:25:30,125 --> 01:25:32,085
-我没有别的意思。-你紧张吗?
- I didn't mean anything by it. - Are you nervous?

1617
01:25:32,711 --> 01:25:34,355
她有一半时间都在开大家的玩笑。
She's pulling everybody's leg half the time.

1618
01:25:34,379 --> 01:25:35,422
这就是我爱她的原因。
That's why I love her.

1619
01:25:35,505 --> 01:25:37,257
太荣幸了，先生。
What an honor, sir.

1620
01:25:37,341 --> 01:25:40,289
是照片让你改变主意不想见我们了吗?
Um, was it the pictures that made you change your mind about seeing us?

1621
01:25:41,053 --> 01:25:43,513
我怎么知道照片里的人真的是你?
How can I know this is you, really, in the picture?

1622
01:25:44,848 --> 01:25:45,849
是的，先生。
Uh, yes, sir.

1623
01:25:45,932 --> 01:25:47,809
好吧，我是医生。
So, well, I'm the doctor.

1624
01:25:47,893 --> 01:25:49,770
她是护士。他是律师。
She's the nurse. He's the attorney.

1625
01:25:49,853 --> 01:25:54,483
我们都是在比利时认识的，如果你还记得的话，那是我们第一次见面的地方。
We all met in Belgium, which, if you recall, is where we met for the first time.

1626
01:25:54,566 --> 01:25:57,861
还有去年夏天在华盛顿举行的B.E.F.三月。
As well as Washington, last summer, at the B.E.F. March.

1627
01:25:58,820 --> 01:26:02,449
我告诉你一件我记得很清楚的事。
I'll tell you one thing that I can remember quite clearly.

1628
01:26:03,158 --> 01:26:09,081
你做了一件…我相信你唱了一首歌。
You did something that... You sang a song, I believe.

1629
01:26:10,374 --> 01:26:11,500
哪一个哪一个，先生?
Which... Which one, sir?

1630
01:26:11,583 --> 01:26:13,335
好吧，这是要你记住的。
Well, that's for you to remember.

1631
01:26:13,418 --> 01:26:16,963
我见了成千上万的人。你才见过我两次。
I met thousands of people. You just met me twice.

1632
01:26:17,047 --> 01:26:19,049
所以，你应该记住这首歌。
So, you should remember the song.

1633
01:26:20,592 --> 01:26:22,761
我想让你现在唱，然后我就知道是你了。
I'd like you to sing it now, then I'll know it's you.

1634
01:26:23,637 --> 01:26:24,679
唱首歌。
Sing a song.

1635
01:26:24,763 --> 01:26:27,057
你曾见过梦吗-梦游?——走?
Did you ever see a dream - Dream walking? - Walking?

1636
01:26:27,140 --> 01:26:30,977
嗯，我做了是的…你曾听过一个梦吗?说话吗?
Well, I did Yes... Did you ever hear a dream... Talking?

1637
01:26:31,061 --> 01:26:32,062
看到……正确的。
See... Right.

1638
01:26:32,145 --> 01:26:34,731
然后我做了哦，不，不。这是……不是这样的。
Then I did Oh, no, no. That's... That's not it.

1639
01:26:35,732 --> 01:26:38,318
嗯…是用法语写的吗?
Um... Was it in French?

1640
01:26:38,402 --> 01:26:39,820
我一听到就知道了。
I'll know it when I hear it.

1641
01:27:05,262 --> 01:27:07,806
是的。就是这样。
Yes. That was it.

1642
01:27:08,390 --> 01:27:09,516
这是正确的。
That's right.

1643
01:27:09,599 --> 01:27:11,017
我们瞎编的。
We made it up.

1644
01:27:11,101 --> 01:27:12,602
这是说不通的。
Well, it's not supposed to make sense.

1645
01:27:12,686 --> 01:27:14,438
这只是一首毫无意义的歌。
It's just a nonsense song.

1646
01:27:15,105 --> 01:27:16,815
但它让我们感觉很好。
But it makes us feel good.

1647
01:27:16,898 --> 01:27:18,733
-你是医生吗?-是的，先生。
- And you're the doctor? - That's right, sir.

1648
01:27:18,817 --> 01:27:22,279
你在一天内疏散了四千人。
And you evacuated 4,000 men in one day.

1649
01:27:22,362 --> 01:27:23,613
你很有名。
You're very famous.

1650
01:27:24,030 --> 01:27:25,073
不同的医生。
Different doctor.

1651
01:27:26,158 --> 01:27:29,661
那是旧金山来的社交男。
That's the social guy from San Francisco.

1652
01:27:30,370 --> 01:27:31,371
我的人生故事。
Story of my life.

1653
01:27:32,414 --> 01:27:33,415
不是你?
Not you?

1654
01:27:33,498 --> 01:27:37,127
伯特和我在一天内疏散了几千人，长官。
Burt and I did evacuate a couple of thousand men in one day, though, sir.

1655
01:27:37,210 --> 01:27:43,091
还有你，先生，你用刀捅了30个德国人，他们叫你黑死病?
And you, sir, you stabbed 30 Germans with your knife, and they called you "Black Death"?

1656
01:27:43,175 --> 01:27:45,177
不，先生，那是黑死病亨利·约翰逊。
No, sir, that was Black Death Henry Johnson.

1657
01:27:45,260 --> 01:27:48,930
但在他们给我这个之前，我确实得到了12个。——哦。
But I did get 12 of 'em - before they gave me this. - Oh.

1658
01:27:49,014 --> 01:27:50,724
我还救了很多人的命。
I also saved a lot of lives.

1659
01:27:50,807 --> 01:27:51,933
-真的吗?-是的。
- You did? - Yeah.

1660
01:27:52,434 --> 01:27:55,312
那是件值得骄傲的事。
Well, that's something to be proud of.

1661
01:27:55,395 --> 01:27:58,607
他们让你穿那些法国制服真是可耻。
It's shameful they made you wear those French uniforms.

1662
01:27:58,690 --> 01:28:00,370
你应该穿你自己国家的制服。
You should wear your own country's uniform.

1663
01:28:00,442 --> 01:28:03,069
从你嘴里传到上帝的耳朵里，先生，谢谢你。
From your mouth to God's ears, sir. Thank you.

1664
01:28:04,529 --> 01:28:06,072
那么，将军?
So, uh, General?

1665
01:28:07,741 --> 01:28:08,742
比尔Meekins。
Bill Meekins.

1666
01:28:09,326 --> 01:28:15,874
比尔·米金斯是我的朋友，他和他女儿的遭遇真是个悲剧。
Well, Bill Meekins was a friend of mine, and it's a tragedy what happened to him and his daughter.

1667
01:28:15,957 --> 01:28:18,043
没人关心这事真是太丢脸了。
And it's a disgrace that no one cares.

1668
01:28:18,126 --> 01:28:20,003
-哦，我们在乎。——事实上。
- Oh, we care. - Indeed.

1669
01:28:20,086 --> 01:28:22,964
其实是已故的伊丽莎白·米金斯雇的我们。
The late Elizabeth Meekins hired us, actually.

1670
01:28:23,048 --> 01:28:24,257
她雇了你?为什么?
She hired you? Why?

1671
01:28:24,841 --> 01:28:27,385
她不相信她父亲是自然死亡。
She didn't believe that her father died of natural causes.

1672
01:28:27,469 --> 01:28:29,095
在从欧洲回来的路上。
On his way back from Europe.

1673
01:28:29,179 --> 01:28:32,224
我最后一次和我朋友通话时，他从罗马给我打电话。
The last time I spoke to my friend, he called me from Rome.

1674
01:28:32,724 --> 01:28:34,309
从酒店打电话给我。
Called me from the hotel.

1675
01:28:34,768 --> 01:28:37,521
告诉我他看到了什么可怕的东西。
Told me of something monstrous that he had seen.

1676
01:28:38,146 --> 01:28:39,856
使他大为不安。
Disturbed him greatly.

1677
01:28:40,815 --> 01:28:43,693
这就是比尔被杀的原因。
That was why Bill was killed.

1678
01:28:48,490 --> 01:28:50,700
你进来的时候看到楼下那个人了吗?
You see the man downstairs when you came in?

1679
01:28:51,993 --> 01:28:56,748
每隔几周，他就会来…-你看到一个包了吗?——嗯。
Every couple of weeks, he comes and he brings... - Did you see a bag? - Mm-hmm.

1680
01:28:56,831 --> 01:28:59,709
他给了我一袋钱。
A bag of money he offers to me.

1681
01:29:00,168 --> 01:29:01,378
钱干什么?
Money for what?

1682
01:29:02,837 --> 01:29:04,172
发表演讲
To give a speech.

1683
01:29:05,423 --> 01:29:08,009
他不肯告诉我谁在背后支持他。我问他。
He won't tell me who's behind him. I ask him.

1684
01:29:09,052 --> 01:29:10,387
然后问:“这是谁送的?”
And say, "Who's this from?"

1685
01:29:10,470 --> 01:29:11,656
但他没有给我答案。
And he doesn't give me an answer.

1686
01:29:11,680 --> 01:29:13,348
他们付钱让你做他们的喉舌。
They're paying you to be their mouthpiece.

1687
01:29:13,431 --> 01:29:14,641
没错，完全正确。
That's right, exactly.

1688
01:29:14,724 --> 01:29:17,060
他们知道老兵们也会跟随。
And they know the veterans will follow.

1689
01:29:17,936 --> 01:29:19,104
五人委员会。
The Committee of the Five.

1690
01:29:19,563 --> 01:29:22,774
有人在试图做一些黑暗而奸诈的事。
Well, somebody is trying to do something dark and treacherous.

1691
01:29:26,194 --> 01:29:27,195
到这里来。
Come here.

1692
01:29:28,196 --> 01:29:29,948
问他愿不愿意在晚会上讲话。
Ask him if he'll speak at the gala.

1693
01:29:30,031 --> 01:29:31,992
进一步推进。就像亨利说的。
Push it further. Like Henry said.

1694
01:29:32,659 --> 01:29:36,913
先生，如果这些人要见你…——嗯。
Sir, um, if these guys - are meeting you... - Hmm.

1695
01:29:36,997 --> 01:29:46,172
如果你想找出幕后黑手是谁，为什么不更进一步把他们带到我们的重聚晚会上呢?
And you wanna find out who's behind it all, why not go further and lead them to our reunion gala event?

1696
01:29:46,256 --> 01:29:49,217
他们可能会以某种方式表现出来。
They might show themselves in some fashion.

1697
01:29:56,349 --> 01:29:58,977
马奎尔，你能告诉我，你为什么每个月都来?
Maguire, can you tell me, why do you come every month?

1698
01:29:59,477 --> 01:30:02,230
将军，我不能在别人面前说这件事。
Well, General, I can't speak about it in front of other people.

1699
01:30:02,314 --> 01:30:04,899
为什么不呢?我是说，你说没什么好隐瞒的。
Well, why not? I mean, you say there's nothing to hide.

1700
01:30:04,983 --> 01:30:06,901
这是为了一个好的事业。
And it's in the name of a good cause.

1701
01:30:06,985 --> 01:30:09,195
是的，先生，但不是每个人都明白。
Well, yes, sir. But not everyone understands it.

1702
01:30:09,279 --> 01:30:11,948
我不明白的是你代表的是谁。
What I don't understand is who or what you represent.

1703
01:30:13,116 --> 01:30:14,159
你能告诉我吗?
Can you tell me?

1704
01:30:15,785 --> 01:30:19,039
我无权透露我代表谁，先生。
Well, I'm not at liberty to say who I represent, sir.

1705
01:30:19,122 --> 01:30:24,711
但他们都是非常重要的人，他们有一个非常重要的组织会让一切变得更好。
Uh, but they are very important people, and they have a very important organization that's gonna change everything for the better.

1706
01:30:25,462 --> 01:30:31,176
正如我告诉过你的，先生，我们的目的是在经济危机时期正确地领导这个国家。
The purpose, as I've told you, sir, is to lead this nation properly in this time of economic crisis.

1707
01:30:31,259 --> 01:30:33,178
白宫里有个瘸子。
There's a cripple in the White House.

1708
01:30:33,637 --> 01:30:39,059
罗斯福是软弱的。我们希望你代表退伍军人和新领导层发言。
Roosevelt is weak. We'd like you to speak on behalf of the veterans and new leadership.

1709
01:30:39,142 --> 01:30:41,227
这就是选举的意义，马奎尔。
Well, that's what elections are for, Maguire.

1710
01:30:41,311 --> 01:30:42,854
你不相信宪法吗?
Don't you believe in the Constitution?

1711
01:30:43,355 --> 01:30:46,566
当然，但我们认为现在迫切需要采取行动。
Of course, but we feel that action is urgently needed now.

1712
01:30:47,233 --> 01:30:49,819
从一个退休将军那里得到的吗?
From a retired general before the election?

1713
01:30:49,903 --> 01:30:51,404
你想让我当独裁者吗?
Do you want me to be a dictator?

1714
01:30:51,488 --> 01:30:53,490
这是你的大赞助商想要的吗?
Is that what your big sponsors want?

1715
01:30:55,742 --> 01:30:56,910
呃,…一个独裁者?
Uh, a... A dictator?

1716
01:30:56,993 --> 01:30:59,245
不，没必要这么说。
No, it doesn't have to be said like that.

1717
01:30:59,329 --> 01:31:02,374
总理?这样会更好吗?
Okay, chancellor? Does that make it better?

1718
01:31:02,457 --> 01:31:04,334
这仍然违反宪法。
It still violates the Constitution.

1719
01:31:04,417 --> 01:31:06,920
他们在德国和意大利的老兵身上做了这个实验。
They did this with veterans in Germany and Italy.

1720
01:31:07,003 --> 01:31:08,129
很成功。
Very successful.

1721
01:31:12,175 --> 01:31:15,178
先生，五人委员会捐了一万八千人。
18,000, sir, from the Committee of the Five.

1722
01:31:15,261 --> 01:31:16,322
健全美元委员会。
Uh, Committee for a Sound Dollar.

1723
01:31:16,346 --> 01:31:17,746
-从谁那里?-五人委员会?
- From who? - Committee of the Five?

