我的亲爱的。
My darling.

1872
01:40:54,882 --> 01:40:57,051
我的亲爱的。
My darling.

1873
01:40:58,219 --> 01:41:01,138
那是Cornelius Vanderbilt。
That is Cornelius Vanderbilt.

1874
01:41:02,515 --> 01:41:03,516
妈妈吗?
Mother?

1875
01:41:03,599 --> 01:41:04,600
是的,亲爱的。
Yes, darling.

1876
01:41:04,684 --> 01:41:09,438
妈妈，那是康奈利·范德比尔特，他就站在爱丽丝·马博旁边。
Mother, that is Cornelius Vanderbilt, and he's standing right next to Alice Marble.

1877
01:41:09,522 --> 01:41:11,107
她可能会赢得美国网球公开赛。
She might win the US Open.

1878
01:41:11,190 --> 01:41:12,350
我的父母必须去见他们。
My parents have to meet them.

1879
01:41:12,400 --> 01:41:14,443
他们一直想见爱丽丝·马博。
They've wanted to meet Alice Marble the whole time.

1880
01:41:15,653 --> 01:41:18,030
你能等两秒钟，我们马上回来吗?
Can you just wait for two seconds and we'll come back?

1881
01:41:18,114 --> 01:41:20,700
你听到父亲说你要搬进来了吗?
Did you hear what Father said about you moving in?

1882
01:41:20,783 --> 01:41:23,160
-这不是很令人兴奋吗?-不用了，谢谢。
- Isn't that exciting? - No, thank you.

1883
01:41:24,704 --> 01:41:26,539
什么?你怎么…你是什么意思?
What? What do you... What do you mean?

1884
01:41:26,622 --> 01:41:27,832
不用了，谢谢。
No, thank you.

1885
01:41:29,458 --> 01:41:31,460
"不，谢谢"是什么意思?
What does "No, thank you" mean?

1886
01:41:32,044 --> 01:41:35,840
我等错的事等了太久。
I've waited too long for the wrong thing.

1887
01:41:37,800 --> 01:41:42,513
它变成了一个完全不同于以往的样子。
It turned into something very different than it ever once could be.

1888
01:41:45,641 --> 01:41:48,144
我觉得你可能会遭遇不幸。
I think terrible things might happen to you.

1889
01:41:49,770 --> 01:41:55,109
对别人说这种话……更不用说你的爱人了。
What a thing to say to anyone... let alone your beloved.

1890
01:42:01,782 --> 01:42:05,119
妈妈，那是科尼利厄斯·范德比尔特和爱丽丝·马博。我们去见见他们吧。
Mother, there's Cornelius Vanderbilt and Alice Marble. Let's go meet them.

1891
01:42:21,052 --> 01:42:22,094
没事的，伯特。
It's okay, Burt.

1892
01:42:23,262 --> 01:42:24,680
是啊，你还有我们。
Yeah, you still have us.

1893
01:42:26,015 --> 01:42:28,267
感谢上帝。我快没人了。
Thank God. I'm running out of people, fast.

1894
01:42:29,560 --> 01:42:33,522
几个重要人物，我相信你想见见他们。是这样吗?
Some important men who, uh, I believe you wanted to meet. Is that right?

1895
01:42:33,606 --> 01:42:35,042
是的。是的，我想见见他们。
Yeah. Yes, I would like to meet them.

1896
01:42:35,066 --> 01:42:37,568
伯伦森，我们可以去见我们说过的那些人。
Berendsen, we can meet these people that we talked about.

1897
01:42:37,651 --> 01:42:39,445
瓦莱丽，你跳舞的样子真可爱。
Valerie, you looked so lovely dancing.

1898
01:42:39,528 --> 01:42:41,288
也许你该和朋友们待在这里。
Maybe you should stay here with your friends.

1899
01:42:41,781 --> 01:42:44,033
汤姆·沃兹在和将军说话。
There's Tom Voze talking to the general.

1900
01:42:44,116 --> 01:42:45,409
哦,是的。
Oh, yes.

1901
01:42:45,493 --> 01:42:48,329
我一辈子都在躲着这些人。
I spent my whole life avoiding these people.

1902
01:42:48,412 --> 01:42:49,830
我也这么想，将军。
I feel the exact same way, General.

1903
01:42:49,914 --> 01:42:52,625
这些可能是比较好的，值得一试的。
These might be some of the better ones worth giving a chance.

1904
01:42:59,423 --> 01:43:03,803
迪伦贝克将军，我是内文斯电信的内文斯先生。
General Dillenbeck, this is Mr. Nevins of Nevins Telecommunications.

1905
01:43:03,886 --> 01:43:08,140
贝尔波特先生，贝尔波特化工公司，杰弗斯新闻连锁店的杰弗斯先生。
Mr. Belport, Belport Chemicals, Mr. Jeffers of Jeffers Newschain.

1906
01:43:13,312 --> 01:43:17,626
我们本想邀请汤姆林森先生，传奇汽车发明家，但他今晚来不了。
We wanted to have Mr. Tomlinson, legendary auto inventor, but he couldn't be here tonight.

1907
01:43:17,650 --> 01:43:20,236
他在慕尼黑有个很棒的公司。
He has a fantastic operation in Munich.

1908
01:43:21,737 --> 01:43:23,531
吉尔，我可以叫你吉尔吗?
Gil, may I call you Gil?

1909
01:43:23,614 --> 01:43:25,491
不。你可以叫我将军。
No. You can call me General.

1910
01:43:25,574 --> 01:43:26,951
他更喜欢将军。
He prefers General.

1911
01:43:27,034 --> 01:43:29,495
吉尔，我明白。我们理解。
Gil, I understand. We understand.

1912
01:43:29,578 --> 01:43:31,163
他更喜欢被称为将军。
He prefers to be called General.

1913
01:43:31,247 --> 01:43:32,248
最近怎么样，吉尔?
How's it going, Gil?

1914
01:43:32,331 --> 01:43:33,999
安德鲁·内文斯报道。你可以叫我安迪。
I'm Andrew Nevins. You can call me Andy.

1915
01:43:34,083 --> 01:43:37,253
好吧，我叫你安迪。你叫我将军。
Well, I'll call you Andy. You call me General.

1916
01:43:37,336 --> 01:43:40,965
我是来为我朋友比尔·米金斯的死算账的。
I'm here to reckon for the death of my friend Bill Meekins.

1917
01:43:41,048 --> 01:43:42,091
哦，那是谁?
Oh, who's that?

1918
01:43:42,591 --> 01:43:45,803
比尔Meekins吗?我们今晚要向他致敬。
Bill Meekins? We're honoring him tonight.

1919
01:43:46,345 --> 01:43:47,805
负责债券交易。
Ran the bond exchange.

1920
01:43:47,888 --> 01:43:50,057
当然，我对发生的事非常抱歉。
Of course, I'm terribly sorry about what happened.

1921
01:43:50,141 --> 01:43:51,142
我差点忘了。
I almost forgot.

1922
01:43:51,225 --> 01:43:52,309
女儿的悲剧。
Tragedy with the daughter.

1923
01:43:52,393 --> 01:43:53,894
可怕的悲剧。
Terrible tragedy.

1924
01:43:53,978 --> 01:43:58,023
我期待着今晚与你们谈谈海外的商业机会。
I look forward to speaking with you tonight about business opportunities overseas.

1925
01:43:58,107 --> 01:44:03,237
由于强有力的领导，我们在慕尼黑的工厂获得了惊人的回报。
Our plant in Munich is getting fantastic returns because of strong leadership.

1926
01:44:03,320 --> 01:44:04,905
知道如何把事情做好。
Knowing how to get things done.

1927
01:44:05,489 --> 01:44:06,907
让我们干一杯。
Let's have a toast.

1928
01:44:07,950 --> 01:44:10,953
是的，好的。很好。我们是三个人。
Yes, all right. Good. We are the three.

1929
01:44:11,036 --> 01:44:13,497
汤姆，你可以是第四个，就像我们在打高尔夫球一样。
Tom, you could be the fourth, like we're playing golf.

1930
01:44:13,581 --> 01:44:16,625
为了好运，我们需要一个合适的第五名。
And for good luck, we need a proper fifth.

1931
01:44:16,709 --> 01:44:17,710
将军?
General?

1932
01:44:21,213 --> 01:44:22,715
你能进来一下吗?
Won't you please step in?

1933
01:44:26,260 --> 01:44:27,261
敬将军。
To the general.

1934
01:44:27,344 --> 01:44:28,405
-将军。-敬将军。
- The general. - To the general.

1935
01:44:28,429 --> 01:44:29,430
一般。
To General.

1936
01:44:34,685 --> 01:44:37,354
说什么跟着错误的上帝回家。
Talk about following the wrong God home.

1937
01:44:38,355 --> 01:44:43,319
还有什么比美国企业建立的独裁政权更不美国的呢?
What's more un-American than a dictatorship built by American business?

1938
01:44:43,402 --> 01:44:46,131
这里有两个属性，将军，如果您想要使用它们的话。
There are two properties, General, if you should ever want to use them.

1939
01:44:46,155 --> 01:44:47,448
你或你的家人。
You or your family.

1940
01:44:47,531 --> 01:44:50,659
位于马里兰州的先锋点，贝尔波特化学品的故乡。
Pioneer Point in Maryland, the home state of Belport Chemicals.

1941
01:44:50,743 --> 01:44:53,746
这是你和老兵们的好去处。
A great retreat for you or the veterans.

1942
01:44:53,829 --> 01:44:55,289
还有一个在东汉普顿。
And another one out in East Hampton.

1943
01:44:55,372 --> 01:44:56,600
你和你的家人可能会喜欢。
You and your family might like it.

1944
01:44:56,624 --> 01:45:01,045
我会考虑的，不过我和妻子喜欢泽西海岸的小房子。
I'll think about it, though the wife and I enjoy a little place on the Jersey Shore.

1945
01:45:01,128 --> 01:45:03,756
也许你需要更大的想象力，将军。
Maybe you need a larger imagination, General.

1946
01:45:05,090 --> 01:45:07,218
所以我们才会在这里。
That's how we all ended up here.

1947
01:45:08,010 --> 01:45:11,222
别管这些人，将军。他们认为他们拥有世界。
Never mind these men, General. They think they own the world.

1948
01:45:11,305 --> 01:45:13,057
是时候继续你的演讲了。
It's time to be getting on with your speech.

1949
01:45:14,808 --> 01:45:16,644
我们期待您的演讲。
We're looking forward to your speech.

1950
01:45:35,120 --> 01:45:40,417
现在，第369届的特邀明星奥吉，出现在眼镜上。
And now, a featured star of the 369th, Auggie, on the glasses.

1951
01:45:47,091 --> 01:45:48,425
那是什么?
What is that?

1952
01:45:50,427 --> 01:45:53,013
这是苏黎世最好的创新之一。
This is one of the finest innovations from Zurich.

1953
01:45:53,097 --> 01:45:55,641
消除所有的痛苦和焦虑。
Removes all pain, all anxiety.

1954
01:45:55,724 --> 01:45:56,725
嗯?
Hmm?

1955
01:45:58,727 --> 01:46:01,730
所有不必要的想法占据了头脑。
All needless thoughts that occupy the mind.

1956
01:46:09,446 --> 01:46:10,990
我的背疼死了。
My back is killing me.

1957
01:46:11,073 --> 01:46:18,831
通常情况下，像我这样的人，我们不得不求助于酒精和吗啡，而这可能会导致上瘾……哦，太快了。
Now, normally, guys like me, we have to turn to booze and morphine, and that can lead to addiction... Oh, that's fast.

1958
01:46:18,914 --> 01:46:20,749
这是先进的。
That is advanced.

1959
01:46:20,833 --> 01:46:22,585
哦，那是巨大的能量。
Oh, that is tremendous energy.

1960
01:46:23,711 --> 01:46:25,838
-我不疼。-很好，不是吗?
- I feel no pain. - It's good, isn't it?

1961
01:46:25,921 --> 01:46:27,089
这很好。
That is good.

1962
01:46:27,172 --> 01:46:29,383
伯特，这事还没完呢。
There's more where this came from, Burt.

1963
01:46:29,925 --> 01:46:31,343
我想多了解一点。
I wanna know more about this.

1964
01:46:31,427 --> 01:46:33,679
我想要这种化合物。
I would love to have the chemical compound.

1965
01:46:33,762 --> 01:46:40,644
当我和我的姐妹们在Vril Society聚会时，我们会举办一个séance，在那里我们可以放松一下，它就像一种天线。
When I get together with my sisters at the Vril Society, we hold a séance where we let our hair down, and it acts as a kind of antenna.

1966
01:46:40,728 --> 01:46:42,938
它让我们与更伟大的种族交流。
It allows us to communicate with the greater race.

1967
01:46:43,022 --> 01:46:44,898
说实话，他们来自另一个星系。
Honestly, they come from a different galaxy.

1968
01:46:44,982 --> 01:46:46,525
这真的很吸引人。
It's truly fascinating.

1969
01:46:49,486 --> 01:46:51,905
现在是辛森兄弟。
And now, the Hinson Brothers.

1970
01:46:53,824 --> 01:47:05,753
西班牙夫人，我崇拜你从我第一次见到你的那天晚上我就想对你今晚的演讲说一些友好的建议，将军。
Lady of Spain, I adore you Right from the night I first saw you I wanted to say, for your speech tonight, General, some friendly advice.

1971
01:47:05,836 --> 01:47:08,505
求你了，求你了，别给他任何友好的建议。
Oh, please, please, please, don't give him any friendly advice.

1972
01:47:08,589 --> 01:47:10,674
是啊，有什么友好的建议吗?
Oh, yeah, well, what's the friendly advice?

1973
01:47:12,551 --> 01:47:15,429
今晚，人们将通过广播收听你的演讲。
Tonight, people will be listening to you on the radio.

1974
01:47:15,512 --> 01:47:20,100
你永远不会有更多的观众，也不会有更多的人关注你。
You'll never have a bigger audience with more excited attention from everyone.

1975
01:47:20,184 --> 01:47:23,062
他们会从你身上寻找灵感。
They'll be looking to you for inspiration.

1976
01:47:23,729 --> 01:47:31,945
记住那些为我们流血牺牲的退伍军人，记住比尔·米金斯，向他致以崇高的敬意。
Remember the veterans who have bled and died on our behalf, and remember Bill Meekins and honor him respectfully.

1977
01:47:32,029 --> 01:47:41,288
如果你因为米金斯的死而突发奇想，在复杂的犯罪案件中迷失了方向，这会给你带来不好的影响，我们不希望你这样，将军。
If you improvise and get lost in the woods of some complicated criminal situation over Meekins's death, it will reflect badly on you, and we don't want that for you, General.

1978
01:47:42,498 --> 01:47:48,587
将军说得很清楚他会尊重比尔·米金斯并说出真相。
The general was very clear about that he was gonna honor Bill Meekins and tell the truth.

1979
01:47:49,838 --> 01:47:51,465
嗯，我就是这个意思。
Well, that's exactly what I mean.

1980
01:47:51,548 --> 01:47:53,676
关注米金斯的优点。
Focus on the good qualities Meekins had.

1981
01:47:53,759 --> 01:47:55,928
他的安静和他的善良。
His quietness and his kindness.

1982
01:47:56,011 --> 01:47:58,889
这就是我打算用自己的方式去做的。
That's what I intend to do in my own way.

1983
01:48:06,397 --> 01:48:08,315
-那是什么?-摸摸这个。
- What is that? - Feel this.

1984
01:48:08,691 --> 01:48:09,942
这是海象。
This is walrus.

1985
01:48:11,151 --> 01:48:12,945
哦，好软。
Oh, that is soft.

1986
01:48:14,405 --> 01:48:15,989
一只海象因此被杀?
A walrus was killed for this?

1987
01:48:16,073 --> 01:48:22,496
不，先生，他是老死的。因为他做出了明智的选择，他活得又长又幸福。
No, sir, he died of old age. He lived a long, happy life because he made smart choices.

1988
01:48:24,415 --> 01:48:26,333
这是对你的基金会的贡献。
It's a contribution for your foundation.

1989
01:48:27,376 --> 01:48:28,961
我没有基金会。
I don't have a foundation.

1990
01:48:29,420 --> 01:48:31,630
好吧，也许你应该开始一个。我可以帮你。
Well, maybe you should start one. I can help you.

1991
01:48:31,714 --> 01:48:33,966
36000美元,一般。
$36,000, General.

1992
01:48:34,049 --> 01:48:37,553
想想你能用伯伦森医生和他的医疗创新做什么。
Think of everything you can do with Dr. Berendsen and his medical innovations.

1993
01:48:37,636 --> 01:48:39,054
有这么多事情要做。
So much to be accomplished.

1994
01:48:39,138 --> 01:48:40,806
你必须拿钱。
You have to take the money.

1995
01:48:40,889 --> 01:48:42,516
什么叫我得接?
What do you mean, I have to take it?

1996
01:48:43,600 --> 01:48:53,485
听我说。有人，而不是我，会把你的脸和你的名字，登在《纽约时报》上，然后用它来擦他们的狗屁股。
Listen to me. Someone, not me, they will take your face and your name, put it in the New York Times, and wipe their dog's ass with it.

1997
01:48:54,862 --> 01:48:57,781
想想你一生中所完成的一切。
Think of everything you've accomplished in your life.

1998
01:48:57,865 --> 01:48:59,992
它会被遗忘，被抹去。
It'll be forgotten, erased.

1999
01:49:01,201 --> 01:49:05,247
你会被当成老疯子被历史埋葬。
You'll be treated like an old kook and buried by history.

2000
01:49:05,330 --> 01:49:09,918
这就是他们能做的。做正确的演讲。
That's what they can do. Make the right speech.

2001
01:49:10,753 --> 01:49:14,548
不然他们会把你变成殉道者说是无政府主义者干的。
Or they'll turn you into a martyr and say an anarchist did it.

2002
01:49:15,591 --> 01:49:17,801
别犯比尔·米金斯那样的错误。
Don't make the mistake like Bill Meekins.

2003
01:49:17,885 --> 01:49:20,345
那是一起悲惨的生命盗窃案。
That was a tragic theft of a life.

2004
01:49:20,429 --> 01:49:23,223
西班牙夫人，我爱你
Lady of Spain, I love you

2005
01:49:26,310 --> 01:49:28,187
那是欣森兄弟。
That was the Hinson Brothers.

2006
01:49:29,146 --> 01:49:30,731
辛森兄弟，他们很棒。
The Hinson Brothers, they were great.

2007
01:49:30,814 --> 01:49:32,316
你不同意吗?是的。
Don't you agree? Yes.

2008
01:49:32,399 --> 01:49:35,611
Hinson兄弟。在做，呃，西班牙夫人。
Hinson Brothers. Doing, uh, Lady of Spain.

2009
01:49:35,694 --> 01:49:40,908
是的，西班牙夫人。我曾经遇到一位西班牙女士，她把我变成了一个痛苦的绅士。
Yeah, Lady of Spain. I met a lady of Spain once and she turned me into a gentleman of pain.

2010
01:49:40,991 --> 01:49:42,326
是的。
Yes.

2011
01:49:42,409 --> 01:49:50,834
现在，我要带出来的这位先生是我们团的一名医生我喜欢称他为"朋友"
Now, the gentleman I'm about to bring out right now is a doctor of our regiment and a man I like to call "friend."

2012
01:49:50,918 --> 01:49:53,128
请欢迎伯特·伯伦森。
Please welcome Burt Berendsen.

2013
01:49:53,212 --> 01:49:54,963
来吧，伯特。
Come on, Burt.

2014
01:49:55,047 --> 01:49:58,383
该你演讲了，伯特。伯特?
Time to give your speech, Burt. Burt?

2015
01:49:59,259 --> 01:50:01,220
伯特·伯伦森医生。
Dr. Burt Berendsen.

2016
01:50:06,099 --> 01:50:09,603
我叫伯特·伯伦森。你们大多数人都认识我。
My name is Burt Berendsen. Most of you know me.

2017
01:50:09,686 --> 01:50:13,816
我是埃尔米拉一个机械师的儿子。
I am the son of a mechanic from Elmira.

2018
01:50:14,274 --> 01:50:20,280
作为一个孩子，我们很自然地热爱这个世界。
As a child, we love the world, naturally.

2019
01:50:21,448 --> 01:50:24,868
我们希望全世界都爱我们。
And we hope the world loves us.

2020
01:50:26,620 --> 01:50:32,876
就像我的朋友哈罗德说的，有时我可能跟着错误的上帝回家了。
As my friend Harold said sometimes I might have followed the wrong God home.

2021
01:50:33,418 --> 01:50:34,920
但不是这个人。
Well, not this man.

2022
01:50:36,505 --> 01:50:39,883
他总是跟着正确的上帝回家。
He always followed the right God home.

2023
01:50:45,889 --> 01:50:47,975
Dillenbeck !Dillenbeck !
Dillenbeck! Dillenbeck!

2024
01:50:48,058 --> 01:50:49,476
Dillenbeck !Dillenbeck !
Dillenbeck! Dillenbeck!

2025
01:50:49,560 --> 01:50:50,686
Dillenbeck !
Dillenbeck!

2026
01:50:50,769 --> 01:50:53,564
Dillenbeck !Dillenbeck !Dillenbeck !
Dillenbeck! Dillenbeck! Dillenbeck!

2027
01:50:54,731 --> 01:50:56,733
Drecksgesicht !Drecksgesicht !
Drecksgesicht! Drecksgesicht!

2028
01:50:56,817 --> 01:50:59,069
Drecksgesicht !Drecksgesicht !
Drecksgesicht! Drecksgesicht!

2029
01:51:04,283 --> 01:51:06,869
听那些外滩混蛋的。
Listen to those Bund bastards.

2030
01:51:07,452 --> 01:51:10,080
流血的人，腐烂的人。
Shower of bleeders, rotters.

2031
01:51:11,206 --> 01:51:16,169
如果你们这些用德语对我大喊大叫的人有点勇气，你们就会表现得有尊严。
If you people shouting at me in German had any courage, you would behave with dignity.

2032
01:51:22,885 --> 01:51:24,803
是的!一般Dillenbeck !
Yes! General Dillenbeck!

2033
01:51:27,806 --> 01:51:31,310
我在三大洲参加了五场战争。
I fought in five wars on three continents.

2034
01:51:31,393 --> 01:51:34,146
我这辈子都被人朝我开枪。我的一生。
People shot at me my whole life. My whole life.

2035
01:51:34,229 --> 01:51:36,607
我了解恐惧，也知道如何面对恐惧。
I know fear, and I know facing fear.

2036
01:51:36,690 --> 01:51:44,698
但我真正厌恶的一件事，我真正非常厌恶的一件事，就是残忍。
But the one thing I truly detest, the one thing I truly, truly detest, is cruelty.

2037
01:51:46,575 --> 01:52:04,635
有人给我提供了钱，让我成为那些像你们这样的老兵的自封领袖，根据你们的民意要求，不经选举就能成为白宫的某种顾问。
I've been offered money to become the self-appointed leader of the veterans, veterans like you, to be put in the White House without an election as some sort of advisor by popular demand of you.

2038
01:52:05,719 --> 01:52:12,225
这些人想让我模仿一个叫墨索里尼的欧洲领导人。
These same people want me to emulate a certain European leader named Mussolini.

2039
01:52:15,145 --> 01:52:18,857
他们认为他是这个国家需要的那种领导人。
They think he's the type of leader that this country needs.

2040
01:52:19,566 --> 01:52:25,614
那种会撞死小孩却从不停车的领袖。
The type of leader who ran over a child and never stopped his car.

2041
01:52:27,866 --> 01:52:34,081
这类领导人的借口是，“一个人在国家事务中有什么关系?”
The type of leader whose excuse was, "What's one person in the affairs of the state?"

2042
01:52:36,792 --> 01:52:39,878
比尔·米金斯将军在那辆车里。
General Bill Meekins was in that car.

2043
01:52:40,545 --> 01:52:42,089
他是我的一个朋友。
He was a friend of mine.

2044
01:52:42,172 --> 01:52:43,590
他是个好人。
He was a good person.

2045
01:52:44,466 --> 01:52:56,895
但当他讲了这个故事，当他打算在这个舞台上再讲一遍的时候，他就变成了另一个在国家事务中毫无价值的人。
But when he told that story, when he intended to tell it again here on this stage, he became another person whose life was worth nothing in the affairs of the state.

2046
01:52:57,646 --> 01:52:59,731
他被谋杀了。
He was murdered.

2047
01:52:59,815 --> 01:53:07,114
是的，他被谋杀并蒙羞，就像我今晚在这里讲述这个故事可能会被谋杀或蒙羞一样。
Yes, he was murdered and dishonored, as I might be murdered or dishonored for telling that story here tonight.

2048
01:53:09,241 --> 01:53:11,618
当这种情况发生时，这将成为一个什么样的国家?
What kind of country does this become when that happens?

2049
01:53:13,370 --> 01:53:19,918
我成为一名海军陆战队员是为了服务于宪法，它的宗旨是让我们所有人在人类的兄弟情谊中一律平等。
I became a Marine to serve the Constitution, which intends for us all to be equal in the brotherhood of mankind.

2050
01:53:20,002 --> 01:53:27,134
但当有权势的人为妨碍他们的人破例时又有什么好处呢?
But what good is it when powerful people make exceptions for the people who stand in their way?

2051
01:53:27,968 --> 01:53:36,184
有些有影响力和权力的人喜欢看到普通人被仇恨激怒，因为这分散了我们对公平和善良的注意力。
Some people of influence and power like it when regular folks are fired up by hatred because it distracts us from the fairness and kindness.

2052
01:53:36,810 --> 01:53:44,109
他们不希望我们想太多，这样他们就可以从他们已经拥有的东西中得到越来越多的东西，那是巨大的财富。
They don't want us to think about too much just so they can get more and more of what they already have, which is vast wealth.

2053
01:53:44,901 --> 01:53:46,445
这是你的国家。
This is your country.

2054
01:53:46,528 --> 01:53:48,739
这是你的国家。
This is your country.

2055
01:53:50,699 --> 01:53:52,909
别让大人物把它抢走。
Don't let the big men take it away from you.

2056
01:53:56,371 --> 01:53:59,166
Dillenbeck !Dillenbeck !
Dillenbeck! Dillenbeck!

2057
01:53:59,249 --> 01:54:01,752
Dillenbeck !Dillenbeck !
Dillenbeck! Dillenbeck!

2058
01:54:01,835 --> 01:54:03,420
看，是那个人。
Look, it's that guy.

2059
01:54:03,503 --> 01:54:05,172
我是银行家的儿子。
I'm the son of a banker.

2060
01:54:05,255 --> 01:54:07,799
我是共和党人。
I'm a Republican.

2061
01:54:07,883 --> 01:54:10,510
-保罗和亨利在哪里?-这里不行。
- Where's Paul and Henry? - Not here.

2062
01:54:10,594 --> 01:54:11,595
我是个保守派。
I'm a conservative.

2063
01:54:11,678 --> 01:54:13,072
侦探们呢?你知道他们在哪里吗?
What about the detectives? Do you know where they are?

2064
01:54:13,096 --> 01:54:14,306
这里也没有。
Also not here.

2065
01:54:14,389 --> 01:54:19,895
这就是有钱的人只想要更多钱的那种感觉。
That's what it's like when people who have money only think about wanting much more of it.

2066
01:54:20,771 --> 01:54:22,272
这就是他们所想的。
That's all that they think about.

2067
01:54:22,981 --> 01:54:28,987
他们忘记了是你们出去保护了他们。
And they forget that you are the ones who went out and protected them.

2068
01:54:30,197 --> 01:54:39,372
你失去了一只眼睛或失去了生命，你的家人不得不受苦，尽管他们是把你送上战场的英雄。
You lost an eye or you lost your life, and your family had to suffer, though they were the heroes who sent you off to war.

2069
01:54:42,167 --> 01:54:44,044
朝我开枪的人是个懦夫。
Whoever's shooting at me is a coward.

2070
01:54:44,419 --> 01:54:46,254
我在世界各地都中过枪。
I've been shot at all over the world.

2071
01:54:46,338 --> 01:54:47,547
拿他的枪!
Get his gun!

2072
01:54:49,216 --> 01:54:51,384
我不害怕。我不害怕。
I am not intimidated. I am not afraid.

2073
01:54:52,761 --> 01:54:55,305
-你没事吧?-伯特，你没事吧?
- You all right? - Burt, are you all right?

2074
01:54:55,388 --> 01:54:56,515
莱姆，我没事。我很好。
Lem, I'm fine. I'm fine.

2075
01:55:07,400 --> 01:55:08,944
永远的暴君!
Sic semper tyrannis!

2076
01:55:09,027 --> 01:55:10,779
迪伦贝克是个叛徒!
Dillenbeck's a traitor!

2077
01:55:10,862 --> 01:55:13,115
-阻止那个人。- Tom Voze是个伟大的人!
- Stop that man. - Tom Voze is a great man!

2078
01:55:13,198 --> 01:55:15,492
汤姆·沃兹是个伟大的人!你有……
Tom Voze is a great man! You have...

2079
01:55:19,204 --> 01:55:20,205
打倒那个人。
Keep that man down.

2080
01:55:20,288 --> 01:55:22,541
有罪却合法。问沃兹先生!
Sinful and legal. Ask Mr. Voze!

2081
01:55:27,212 --> 01:55:35,262
我的祖国，美丽的自由之乡，我为你歌唱，Polizei。Polizei。
My country 'Tis of thee Sweet land of liberty Of thee I sing Polizei. Polizei.

2082
01:55:35,470 --> 01:55:37,597
别吵了!别吵了!到这里来。
Break it up! Break it up! Come here.

2083
01:55:41,643 --> 01:55:44,146
我是老兵，也是爱国者，你个傻瓜。
I'm a veteran and a patriot, you fool.

2084
01:55:44,229 --> 01:55:46,398
你杀了莉兹·米金斯，你个混蛋。
You killed Liz Meekins, you son of a bitch.

2085
01:55:47,232 --> 01:55:49,526
据我所知，她父亲也是。
And for all I know, her father too.

2086
01:55:50,193 --> 01:55:52,237
美国财政部!每一个人,离开!
United States Treasury! Everyone, leave!

2087
01:55:53,446 --> 01:55:55,615
-你没事吧?-这太可怕了。
- Are you okay? - This is terrible.

2088
01:55:55,699 --> 01:55:57,579
我们从没想过会发生这种事。
We never meant for anything like this to happen.

2089
01:55:57,617 --> 01:55:58,910
这是一种暴行。
This is an outrage.

2090
01:55:58,994 --> 01:56:00,036
你会被起诉的。
You're gonna be charged.

2091
01:56:00,120 --> 01:56:01,454
你会被起诉的，汤姆。
You're gonna be charged, Tom.

2092
01:56:01,538 --> 01:56:02,539
你。是的,你。
You. Yes, you.

2093
01:56:02,622 --> 01:56:03,623
不，先生，你搞错了。
No, sir. You are confused.

2094
01:56:03,707 --> 01:56:04,708
不，我没糊涂。
No, I'm not confused.

2095
01:56:04,791 --> 01:56:12,299
除了我自己吃的药和挨枪子，这些眼药水是我能站起来感觉不到疼痛的唯一原因。
Between my own pill and getting shot, these eye drops are the only reason I'm standing and I feel no pain.

2096
01:56:13,049 --> 01:56:17,470
我的天!看看这房间里发生了什么。
And holy shit! Look what's happening in this room.

2097
01:56:17,554 --> 01:56:18,555
一切。
Everything.

2098
01:56:18,638 --> 01:56:19,949
五人委员会的枪。
Gun from the Committee of the Five.

2099
01:56:19,973 --> 01:56:22,684
他骄傲地叫你的名字，汤姆。
He called you by your name, Tom, with pride.

2100
01:56:22,767 --> 01:56:24,019
我不认识那个人。
I don't know that man.

2101
01:56:24,102 --> 01:56:25,687
我们只是为了活命才和他搏斗。
We just fought that man for our lives.

2102
01:56:25,770 --> 01:56:27,123
伯特和我看到他推莉斯·米金斯。
Burt and I saw him push Liz Meekins.

2103
01:56:27,147 --> 01:56:28,148
他是凶手。
He's the killer.

2104
01:56:28,940 --> 01:56:30,400
有足够的证据。
There is enough evidence.

2105
01:56:30,483 --> 01:56:40,452
我很遗憾地告诉你今晚在舞台上向迪伦贝克将军开枪的人就是和米金斯在船上的那个人，他的船票是你们基金会买的。
I am sorry to say that the man who took a shot at General Dillenbeck on that stage tonight was the same man on the boat with Meekins, on a ticket purchased by your foundation.

2106
01:56:40,535 --> 01:56:41,679
没有必要提高你的嗓门。
There is no need to raise your voice.

2107
01:56:41,703 --> 01:56:43,330
你的，沃兹先生。
Yours, Mr. Voze.

2108
01:56:43,413 --> 01:56:44,456
汤姆，发生什么事了?
Tom, what's happening?

2109
01:56:44,539 --> 01:56:45,540
费用是什么?
What are the charges?

2110
01:56:45,624 --> 01:56:47,852
指控的对象是你和你邀请的客人。
The charges are against you and the guests you invited.

2111
01:56:47,876 --> 01:56:49,878
-五国委员会。-为什么?
- The Committee of the Five. - For what?

2112
01:56:49,961 --> 01:56:51,087
五人委员会。
Committee of the Five.

2113
01:56:51,171 --> 01:56:53,173
密谋贿赂美国将军。
Conspiracy to bribe a United States general.

2114
01:56:53,256 --> 01:56:55,550
暗杀未遂。
Attempted assassination.

2115
01:56:55,634 --> 01:56:57,844
阴谋推翻美国政府。
Conspiracy to overthrow the US government.

2116
01:56:57,928 --> 01:57:00,639
和独裁者，意大利，德国进行贸易。
Trading with dictators, Italy, Germany.

2117
01:57:00,722 --> 01:57:06,228
你的基金会显然与两起谋杀案有关，米金斯和他女儿。
Two murders your foundation apparently seems to be responsible for, Meekins and his daughter.

2118
01:57:06,311 --> 01:57:07,812
汤姆，是你干的吗?
Tom, did you do this?

2119
01:57:07,896 --> 01:57:09,981
我觉得米金斯的死是不对的。
I felt it was wrong that Meekins died.

2120
01:57:10,065 --> 01:57:11,816
那是一起悲惨的生命盗窃案。
That was a tragic theft of a life.

2121
01:57:12,525 --> 01:57:18,281
但他必须做点什么，因为他没有看到新的生活方式带来的机遇。
But something had to be done because he didn't see the opportunity of the new ways to live.

2122
01:57:18,365 --> 01:57:20,492
他不明白。米金斯不明白。
He didn't understand. Meekins didn't understand.

2123
01:57:20,575 --> 01:57:21,701
你明白吗?
Do you understand that?

2124
01:57:21,785 --> 01:57:23,245
好的。你得放慢速度。
All right. You need to slow it down.

2125
01:57:23,745 --> 01:57:27,040
汤姆，别告诉我你和我的药有任何关系。
Tom, please tell me you didn't have anything to do with my medication.

2126
01:57:27,123 --> 01:57:31,753
汤姆影响了你的医生，瓦莱丽，就像他以前对你母亲一样。
Tom influenced your doctor, Valerie, as he had done with your mother before.

2127
01:57:35,882 --> 01:57:37,759
-是真的吗?-有一点。
- Is that true? - A little.

2128
01:57:38,385 --> 01:57:39,469
一个小?
A little?

2129
01:57:40,345 --> 01:57:41,680
我这么做是为了你好。
I did it for your own good.

2130
01:57:41,763 --> 01:57:42,847
你给我下毒?
You poisoned me?

2131
01:57:42,931 --> 01:57:45,809
如果你想这么说，好吧。
If that's what you want to call it, fine.

2132
01:57:46,434 --> 01:57:49,729
我是在照顾你，为了你的最大利益。
I was looking after you, your best interests.

2133
01:57:50,272 --> 01:57:52,607
你太鲁莽了，像个孩子。
You're reckless, like a child.

2134
01:57:53,358 --> 01:57:59,030
听我说。你在欧洲到处跑，说战争的坏话?
Listen to me. You're running around all over Europe and saying bad things about the war?

2135
01:58:00,115 --> 01:58:01,908
和一个黑人交往。
Consorting with a Black man.

2136
01:58:03,201 --> 01:58:10,250
在阿姆斯特丹，和一个为你而战的自由人在一起!
Consorting with a man, a free man, in Amsterdam, that fought for you!

2137
01:58:10,834 --> 01:58:12,419
比如诊所，汤姆?
Like the clinics, Tom?

2138
01:58:13,128 --> 01:58:14,254
诊所是什么?
What clinics?

2139
01:58:14,337 --> 01:58:15,922
五人委员会。
Committee of the Five.

2140
01:58:16,006 --> 01:58:17,882
你知道我在说什么诊所，汤姆。
You know what clinics I'm talking about, Tom.

2141
01:58:17,966 --> 01:58:19,718
强制绝育。
Forced sterilization.

2142
01:58:19,801 --> 01:58:20,969
我们走着瞧吧。
We'll see about that.

2143
01:58:21,052 --> 01:58:25,181
我们看到了五人委员会的标志——在那里。-别撒谎了!
We saw the Committee of the Five symbol - there. - Stop lying!

2144
01:58:25,640 --> 01:58:32,397
汤姆有阴谋并不奇怪，但可怕的是……我的上帝。就在瓦莱丽的眼皮底下。
That Tom had an angle was no surprise, but the horror of it... My God. Right under Valerie's nose.

2145
01:58:32,480 --> 01:58:35,483
他们用编造的条件分散她的注意力。
They kept her distracted with the invented condition.

2146
01:58:36,359 --> 01:58:41,656
戈林，希特勒的得力助手，还有希特勒本人。
Goering, Hitler's right-hand man, and Hitler himself.

2147
01:58:41,740 --> 01:58:43,992
大多数人都不知道他是谁。
Most people didn't even know who he was yet.

2148
01:58:45,327 --> 01:58:50,332
汤姆甚至付钱让戈林在杰弗斯的报纸上写一篇关于雅利安新政府的专栏。
Tom even paid Goering to write a column in the Jeffers papers about the new Aryan government.

2149
01:58:50,415 --> 01:58:52,208
不管那是什么。
Whatever that was.

2150
01:58:54,919 --> 01:58:58,173
汤姆刚刚完成了带有符号的修剪。
Tom had just finished the topiary with the symbol.

2151
01:58:58,256 --> 01:59:00,925
你只能从上面看。
You couldn't see it except from above.

2152
01:59:01,968 --> 01:59:06,890
我是说，你一定是某种超级狂热的信徒才能把你的灌木弄成那样。
I mean, you gotta be some kind of super-fanatic believer to make your bushes like that.

2153
01:59:06,973 --> 01:59:08,451
别那样看着我，莉比。
Don't you look at me like that, Libby.

2154
01:59:08,475 --> 01:59:09,476
瓦莱丽,亲爱的。
Valerie, darling.

2155
01:59:09,559 --> 01:59:11,895
所有伟大的社会都是这样建立起来的。
All great societies are built this way.

2156
01:59:12,520 --> 01:59:14,689
你和你那些奇怪的雕塑生活在一个梦幻的世界里。
You live in a dream world with your strange sculptures.

2157
01:59:14,773 --> 01:59:16,358
这很好。你可以拿走。
And that's fine. You can have that.

2158
01:59:16,441 --> 01:59:18,026
但它不能使世界转动。
But it won't make the world go round.

2159
01:59:18,109 --> 01:59:22,697
我很高兴自己不重要，生活在一个有爱和美丽的地方。
I'm very happy to be unimportant and live in a place that has love and beauty.

2160
01:59:22,781 --> 01:59:31,748
艺术和爱，这才是让生命有价值的东西，而你却在创造这个巨大而可怕的未来。
Art and love, that's what makes the life worth living, while you're building this big, gigantic, terrifying future.

2161
01:59:32,499 --> 01:59:34,542
真是浪费你的想象力。
What a waste of your imagination.

2162
01:59:34,626 --> 01:59:38,630
我为我们做了很多，重建德国。
I made plenty, for us, rebuilding Germany.

2163
01:59:39,297 --> 01:59:42,050
我想和世界上最强大的领导人站在一起。
I wanted to stand with the strongest leaders in the world.

2164
01:59:42,717 --> 01:59:44,761
但我也很乐意与他们作战。
But I'm also happy to go to war against them.

2165
01:59:45,303 --> 01:59:48,598
另一场战争吗?但我们刚刚都做了。
Another war? But we just did all that.

2166
01:59:49,891 --> 01:59:55,980
你是说这些有钱人会支持独裁者还是反抗独裁者?
You mean to tell me these rich guys will support dictators or fight them?

2167
01:59:56,064 --> 01:59:58,691
他们只相信赚钱。
They believe in nothing but making money.

2168
01:59:59,234 --> 02:00:04,447
所以米金斯才被杀，就因为他不同意也不支持吗?
And that's why Meekins was killed, because he wouldn't go along with that or support it?

2169
02:00:04,531 --> 02:00:05,824
精神错乱!
Insanity!

2170
02:00:06,491 --> 02:00:08,743
我们就这样走了进去。
And we have walked right into it.

2171
02:00:08,827 --> 02:00:10,578
不。哦，不，不，不。
No. Oh, no, no, no.

2172
02:00:11,162 --> 02:00:15,208
——啊……汤姆很快就认为我们是他抓到将军的最好机会。
- Ah... - Tom quickly saw us as his best chance to get the general.

2173
02:00:15,792 --> 02:00:20,422
如果你能让吉尔·迪伦贝克这样的人参与你的活动，对我也有帮助。
If you got someone like Gil Dillenbeck involved with your event, it would help me to get involved.

2174
02:00:20,505 --> 02:00:25,385
你需要人帮忙吗?你总是……-他总是需要一个人…-瓦莱丽，-你能消停会吗?-在他面前。
So, you need someone? You always... - He always needs someone... - Valerie, - would you give it a rest? - In front of him.

2175
02:00:25,760 --> 02:00:28,513
你想利用这些人来抓我。
You thought you'd use these men to get me.

2176
02:00:28,596 --> 02:00:34,602
但我利用他们和他们的活动揭露了你阻止了你的计划至少十年。
But I used them and their event to reveal you and stop your plan for at least a decade.

2177
02:00:34,686 --> 02:00:37,230
也许还有两三个，希望如此。
Maybe two or three more, hopefully.

2178
02:00:38,314 --> 02:00:40,650
我们确实阻止了阴谋。
We did stop the plot.

2179
02:00:41,776 --> 02:00:42,861
这是真的。
This is true.

2180
02:00:45,113 --> 02:00:49,117
五国委员会没有找到他们的美国独裁者。
The Committee of the Five didn't get their American dictator.

2181
02:00:49,200 --> 02:00:58,293
我在国会委员会，美国人民的最高代表面前，应传票说出我所知道的……将军在国会作证，
I appeared before the congressional committee, the highest representation of the American people, under subpoena to tell what I knew of... The general testified to Congress,

2182
02:00:58,376 --> 02:01:01,087
他们一致认为他是对的。
and they agreed he was right.

2183
02:01:01,838 --> 02:01:04,757
有权势的人想要什么?
What do powerful people want?

2184
02:01:04,841 --> 02:01:06,509
这还不够吗?
Is it never enough?

2185
02:01:06,593 --> 02:01:08,845
他们做最疯狂的事。
They do the craziest things.

2186
02:01:15,518 --> 02:01:17,353
我的天啊!你怎么了?
Oh, my God! What's the matter with you?

2187
02:01:17,437 --> 02:01:18,438
你到底做了什么?
What the hell did you do?

2188
02:01:18,521 --> 02:01:19,999
我的天啊!瓦莱丽，你做了什么?
Oh, my God! Valerie, what have you done?

2189
02:01:20,023 --> 02:01:21,709
你怎么了?你做了什么?
What's the matter with you? What did you do?

2190
02:01:21,733 --> 02:01:25,820
我们有了起诉的所有证据，现在一切都泡影了!
We had everything we needed to prosecute, and now it's all out the window!

2191
02:01:25,904 --> 02:01:27,322
现在这是一个大问题。
It's a huge problem now.

2192
02:01:27,405 --> 02:01:28,448
是的，干得好。
Yes, well done.

2193
02:01:28,531 --> 02:01:33,328
汤姆，我的脸。她毁了我的脸!
Tom, my face. She ruined my face!

2194
02:01:33,411 --> 02:01:36,289
我没办法。它们太可怕了。
I couldn't help it. They're so awful.

2195
02:01:36,372 --> 02:01:37,874
女人，你疯了吗?
Woman, have you lost your mind?

2196
02:01:37,957 --> 02:01:39,375
我说过她是个麻烦。
I told you she was trouble.

2197
02:01:39,459 --> 02:01:40,853
是啊，那太蠢了，瓦莱丽。
Yeah, that was rather stupid, Valerie.

2198
02:01:40,877 --> 02:01:41,979
你会进监狱的，瓦莱丽。
You could go to jail, Valerie.

2199
02:01:42,003 --> 02:01:43,630
告诉他们真相，哈罗德。
Tell them the truth, Harold.

2200
02:01:47,091 --> 02:01:49,219
你没事吧，瓦莱丽?你颤抖。
Are you all right, Valerie? You're shaking.

2201
02:01:51,387 --> 02:01:54,724
哦，我很好。我只是想一枪打爆汤姆和莉比的脸。
Oh, I'm fine. I was just thinking about shooting Tom and Libby in the face.

2202
02:01:54,807 --> 02:01:57,477
——嗯。-我不会做的。别担心。
- Hmm. - I won't do it. Don't worry.

2203
02:01:57,560 --> 02:01:59,120
嗯，这是个好决定。感谢上帝。
Well, that's a good decision. Thank God.

2204
02:01:59,145 --> 02:02:01,415
是的，它会毁了一切。我们就没有案子了。
Yes, it would've bollocksed everything. We'd have no case.

2205
02:02:01,439 --> 02:02:04,567
你必须勇敢地面对他们，就像我们所做的那样。
You have to stand up to them, as we had done.

2206
02:02:04,651 --> 02:02:07,195
你必须活出真实的自己。
And you have to live your truth.

2207
02:02:09,572 --> 02:02:10,573
我爱哈罗德。
I love Harold.

2208
02:02:11,241 --> 02:02:15,245
他给了我生命中最大的幸福，伯特也是。
He's given me the greatest happiness of my life, as has Burt.

2209
02:02:27,257 --> 02:02:29,509
就在那儿。看那个。
There it is. Look at that.

2210
02:02:30,176 --> 02:02:32,470
这就是你面对这个世界的方式。
That's how you face such a world.

2211
02:02:33,555 --> 02:02:37,016
你必须对你的生活充满爱。
You must have love in your heart for your life.

2212
02:02:38,059 --> 02:02:40,979
这是爱与恨的较量。
It is love versus hate.

2213
02:02:41,646 --> 02:02:44,440
我爱我的生活和生活中的人。
I love my life and the people in it.

2214
02:02:45,942 --> 02:02:47,151
甚至比阿特丽斯。
Even Beatrice.

2215
02:02:47,819 --> 02:02:51,072
而且很清楚，不是葡萄牙语，我爱上了她的厄玛。
And clear, not Portuguese, I'm-in-love-with-her Irma.

2216
02:02:51,155 --> 02:02:52,490
弥尔顿。
Milton.

2217
02:02:52,574 --> 02:02:55,118
雪莉和莫蒂在办公室。
Shirley at the office with Morty.

2218
02:02:55,952 --> 02:02:58,413
挂毯。里面的所有东西。
The tapestry. Everything in it.

2219
02:02:59,205 --> 02:03:01,040
甚至我的玻璃眼睛。
Even my glass eye.

2220
02:03:01,124 --> 02:03:04,377
迪伦贝克的狗和我们没吃到的鱼汤。
Dillenbeck's dog and the bouillabaisse we didn't get to have.

2221
02:03:05,587 --> 02:03:09,382
我们每个人都有一幅挂毯，属于我们自己的歌剧。
Each one of us is given a tapestry, our own opera.

2222
02:03:09,465 --> 02:03:11,301
这个人和这个人。
This person and this person.

2223
02:03:11,384 --> 02:03:12,802
正在考虑。
Thinking about it.

2224
02:03:14,304 --> 02:03:15,930
光有爱是不够的。
Love is not enough.

2225
02:03:16,014 --> 02:03:18,308
你得为保护善良而奋斗。
You got to fight to protect kindness.

2226
02:03:19,225 --> 02:03:21,853
你会对人和事产生依恋。
You get attached to people and things.

2227
02:03:23,021 --> 02:03:25,315
他们可能会让你心碎。
And they might just break your heart.

2228
02:03:25,398 --> 02:03:26,941
但那就是活着。
But that's being alive.

2229
02:03:28,776 --> 02:03:32,572
我很不喜欢的背撑救了我。
My back brace that I so disliked had saved me from this bullet.

2230
02:03:32,655 --> 02:03:34,115
你这个幸运的混蛋。
You lucky bastard.

2231
02:03:34,198 --> 02:03:36,993
我们三个帮助阻止了这个可怕的阴谋。
And we three had helped stop this terrible plot.

2232
02:03:37,076 --> 02:03:38,328
我真不敢相信。
I can't believe that.

2233
02:03:38,411 --> 02:03:42,790
伯特·伯伦森，哈罗德·伍德曼，瓦莱丽·沃兹。
Burt Berendsen, Harold Woodman, and Valerie Voze.

2234
02:03:43,374 --> 02:03:47,754
混蛋,奈文斯……汤姆不会被拘留太久。
Jerks, Nevins... Tom would not stay arrested long.

2235
02:03:47,837 --> 02:03:49,505
那些人从来不会。
Those people never do.

2236
02:03:49,589 --> 02:03:51,591
和我的律师谈谈。你会看到。
Talk to my lawyer. You'll see.

2237
02:03:52,383 --> 02:03:55,845
五人委员会从未面临任何指控。
Committee of the Five never faced any charges.

2238
02:03:56,512 --> 02:03:59,349
他们消失了，就像他们会做的那样。
They disappeared, as they can do.

2239
02:04:00,058 --> 02:04:02,435
汤姆和他的朋友们诽谤将军。
Tom and his friends smeared the general.

2240
02:04:04,020 --> 02:04:07,857
这是对他们能力的警告。
It was a warning of what they were capable of.

2241
02:04:09,984 --> 02:04:13,446
马奎尔神秘去世，年仅37岁。
Maguire died mysteriously at the age of 37.

2242
02:04:13,988 --> 02:04:15,573
他知道的太多了。
He knew too much.

2243
02:04:16,574 --> 02:04:19,911
瓦莱丽和哈罗德在这个国家已经不安全了。
Valerie and Harold were no longer safe in this country.

2244
02:04:23,414 --> 02:04:25,583
一辈子的朋友就是一辈子的朋友。
Friends for life means friends for life.

2245
02:04:26,918 --> 02:04:28,461
你要不惜一切代价。
You do whatever it takes.

2246
02:04:28,544 --> 02:04:30,922
那晚我们就得把他们弄上船。
We had to get them on a boat that very night.

2247
02:04:37,512 --> 02:04:40,181
伍德曼，你应该…谢谢你，亨利。
Woodman, you should... Thank you, Henry.

2248
02:04:40,264 --> 02:04:41,974
我早就知道了。我做了决定。
I'm way ahead of you. I made my decision.

2249
02:04:42,433 --> 02:04:43,935
哈罗德和我一起去。
Harold's coming with me.

2250
02:04:44,018 --> 02:04:45,561
不，你和我一起去。
No, you're coming with me.

2251
02:04:45,645 --> 02:04:47,438
不，你和我一起去。
No, you're coming with me.

2252
02:04:49,232 --> 02:04:53,861
你会再见到我的，伯伦森医生，因为历史会重演。
You'll be seeing me again, Dr. Berendsen, because history repeats itself.

2253
02:04:53,945 --> 02:04:56,489
再见，老朋友。阿姆斯特丹见。
Goodbye, old friend. We'll see you in Amsterdam.

2254
02:04:57,115 --> 02:04:59,242
哦,不。你不会去阿姆斯特丹的。
Oh, no. You're not going to Amsterdam.

2255
02:04:59,325 --> 02:05:00,326
什么?
What?

2256
02:05:00,410 --> 02:05:03,788
盖世太保迟早会破门而入的。
It's only a matter of time before the Gestapo kicks down your door.

2257
02:05:03,871 --> 02:05:04,872
毫米。
Mm.

2258
02:05:04,956 --> 02:05:06,332
盖世太保是什么?
What's the Gestapo?

2259
02:05:06,416 --> 02:05:08,376
——哦。-是啊，你不会想知道的
- Oh. - Yeah, you don't wanna know.

2260
02:05:09,127 --> 02:05:11,546
我们会送你去更安全的地方。
We'll, uh, send you somewhere safer.

2261
02:05:11,629 --> 02:05:13,881
每年这个时候天气都很好。
Beautiful weather this time of year.

2262
02:05:13,965 --> 02:05:16,342
还有蓝头病毒的迁移。
And the blue-headed vireo migration to boot.

2263
02:05:16,426 --> 02:05:18,219
是的。这是一个壮观的鸟类之乡。
Yes. It's spectacular bird country.

2264
02:05:18,302 --> 02:05:19,429
-不是吗?——真的。
- Isn't it, though? - Really.

2265
02:05:19,512 --> 02:05:21,514
-是的。-我嫉妒。
- Yeah. - I'm jealous.

2266
02:05:21,597 --> 02:05:22,598
伯特。
Burt.

2267
02:05:23,641 --> 02:05:25,268
伯特，跟我们一起去吧?
Burt, why don't you come with us?

2268
02:05:27,103 --> 02:05:28,271
我选择留下。
I choose to stay.

2269
02:05:28,813 --> 02:05:33,776
谁知道呢?也许我会找到新的生活和新的爱情。-希望如此。
Who knows? Maybe I'll find a new life - and a new love. - I hope so.

2270
02:05:34,902 --> 02:05:38,239
因为说到爱，没有什么比清晰更美好的了。
Because when it comes to love, there's nothing quite so good as clarity.

2271
02:05:38,948 --> 02:05:39,949
我同意。
I agree.

2272
02:05:41,451 --> 02:05:47,290
我留下来是为了我的国家，这样有一天，我最好的朋友们可以回来。
I stayed to stand up for my country so that one day, my best friends could come back.

2273
02:05:51,002 --> 02:05:52,128
再见,伯特。
Goodbye, Burt.

2274
02:05:56,883 --> 02:05:58,509
再见，我的好朋友。
Au revoir, my good friend.

2275
02:06:01,804 --> 02:06:03,514
高兴点吧，伯特!
Be happy, Burt!

2276
02:06:05,391 --> 02:06:08,019
——亨利。保罗。将军。-谢谢。
- Henry. Paul. General. - Thank you.

2277
02:06:08,102 --> 02:06:09,854
-再见了。——弥尔顿。
- Farewell for now. - Milton.

2278
02:06:10,897 --> 02:06:12,774
我有点希望和朋友们一起跑步。
Part of me wished I did run with my friends.

2279
02:06:17,862 --> 02:06:19,280
但我没有。
But I didn't.

2280
02:06:21,073 --> 02:06:27,872
你希望你的心和你的子民跟随正确的神回家。
You want for your heart and for your people to follow the right God home.

2281
02:06:55,066 --> 02:06:56,317
阿姆斯特丹。
Amsterdam.

2282
02:06:57,109 --> 02:06:58,528
阿姆斯特丹。
Amsterdam.

2283
02:07:07,370 --> 02:07:17,588
我在国会委员会，美国人民的最高代表面前，应传票说出我所知道的活动，我认为这些活动可能导致企图…
I appeared before the congressional committee, the highest representation of the American people, under subpoena to tell what I knew of activities, which I believe might lead to an attempt...

2284
02:07:17,672 --> 02:07:20,174
建立法西斯独裁政权。
to set up a fascist dictatorship.

2285
02:07:20,258 --> 02:07:30,226
据我所知，计划是组建一个退伍军人组织，作为恫吓或俱乐部，至少可以恐吓政府并瓦解我们的民主制度。
The plan as outlined to me was to form an organization of veterans, to use as a bluff or as a club, at least to intimidate the government and break down our democratic institutions.


